title: mini cheesecakes
directions: You will need 18 paper muffin cups.

title: hamburg soup
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain grease.
Add onion, tomatoes, water and broth.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Add potatoes and carrot.
Cook until tender.
Then add macaroni.
Cook until done.

title: 8 layer dip
directions: On a 12-inch serving plate, spread bean dip.
Top with remaining ingredients as listed.
Chill an hour before serving. Serve with crackers or Doritos.

title: pears a la creme
directions: About 2 hours before serving, place butter, brown sugar and spices in skillet.
Drain pear halves; arrange on top of butter mixture.
Set aside.
With spoon, scoop out 6 to 8 servings of ice cream into individual bowls and return to freezer until 10 minutes before serving.
Simmer pear halves in butter mixture in skillet for 10 minutes, turning occasionally.
Place a hot pear half on top of ice cream.
Spoon glaze over top of each pear.

title: grandma mills' sour cream raisin pie
directions: Cook raisins in boiling water until plump.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Set aside.
Mix sugar, sour cream and flour in a bowl.
Let set for 5 to 10 minutes to thicken a little.
Add raisins.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 325° until golden brown all over the top.

title: pound cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature before starting. Cream butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla, flour and whipping cream alternately; begin with flour and end with flour.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.

title: sauteed mushrooms
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in large skillet.
Add mushrooms; saute 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Make layers according to directions on box.
Cool.
Punch holes in top of each layer with fork.
Spoon on pineapple.
Frost cake with Butter Cream Frosting.

title: molded gazpacho(lo-cal; 5 cups)
directions: Mix 1 cup tomato juice with gelatin and heat until dissolved. Add rest of tomato juice, wine vinegar and spices.
Chill until it begins to set, then mix with tomatoes, green onions, pepper, cucumber, celery and parsley.
Pour into mold and chill until firm. (Use ring mold.)

title: kathleen's lime and cheese jello
directions: Make jello according to package directions.
Chill until firm. Whip jello and blend in Cool Whip.
Blend in cottage cheese.
Add drained pineapple.
Chill until set.

title: potato casserole
directions: Slice potatoes and parboil.
Place layer of potatoes in baking dish; cover with mixture of soup and sour cream.
Top with cheese and bacon bits.
Repeat with another layer.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Soften yeast in 1/4 cup warm water; let stand 5 minutes.
In large bowl combine milk, hot water and shortening.
Add sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Blend in 2 cups flour.
Add eggs and remaining flour (dough will be soft).
Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight.
Turn soft dough out onto well floured board, turning to coat.
Divide dough into 2 parts.
Roll each part into an 8 x 12-inch rectangle.
Spread with 1/2 butter; sprinkle with cinnamon sugar mixture and raisins.
Roll and pinch ends together. Cut with sharp knife (or use a string) into 1-inch pieces and set onto ungreased baking sheet 2 to 4 inches apart.
Cover.
Let rise 2 1/2 hours or until double.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Cover cabbage leaves with boiling water for 5 minutes; drain. Combine next 6 ingredients and 1/2 can tomato sauce.
Place equal amounts of meat in center of leaves.
Roll up and fasten with toothpick.
Place in large skillet.
Stir in remaining sauce, sugar, lemon juice and water.
Simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese apples
directions: Cook apples until tender.
Drain.
Place in buttered casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle over apples. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: *May use pumpkin pie spices in the can.

title: quickie dip
directions: In a bowl, gently blend spaghetti sauce mix into sour cream. Cover and chill.
Makes 2 cups.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Chop or dice artichoke hearts.
Mix with other ingredients and put in pie plate or quiche pan and bake at 350° for about 40 to 45 minutes.
Spread on crackers.

title: green bean supreme
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1 can onion rings and mix well. Pour into lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Top with remaining onion rings.
Bake until brown.
Makes 8 servings.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in salted water until tender, drain.
Saute onions and carrots in al little bit of margarine until soft.
Mix soup and sour cream together and fold in zucchini.
Melt remaining margarine and mix with the stuffing mix including seasoning packet.
Put half of stuffing mix in bottom of 13
X 9 inch pan. Spread zucchini mixture over the stuffing, then spread carrot and onion mixture over zucchini.
Then put the rest of the stuffing mixture on top.
Bake at 350 for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion. Drain well. Add remaining ingredients. Save enough stuffing to put on top. Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: crunchy green pea salad
directions: Rinse peas in hot water (steam if fresh; drain).
Combine vegetables, nuts and bacon with sour cream.
Mix prepared dressing, mustard and garlic together and pour over salad.
Toss gently.

title: eggnog
directions: Combine well beaten eggs, Eagle Brand milk, vanilla and salt until thoroughly blended.
Gradually beat in milk.
When ready to serve, gently fold in whipped cream, pour into punch bowl or serving cups.
Sprinkle with nutmeg, if desired.

title: barbecue sauce over chicken
directions: Cok sauce 4 minutes and pour over chicken.
Bake at 375° until chicken is done.

title: hot fruit pudding
directions: Peel apples; slice and sprinkle with lemon juice.
In 2 1/2-quart casserole dish, layer apples, pineapple and cranberries.

title: tuna vegetable ala king
directions: In heavy saucepan, melt butter over medium heat.
Stir in onion and flour.
Gradually stir in milk until well blended. Cook, stirring constantly, until well blended, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients except cheese.
Put cheese on top and put in oven until cheese melts.

title: popovers
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Generously grease nonstick popover pan or large size muffin pan.
Stir all ingredients with fork just until smooth (do not overbeat).
Fill cups half full.
Bake 20 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 325°.
Bake about 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Immediately remove from cups.
Serve hot. Makes 6 in popover pan or 8 in muffin pan.

title: all-in-one dinner
directions: Saute ground beef until brown; drain.
Place alternate layers of beef and fresh vegetables in greased casserole dish in order listed.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour tomatoes over all and top with cheese.
Dot with butter.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: kit-kat bars
directions: Mix and bring to boil first 5 ingredients.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Put a layer of whole club crackers on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour 1/2 of boiled mixture over crackers. Put another layer of club crackers.
Pour remaining boiled mixture.
Put a third layer of club crackers.
Frost with chocolate and butterscotch chips and peanut butter, melted together.
Refrigerate until chocolate hardens.
Cut into bars.

title: coleslaw dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and blend well.
A blender may be used to mix.

title: microwave baked beans
directions: Set power select at High. In 1 1/2-quart microwavable casserole dish, heat bacon and onion 3 to 4 minutes or until bacon is cooked.
Drain off fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients; heat, covered with wax paper, 8 to 10 minutes at High.
Stir.
Set power select at Medium-low.
Heat, covered with wax paper, 12 to 15 minutes.
Adjust this cooking stage to thickness of beans desired.

title: sausage rice casserole
directions: Fry sausage until brown.
Put in green pepper, onion and celery until soft.
Put in the 4 cups water with noodle soup and rice.
Add to sausage mixture.
Bake in 350° oven.
Stir after 1/2 hour, then bake 1/2 hour more.

title: turtle cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla; beat until smooth. Layer:
caramel topping on bottom, cream cheese mix next and then chocolate topping.
Put pecans on top.
Bake 1 hour at 400°. Makes 2 pies.

title: salmon pate
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll into a ball.
Roll into either walnuts or chives.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: italian cheesecake
directions: In large mixing bowl with an electric mixer, cream Ricotta cheese and cream cheese.
Add sugar, eggs, vanilla and lemon extract; mix well.
Add flour and cornstarch, then add melted butter.
Fold in sour cream.
Grease a 9-inch spring-form pan and sprinkle generously with graham cracker crumbs.
Pour cheese mixture into pan.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 1 hour.
Then turn off the heat and leave cake in oven 2 hours.
Do not open the oven door during the 3 hours cake is in oven.
This is most important step of recipe.
After the 3 hours, remove cheesecake from oven and cool completely.
Store in refrigerator until serving.

title: avocado cream soup
directions: In saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender but not browned.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper sauce, milk and broth. Cook and stir until smooth and soup comes to a boil.
Simmer, uncovered, about 10 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions in large pan.
Pour salt over this. Let soak 1 1/2 hours.
Mix and soak 1 1/2 hours longer.
Drain and add to boiling vinegar mixture.
Mix remainder of ingredients. Add pickles and onions; heat and put in jars.
Cover with hot juice and seal lids.

title: german baked beans
directions: In large bowl combine all ingredients. Transfer to a 2 qt baking dish coated with non stick cooking spray.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until bubbly.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in 1 cup water 10 minutes.
Add all other ingredients in same pot with broccoli and water.
Bring to a boil. Pour in long casserole dish, 11 3/4 x 7 1/2 inch.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: cheesy eggs
directions: Break eggs into microwave-safe cereal bowl.
Beat with fork until blended.
Mix in milk, salt and pepper.
Cut cheese into small pieces and add to egg mixture.
Microwave on High, uncovered, 2 to 2 1/2 minutes, or until eggs are just about set. Stir one time.
For 2 to 3 servings, double all ingredients. Increase cooking time to 3 1/2 to 4 1/2 minutes; stir 2 times.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Butter sides and bottom of large Dutch oven.
Leave excess butter in pan.
Stir sugar and evaporated milk.
Bring to boil until soft ball stage or 234° and stir constantly.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Beat with wooden spoon until blended.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9-inch dish.
Makes approximately 2 pounds.
Mold into any shapes desired!

title: "plains" cheese ring
directions: Mix and press into ring mold.
Serve with strawberry preserves in center.

title: hot cross buns
directions: Add shortening, sugar and salt to milk.
When lukewarm, add yeast cake dissolved in water, spices, well beaten eggs and sufficient flour to make a stiff dough.
Mix well.
Add raisins. Cover and let rise overnight.
In morning, divide into pieces and form into neat buns.
Place on greased pan an inch apart; let rise and brush over with milk or beaten egg.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Combine 1 cup powdered sugar, 1/4 teaspoon vanilla and enough milk to make drizzling consistency (about 1 1/2 tablespoons).
Drizzle over top of buns.

title: crab dip in pepper shell
directions: Cut thin slice from stem end of green pepper.
Remove seeds and membranes.
Mix sour cream, crabmeat, garlic salt and lemon peel.
Pour into green pepper shell.
Use celery, carrots and cucumber as dippers.

title: tuna bumsteads
directions: Fix your favorite tuna salad or simply mix 1 can of tuna with Miracle Whip salad dressing.
Pop one piece of bread into toaster. Spread the tuna on top.
Place a slice of cheese on the top and stick it on a cookie sheet.
Turn the oven on broil and put it under the broiler for a couple of minutes until the cheese melts.

title: shortcake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together lightly. Pour thick batter into 8 x 10, or 9 x 9, inch pan. Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar on top. Bake until brown in 375° oven for 30 minutes. Serve warm with berries and whipped cream.

title: stroganoff noodles
directions: Brown in large frypan at 350° the hamburger, salt and pepper. Sprinkle dry onion soup and ginger over meat.
Now add 3 to 4 cups medium noodles.
Add, being sure all noodles are wet the mushrooms and water.
Cook at 225° for 20 to 25 minutes, stirring once or twice.
Add flour and sour cream to frypan; mix and cook 3 minutes.
Then serve!

title: sour cream dressing for cole slaw(diet recipe)
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill.

title: tropical fruit punch
directions: In punch bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk and juice concentrates; mix well.
Gradually add club soda; stir.
Garnish with orange slices.
Serve over ice.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package. Add other ingredients (1/2 jar Cheez Whiz) and bake until top is brown (about 30 minutes). Spread rest of Cheez Whiz on top.
Add onion rings. Bake about 5 minutes longer in a 350° oven.

title: hamburger chowder
directions: In large Dutch oven, brown meat and drain.
Add all other ingredients except corn and peas.
Simmer 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add peas and corn and heat to serving temperature.

title: minestrone soup
directions: In 5-quart Dutch oven or saucepot over high heat, cook onion, celery, beef and cabbage, stirring carefully so meat stays chunky. Cook until all juices evaporate and rest are lightly browned.
Add tomatoes, beans and corn.
(Use their liquids, do not drain juices off.)
Add macaroni, bouillon and 2 1/2 cups water.
Heat to boiling to break up tomatoes.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer at least 20 to 25 minutes until macaroni is cooked and vegetables are tender.
If it is too thick, add more tomato juice.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Brown ground beef in large skillet; drain excess fat.
Add to other ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook onion in hot oil until golden.
Add meat and garlic; brown lightly.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer, uncovered, 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until thick.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve on hot cooked spaghetti.
Pass bowl of grated Parmesan cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Cook in microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir.
Cook another 4 minutes; add 1 teaspoon butter and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Cook on High for 1 1/2 more minutes; take out and add 1 teaspoon baking soda.
Pour on buttered powdered sugared tray (pour quickly, candy hardens fast).

title: scones
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Rub in butter.
Wash raisins (currants) and dry; mix in raisins (currants).
Knead for a few minutes.
Roll to 1/2 inch.
Cut into squares/circles.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: In a casserole dish spread the refried beans.
Spread the ground meat over the beans.
Mix the taco seasoning with the sour cream and spread on top of meat.
Mix the avocados with the mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Spread on next.
Cover with shredded cheese and top with chopped lettuce, tomatoes and onions.
(Can do day before and cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate.)

title: jerry goyer's roast beef
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Select meat and add salt and pepper. Place on roasting pan with rack.
Bake 6 minutes per pound.
After roasting time is completed, do not open oven door for 2 hours. Slice and serve.
Garnish with miniature beets filled with horseradish.

title: diabetic melon lime cooler
directions: Place melon cubes in a single layer on a baking sheet.
Cover and freeze 30 minutes or until firm.
Position knife blade in food processor bowl; add frozen melon, sherbet and lime juice.
Process until smooth.
Pour into glasses.
Garnish with strawberries if desired.

title: pepperoni bites
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Cut cheese slices into 1-inch squares. Place one cheese square on each cracker.
Top cheese with a pepperoni slice.
Place crackers on baking sheet.
Bake 4 to 5 minutes or until cheese melts. Serve immediately.
Makes 48 appetizers.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook cauliflower 10 minutes.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, sour cream, curry powder and cheese.
Place cauliflower in dish.
Pour other ingredients over it.
Dot with butter and bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: graham cracker toffee bars
directions: Cover cookie sheet with foil.
Lay graham crackers on cookie sheet; sprinkle nuts on top. Boil sugar and butter for 2 1/2 minutes. Pour over graham crackers and nuts. Bake in 325° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chocolate cake or black joe cake
directions: Mix well all the ingredients.
Add 1 cup hot coffee and mix. Pour
into	greased
and
floured
x 9-inch pan or 2 layers. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pile on
directions: Pile ingredients on top of each other in order given.
Very good.
Great for least effort in serving a big crowd.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs, sugar and Wesson oil until smooth; set aside.
Combine dry ingredients and add to egg mixture 1/3 at a time.
Add pumpkin last.
Pour into 13x9 inch pan.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: chow mein hot dish(grandkids favorite)
directions: In 2-quart casserole, brown beef, onions and celery.
Drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients (except noodles and cashews). Cover and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove cover and bake 30 minutes more.
Top with noodles and cashews.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: delicious sweet, hot, garlic pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and cut into long lengths, approximately 3 inch long. Cut tomatoes and onions in wedges. Slice peppers in half. For hotter taste, leave seeds, otherwise remove seeds. Peel garlic and leave whole. Pack jars with cucumber spears on outer edges of jar with tomato, garlic and pepper in the center. Add 1 tsp. of salt per jar. Bring vinegar, water and sugar to a boil and pour over packed jars. Seal with lids. Place in open kettle; cover jars with hot water and boil for 10 minutes. Remove and let cool.

title: salsa dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese on a plate. Top with salsa. Sprinkle shredded Cheddar cheese over top of salsa. Serve with tortilla or corn chips. Great on football game days.

title: steak mozzarella
directions: Combine flour and Cheddar cheese.
Dip steak in egg and coat with flour mixture.
Press into steak.
Brown in oil.
Transfer to a shallow baking dish.

title: sand cups
directions: Will also need miniature toy umbrellas.

title: chicken and fruit salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a large bowl; set aside while preparing rest of ingredients, then add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: chocolate peanut torte
directions: Combine wafer crumbs, butter and 2/3 c. peanuts.
Press into an ungreased 13 X 9 X 2 baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 8-10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar and peanut butter until smooth.
Fold in 2 c. whipped topping.
Spread over crust.
In a mixing bowl, beat milk and pudding mixes on low for 2 minutes.
Carefully spread over cream cheese layer.
Cover and refrigerate for 4-6 hours.
Just before serving carefully spread remaining topping over the pudding layer.
Sprinkle with grated chocolate and the remaining peanuts. Yield 16-20 servings.

title: chocolate cookies(emily's favorite!)
directions: Melt together butter and chocolate squares.
Add immediately 1 cup sugar and 2 eggs, one at a time.
Add 1 cup flour, 1 teaspoon baking powder and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Let stand in refrigerator for 3 hours or overnight.
Roll in a ball the size of a walnut and roll in confectioners sugar.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix and spread on pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Let cool.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook and stir ground beef until brown (drain).
Stir in water, macaroni, sauce mix, chili powder, garlic and cayenne pepper. Heat to boiling; stir constantly.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Uncover and cook 5 minutes.

title: ham and cheese chowder
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Place water and salt in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Add potatoes and reduce heat.
Cook 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Drain potatoes, reserving 1 cup of liquid.

title: onion dressing
directions: Use electric mixer to combine onion, garlic, mustard, lemon peel, salt, oregano, pepper and lemon juice.
Blend until smooth. Slowly add oil until all oil is blended into dressing.
Use with Vegetable Medley Salad.

title: heath bar squares
directions: Blend oleo, brown sugar, white sugar and flour to make crumb mixture.
Set aside 3/4 cup.
Add buttermilk, vanilla, baking soda and egg.

title: rhubarb whipped cream pie
directions: Soften gelatin in water.
Heat rhubarb and sugar to boiling; add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Cool.
When mixture begins to thicken; fold in whipped cream.
Pour into pie shell and chill for 1 hour.

title: simple salisbury steak
directions: Mix 1/4 cup gravy, beef, bread crumbs, onion and egg thoroughly.
Shape firmly into 4 patties.
In skillet over medium-high heat, heat 1 tablespoon oil.
Brown patties.
Pour off fat.
Add remaining gravy.
Heat to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes or until done.

title: molasses stack cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Stir in molasses.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add mixture of flour, soda and salt to cream mixture, alternating dry ingredients and milk.
Beat after each addition.
Grease and flour 3 (8-inch) baking pans.
Pour 1 1/3 cups of batter into each.
Refrigerate remaining batter.
Bake at 375° about 15 minutes or until done. Cool 5 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Repeat process with remaining batter.
Spread applesauce between layers.
Sprinkle top layer with powdered sugar.

title: lazy man's cake
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 35 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan. It makes a nice moist cake. Put on your favorite frosting.

title: cherry cookies
directions: Stir together flour, salt and baking powder; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Add flour mixture.
Thoroughly combine.
Stir in nuts, dates and 1/3 cup of cherries.
Portion dough using level measuring tablespoonful.
Roll in crushed corn flakes cereal.
Place about 2 inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Top each cookie with a cherry quarter.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove immediately and cool on wire racks. Makes 5 dozen.
Two cookies contain 170 calories.

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat egg yolks well.
Add condensed milk.
Mix on low.
Add juice and cream of tartar.
Mix well.
Pour into crust and bake until set 10 to 15 minutes.
Freeze for at least 3 hours before topping with meringue.
This pie will keep for several days.

title: fast and easy cheese cake
directions: Let cream cheese soften to room temperature (if you are in a rush, soften in microwave).
Mix cream cheese with Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice until smooth.
Pour into pie crust and chill for 1 to 2 hours.
Add fruit to top and serve.
(Fresh fruit is a very good topping.)

title: reese's pieces
directions: Mix and roll into balls.
Put in freezer until easy to work with.
Melt chocolate and almond bark together.
Dip in and set until ready to eat.
Makes approximately 12 dozen marble size candies.

title: sweet and sour turkey
directions: Brown turkey under broiler in a pan until skin is crisp. Sprinkle with garlic powder.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over turkey.
Cover pan; bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, basting occasionally.

title: easy, easy casserole
directions: Put soups and water in casserole.
Add rice; stir.
Place chicken breasts on top.
Sprinkle dry onion soup mix over casserole.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: just fudge
directions: Put the first 6 items in saucepan over low heat and stir frequently until all is melted with a candy thermometer in all the while. Put a lid on with it tilted against the thermometer.
Turn heat to medium heat. Stir no more. When the candy boils, carefully remove lid and continue cooking until thermometer registers 232°. Carefully remove from heat and add vanilla.
When candy has cooled to 120°, remove thermometer and beat candy until it loses the satiny sheen. Quickly pour or spread on buttered platter.
Cut in squares and store in airtight container so it will not dry out.

title: zucchini italian style
directions: Cook onion slowly in margarine until golden.
Add zucchini and continue cooking for 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes and juice.
Cook until zucchini is done and liquid thickens.
Add cheese on top, pressing slightly into hot juice.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 5 to 8 minutes, until cheese is melted.

title: chicken florentine with rice
directions: Cook and stir chicken and onion in hot margarine in large skillet until lightly browned, about 5 minutes.
Stir cornstarch into broth.
Add to chicken with spinach, carrots, oregano and nutmeg.
Bring to a full boil.
Stir in rice and simmer 5 minutes. Cover; remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in cheese.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Blend together first 7 ingredients.
Add eggs to mixture one at a time.
Pour 1/2 mixture into a greased Bundt pan (or tube pan).

title: taco salad
directions: Mix well, except Doritos.
Last minute, crush chips and mix in salad.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, oil, squash and vanilla.
Mix well and set aside.
In a separate bowl, combine flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon; sift together.
Add dry ingredients to creamed ingredients.
Blend well.
Divide batter into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat sugar, cocoa and eggs until foaming.
Heat milk and canned milk until lukewarm.
Meanwhile, dissolve junkets tablets in a tablespoon of warm water and set aside.
Stir the egg mixture into the milk and then pour into a 1-gallon freezer.
Then add your junkets and a little vanilla.
Stir lightly.
Let stand until mixture jells.
This will take about 15 to 20 minutes.
Start freezer.
Use ice and rock salt.
(If it does not start to freeze, you are not using enough salt.)

title: chopped meat soup
directions: Brown beef in Dutch oven. Add onion and garlic.
Saute 5 minutes.
Pour off fat.
Add everything but macaroni. Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Add pasta.
Cover and cook 15 minutes more. Serve with grated cheese and Italian bread.

title: tamale dip
directions: Cube cheese.
Combine chili and cheese (cubes) in a skillet and heat until cheese melts.
Chop up tamales and add to mixture. Heat.
Put in chafing dish, top with cheese, olives and onions. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 9-inch pie plate.
Cook ground beef and onion until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in salt.
Spread in pie plate; sprinkle with cheese.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheeses. Add the remaining ingredients. Mix all together with cheeses. Can roll ball in crushed pecans if you like.

title: homemade chili
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic until meat is not pink.
Add just enough water to cover meat.
Add salt.
Cook for 2 hours.
Then add Chili Quick and cook 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla.
Blend flour and buttermilk with sugar mixture.
Add the rest of ingredients.

title: linda's lasagna
directions: Cook noodles in salted water about 15 minutes.
Drain.
Heat oil in skillet; cook garlic and onion until soft.
Add beef and seasonings and cook until crumbly.
Add tomato paste and water. Simmer 5 minutes.
Set aside.
In a baking dish 9x13x2 inches, put a thin layer of meat sauce, half the noodles, all of the Ricotta cheese, and half of the Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat with half of the remaining meat sauce, the rest of the noodles, remainder of sauce, and Mozzarella.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: layered beef casserole
directions: Grease a 4-quart casserole.
Fill with layers of potatoes, corn, peas and beef.
Sprinkle beef layer with beef broth, basil and oregano.
Add layers of green beans, onions and tomatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: toll house oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift flour, salt
and
soda.
Cream fat and sugars; add eggs, one at a
time
and
beat
after each addition.
Add hot water, then dry ingredients.
Add chocolate chips and oatmeal. Mix thoroughly, add vanilla. Bake 8 minutes in 375° oven.

title: lemonade nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and lemon peel.
Beat well.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture and add alternately with milk, beating until smooth, after each addition. Stir in pecans.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until done.
Let cool in pan 10 minutes.
Combine lemon juice and 4 tablespoons of sugar, spoon over top of slightly warm bread.
Remove from pan; cool, wrap and store overnight before cutting.

title: charlotte russe
directions: Combine all ingredients in top of a double boiler and cook over boiling water, stirring constantly, until mixture coats a spoon.
Cool.
When it begins to set, add 1/2 pint whipping cream, which has been whipped with 1 teaspoon almond flavoring.
Mix well and refrigerate.
Allow mixture to congeal.

title: b.b.q.  chicken breast
directions: Arrange boneless, skinless chicken breasts in bottom of baking dish.
Sprinkle a fair amount of salt, pepper, garlic powder and brown sugar onto chicken breasts.
Pour BBQ sauce over seasoned chicken.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Bake at 375° for 30-40 minutes. Serve over steamed rice.

title: seafood chowder
directions: Cook onions in the butter until tender.
Add water until it boils.
Add seafood.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes, then take seafood out and put in a bowl.
Add potatoes, salt and pepper.
Simmer 4 to 6 minutes until potatoes are tender.
Add milk and half and half and bring to a boil.
Take off heat.
Stir in cheese.
Let stand 2 minutes.
Put seafood back in.
Stir and serve.
Serves 10 (1 cup) servings.

title: vegetable dip or spread
directions: Blend all cheeses, milk, dill weed and pepper until smooth. Put in bowl and add sunflower seeds and carrots.
Cover and chill. Serve with vegetable sticks, crackers or chips.

title: candied pecans
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, bake pecans at 250° for 5 minutes. In large saucepan melt butter; stir in corn syrup and 1/4 cup sugar, and a dash of cinnamon. Bring to boil, let boil for 3 minutes. Pour syrup over pecans. Bake at 250° for 1 hour. Stir 4 times. When done sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.

title: easy cheesy french bread
directions: Slice bread in half the long way.
Mix mayonnaise and cheese together.
Spread on each half of bread.
Sprinkle green onion and parsley on top.
Broil until hot and bubbly.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add flour mixture
and milk alternately to egg mixture.
Beat well.
Stir in flavoring and coconut.
Place in tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix and chill before serving.

title: cottage cheese bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Combine butter, sugar, salt, soda, egg and cottage cheese with 1 1/4 cups flour; blend well.
Add remaining flour; mix thoroughly.
Allow to rise in warm place for 1 hour.
Stir down and place in greased 8-inch round casserole.
Allow to rise for 1 hour longer.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Brush with melted butter; sprinkle with salt.

title: awesome meat loaf!
directions: Preheat oven to 400° to 425°.
Mix all meat loaf ingredients together.
Place in a large, nonstick meat loaf pan.
Place meat loaf pan onto cookie sheet (to catch drippings).
Bake 1 1/2 hours. After 1 hour, drain drippings from meat loaf very carefully.
When done, cool 5 to 10 minutes before cutting.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: flaming dessert fruit salad
directions: Mix all fruit in a large centerpiece bowl.
On a separate saucer, saturate sugar cubes with extract and light with match. Scrape cubes into center of fruit salad and let burn until cubes have melted onto fruit.
Serve alone or as a topping for ice cream.

title: burger 'n beans
directions: Brown hamburger and chopped onions.
Mix with
remaining ingredients.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours or simmer slowly until bubbly.

title: five flavors pound cake
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add flour, alternating with milk.
Add 5 flavors.
Bake in a well-greased Bundt pan for 1 1/4 hours at 325°.
During the last 30 minutes, check to see if the top of the cake needs to be protected from overbrowning.
If so, make a tent of aluminum foil to cover the surface of the cake and continue baking.

title: chow-chow
directions: Mix celery seed, vinegar, salt and sugar. Bring to a boil. Add chopped vegetables and return to a boil.
Put in jars and seal.

title: mother's muffins
directions: Beat together milk and mayonnaise.
Put flour in mixing bowl; make a well in it and pour in wet ingredients.
With fork, blend the wet and dry ingredients together.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full and bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: easy hamburger casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on package or box. Drain and rinse well with cold water.
Set aside.

title: candy apples
directions: In a heavy, deep 3-quart saucepan over medium heat, add sugar, corn syrup, candies, water and food coloring.
Bring to a boil. Cook without stirring about 20 minutes or 290°.
Meanwhile, insert skewers into apples part way through each of them.
Grease a cookie sheet.
When syrup is ready, remove pan from heat and swirl apples in hot syrup to coat completely.
Work fast so syrup doesn't harden on you.
Place them on cookie sheets to cool.
If syrup does harden before you're finished, just place it back on the stove for a few minutes on a low flame.
Cool apples for 1 hour before serving.

title: eileen's fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add eggs (1 at a time).
Add pineapple juice and flavorings.
Mix well.
Add half flour ingredients.
Mix other half flour with chopped fruits and nuts. Mix all together.
Pour into greased and foiled tube pan (grease pan then line with foil) and grease again.
Bake at 275° for 3-4 hours.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Broccoli, carrots, cauliflower, green or red peppers or radishes are good vegetables to use.

title: strawberry-lemon pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine granulated sugar and cornstarch.
Add water, egg yolk and butter.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly; cook 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat.
Stir in lemon juice.
Pour into baked crust.
Top with sliced berries.
In small mixer bowl, beat together cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Fold in the 1/3 cup coconut.
In another bowl, beat whipping cream to soft peaks; fold into cream cheese mixture until combined.
Spread on top of the berries.
Sprinkle with the toasted coconut.
Chill 4 hours or overnight.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Mix together.
Brown pork chops.
Place in roaster and cover with sauce.
Double for more than 5 persons.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 2 hours.
Also good with chicken.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together eggs, oil and sugar.
Add zucchini, vanilla and pineapple.
In another bowl, sift flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and baking powder.
Add to first mixture, then add chopped nuts.
Bake in two loaf pans at 325° for 30 to 60 minutes.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Split Twinkies lengthwise.
Place, cream side up, in a single layer in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Cover with pineapple with juice. Slice bananas.
Spread whipped topping. Place in refrigerator until chilled.
Serve.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Empty gravy and mushroom soup into large pot with 3 cans of water.
Heat.
Mix beef, crumbs, onion, egg, parsley, salt, pepper, ginger and nutmeg; mix well.
Form into meatballs.
Roll into flour.

title: beef in wine
directions: Mix all.
Put in large casserole.
Cook 3 hours, covered, in a 300° oven.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Brown onions.
Add bell pepper and mushrooms, season with Worcestershire and Tabasco.
Simmer for a couple of minutes.
Then add stewed tomatoes and tomato sauce and simmer 20 minutes.
Add peeled shrimp and simmer 10 to 15 minutes more.
Serve over yellow rice.
Feeds 4 to 6 people.

title: nellie bealmer's prize rolls
directions: Combine shortening, sugar and salt.
Add beaten eggs and blend.
Dissolve yeast in 3 teaspoons warm water.
Add 1 cup warm water and 2 cups flour; mix well.
Add rest of flour; mix.
Knead until smooth.
Put dough back into clean bowl; cover and let rise 3 hours.
Roll out dough; spread with soft butter.
Sprinkle cinnamon and brown sugar.
Roll up and slice into cinnamon rolls.

title: seafood gruyere(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Make a cream sauce in the top of a double boiler using butter, flour and milk.
Cut cheese into small pieces.
Add to sauce. Cook and stir until cheese melts.
Add garlic powder, salt, mustard, tomato paste and 2 teaspoons lemon juice.
Poach scallops for about 10 minutes in water to which you have added 1 teaspoon lemon juice.
Add 1/2 cup of the broth to cream sauce.
Saute mushrooms in a small amount of butter and add to sauce.
Drain scallops.
Add to sauce.
Add shrimp to sauce.
Add imitation crab meat to sauce.
Heat 10 to 15 minutes.

title: candied pecan halves
directions: Bring sugar and sour cream to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and as many nuts as sugar and cream will cover.
When coating begins to set, spread on cookie sheet to cool.

title: triple decker sandwich
directions: Toast bread and butter 1 side of each slice.
Place lettuce leaf, 2 slices turkey, 1 slice cheese, 1 slice tomato and 1 teaspoon mayonnaise on 1st slice of toast.
Top with another slice of toast and layer remaining ingredients.
Top with 3rd slice of toast.
Cut in half diagonally.

title: dip cookies
directions: Melt butter.
Mix all ingredients except wax and chips together.
Mix with hands and make into cookies.
Melt wax and chips over low heat in double boiler.
Dip cookies and place on wax paper until dry.

title: rice delite
directions: Boil rice until tender.
Cool.
Mix rice, pudding and Cool Whip together.
Divide into dessert dishes (optional).
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar or top with crushed walnuts and top with cherry.
Enjoy.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Mix together and pour in two unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: mema and papa's famous quail
directions: Soak quail in salt water overnight.
Dip quail in flour.
Fry in oil.
Serve with biscuits and quail gravy.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Mix together flour, 2 cups sugar, eggs, pineapple, baking soda, 1 tsp. vanilla and the pinch of salt.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: cold spaghetti medley
directions: Mix all ingredients together; store in refrigerator in covered container for 2 days.
Serve.

title: angel delight
directions: Dissolve gelatine in cold water; add boiling water, sugar, crushed pineapple and lemon juice.
Chill until partly gelled. Whip 2 envelopes of Dream Whip (make sure your bowl, beaters and milk are very cold).
Add to gelatine mixture.
Flake angel food cake into very small pieces.
Put 1/2 of flaked cake into a 9 x 13-inch pan; place 1/2 of gelatine mixture over cake.
Add last 1/2 of cake pieces and remaining gelatine mixture.
Prepare last envelope of Dream Whip.
Spread on top.
Cover with coconut; chill overnight.
"Nuts and cherries can be added on top if desired."

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli until tender;
drain.
Add soup with milk and cheese.
Mix together the Bisquick and butter.
Put on top of broccoli mixture.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: crawfish stuffed bell peppers(serves 8)
directions: Cook wild rice in four cups of salted water for about 45 minutes until tender.
Cook brown rice in 2 3/4 cups salted water until tender.
Saute onion, celery, parsley and mushrooms in small amount of oil until onions are translucent.
Add crawfish, two cups of water and roux.
Simmer for about 25 minutes to make a thick gravy, while stirring frequently and seasoning to taste. Add green onions and cooked rice.
Stir well.
Cut core out of bell peppers, then stuff center with crawfish mixture.
Place in dish with small amount of water in the bottom; cover and bake in oven at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef in skillet; drain.
In large pot or crock-pot stir in chili mix, ground beef, water, tomatoes, and beans, onion. Bring to a boil, stir in chili powder, salt, pepper, and simmer for 45 minutes.
Makes 15 to 20 servings depending on size of bowl.

title: veal casserole
directions: Cut one squash in half. Scoop out seeds and strings.
Place in baking dish, cut side down.
Add a little water and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until tender. Fill cavity with dabs of butter, brown sugar and pecans.
Salt and pepper to taste. Serve hot.

title: moist coconut cake
directions: Cook cake according to package and let cool, then take a spoon and punch holes in the cake and pour the Coco Lopez over the cake. Spread Cool Whip over the cake and sprinkle coconut over the top.

title: tasty rice
directions: Heat oil in frying pan.
Add spaghetti and rice.
Cook until spaghetti is browned (only takes a minute).
Add garlic, onions, broth, water (with bouillon cubes dissolved in it), salt and pepper to taste.
Cook over low heat about 30 minutes until liquid is gone.
Garnish with parsley.

title: corn casserole
directions: Soften cream cheese with corn liquid as needed.
Mix all together and put in baking dish.
Top with buttered bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: ricotta puffs
directions: Beat cheese with egg until thoroughly blended.	Add onion and salt.
Mix well.
Toast 20 to 24, 1 3/4 inch rounds of whole-grain bread on one side.	Heap cheese mixture on the untoasted side of the bread.	Broil for about one minute or until brown and puffy. Sprinkle with paprika.
Serve hot.	Yield: at least 20.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Cook beef and onion.
Drain.
Stir in soup, vegetables and milk. In a separate bowl, mix water and baking mix.
Spread into baking pan.
Pour beef mix over batter and sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Beat eggs and milk together, then add to dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Beat vigorously, add sour cream and baking soda.
Beat well.
Stir in cherries.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until set.

title: chocolate nut pudding
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, sugar, salt and cocoa.
Add milk, melted shortening and vanilla.
Mix only until smooth.
Add nutmeats.
Mix lightly and turn into greased pudding pans to a depth of 1/2-inch.

title: smothered okra and tomatoes
directions: In heavy, large skillet, saute onion in oil for 5 minutes. Add okra and cook until okra ceases to rope (about 15 minutes). Add tomatoes and continue to cook, covered, about 10 minutes.
Add shrimp and seasoning and continue to cook, covered, for about 15 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: doubled-up oreo ice cream
directions: Scald milk until bubbles form around edge.
Remove from heat. Add sugar and salt.
Stir until dissolved.
Stir in half and half, vanilla and whipping cream.
Cover and refrigerate for 30 minutes. Stir in crushed to chilled mixture.
Freeze.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: bread pudding for two
directions: Place bread in a greased 1-quart baking dish. In a bowl, whisk egg and milk. Stir in the brown sugar, butter, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt. Pour over bread. Sprinkle with raisins. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean. Serve warm with ice cream. Yields 2 servings.

title: chicken superb
directions: Around each chicken breast, wrap 2 slices dried beef and 1 slice bacon.
Put in baking dish.
Mix sour cream and cream of mushroom soup together; spoon on top of each breast until all is used.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours.
Serve on rice.

title: pilgrim's bread
directions: Thoroughly combine cornmeal, brown sugar and salt.
Stir gradually into boiling water; stir in oil.
Cool until lukewarm (about 1/2 hour).
Soften yeast in the warm water.
Stir into cornmeal mixture.
Add whole wheat and rye flours; mix well.
By hand, stir in enough white flour to make a moderately stiff dough. Put on a lightly floured board; knead 5 to 10 minutes until smooth and elastic.
Shape into a ball.
Place into a lightly greased bowl, turning once to grease surface.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled (1 hour).
Punch down.
Turn out on lightly floured surface.
Divide in half.
Cover.
Let rest 10 minutes.
Shape into 2 loaves and put into 2 greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans; cover and let rise in warm place until almost doubled (1/2 hour).
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes.
If bread browns too fast, loosely cover with foil after 25 minutes.
Remove from pans; cool.

title: corn casserole
directions: Let cheese and margarine stand until room temperature.
Mix well.
Add the green chilies and mix well.
Then add the corn and mix well.
Place in an ovenproof dish and cook at 350° until bubbly.

title: spice layer cake(indonesian specuke)
directions: Whip butter and margarine until smooth.
Add yolks and whip. Add powdered sugar and whip.
Whip whites until stiff in another bowl.
Add flour to mix and fold in whites just until mixed.
Put more than half in another bowl to remain white.
Add spices to smaller half.
Grease and flour 2 round pans.
Spread 2 tablespoons of brown batter and bake 5 to 10 minutes at 250°.
Immediately spread 1 to 2 tablespoons of white batter and broil with door open until light brown.
Continue, alternating colors, broiling and spreading immediately.
Do one pan at a time if you can't alternate the two.
Cool on rack.
Slice off edges.
Store in foil.
Cut in wedges.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Wash zucchini.
Cut lengthways into quarters.
Cook in microwave about 5 minutes.
(Cover with plastic wrap.)
Cut zucchini into bite size cubes and add to onion.
Stir together cheese, Accent, salt and pepper.
Add to vegetables and stir in beaten eggs.
Melt butter and add to bread crumbs; put on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until a knife, when inserted in the center, comes out clean.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: rice and mushroom casserole
directions: In a 1-quart casserole dish, layer the ingredients.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: six-week bran muffins
directions: Beat
eggs;
add
sugar and oil.
Mix flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add to egg mixture with buttermilk.
Add Raisin Bran and
mix
well.
Store in refrigerator in large bowl with cover. Bake
as
needed in cupcake cups in 375° oven 18 to 20 minutes. Batter keeps 6 weeks.

title: mother's pound cake
directions: Mix sugar, Crisco and eggs until blended.
Sift dry ingredients together except soda.
Add soda to buttermilk.
Add flavorings to egg mixture.
Add buttermilk to egg mixture, then add dry ingredients.
Beat well.
Pour in well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 75 minutes.

title: picnic beans
directions: Drain the cut beans, yellow beans and lima beans. Add all bean ingredients together. Brown and drain sausage and add. Add rest of ingredients. Bake at 325° for 3 hours.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash Mushrooms thoroughly.
Separate the caps from the stems. Place caps upside down in serving dish.
Finely chop remaining stems; set aside.
Mix Crabmeat, Bread Crumbs, chopped Mushroom stems, Salt, Pepper, and Lemon Juice.
Use a melon scoop or teaspoon to scoop out stuffing.
Fill each cap.
Once all caps are filled place under broiler for up to 5 minutes or until stuffing browns.
If an electric stove the broiler setting would be high.

title: potato and cheese casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix all ingredients together.
Leave enough cheese to sprinkle on top of casserole the last 5 minutes of baking.
Put in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish and bake at 350° to 400° for approximately 1 hour.

title: violet's cake
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar and soda.
Bring to a boil the margarine, syrup, water and Crisco. Mix together the buttermilk, eggs and vanilla and add.
Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° until done.
Cover cake with glaze while it is still warm.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice; set aside.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Saute chicken in margarine.
Add bouillon and carrots.
Cover and cook until carrots are tender.
Combine reserved pineapple juice, brown sugar, cornstarch, vinegar and soy sauce.
Add mixture to chicken and carrots.
Cook until thickened. Before serving, add pineapple, onion and green pepper.
Cook until heated.
Serve over rice.
Yields 6 servings.

title: deviled beets
directions: Heat
beets
in
liquid, drain well.
Add other ingredients. Bring to boiling point.
Remove from heat and let cool.

title: cheese bars
directions: Mix together egg yolk, cream cheese, vanilla and 1 cup sugar. Stretch 1 package crescent rolls to bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread mixture over dough.
Stretch 2nd package crescent rolls over mixture.
Beat egg whites until frothy.
Brush over top of dough. Combine 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix Cool Whip with already prepared pudding; set aside.
In medium saucepan, mix powdered sugar, cocoa and milk; cook until bubbly and set aside.
Melt butter and pour over the graham crackers.

Refrigerate, covered, these three mixtures overnight. Next day, layer alternately in a 13 x 9-inch pan, the graham cracker mixture on bottom, then the pudding and Cool Whip mixture, and end with a graham cracker layer.
Pour cooked cocoa mix over the top.

title: garden sausage bake
directions: Heat the oven to 350°.
Combine all the ingredients.
Place in 2-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, 50 minutes.
Makes six servings.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Whip egg whites until foamy.
Add sugar and salt gradually.
Beat until it forms a high peak, fold in chips and nuts.
Cover cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Place in oven and turn off heat. Leave in oven for 4 hours.

title: pot pasta
directions: Simmer ground beef, onions, tomatoes, sauce and garlic for 20 minutes.

Mix half of the macaroni with half of the sauce and pour into large baking pan (spread small amount of sauce in pan first). Spread half of 1 pint of sour cream over this and top with 1 package of shedded Provolone cheese and 1 package of shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Mix remaining sauce and macaroni; pour over sour cream and top with remaining sour cream.
Sprinkle remaining shredded Mozzarella cheese over this and bake for 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: dave's flank steak
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Pour over flank steak, covering both sides.
Cover steak with onion rings and marinate in a closed container overnight.
Remove onion rings and enough marinade to make it easy to grill.
Grill for 6 minutes on each side.
Slice thin, on the diagonal.

title: diabetic pie
directions: Combine egg whites, dry milk and ice water.
Beat until stiff peaks form.
Add Sugar Twin and vanilla. Beat until peaks again. Fold in pecans, cracker crumbs and baking powder.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.
Contains 120 calories per serving. Diabetic Exchange:
1 fat or 1 bread.

title: italian sausage and spaghetti
directions: Cut sausage into 3 to 4-inch long pieces, then brown in small amount of oil; cook well.
Remove sausage, then saute onion and bell pepper until onion is clear.
Place sausage, onion, pepper and mushroom in a 3 to 4-inch deep baking dish.
In a saucepan, mix the tomato sauce and paste together; heat until hot and season to taste with garlic, oregano, salt, pepper and parsley.
Pour mixture over sausage and bake at 350° until bubbling.
Remove and cover with the shredded cheese.
Return to oven until cheese begins to brown.
Served over spaghetti or your favorite pasta.

title: curried chicken and corn chowder
directions: Cook onion in butter (can use margarine) in a large pot over low heat until tender.
Add curry powder.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Stir in chicken and remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 to 10 minutes, stirring often. Yields about 7 cups.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Butter or spray baking dish with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Layer each vegetable until you fill your baking dish.
Top with bacon and 1/4 cup water.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Uncover after 1 hour and bake for 15 minutes or until you feel the bacon is crisp.

title: chow mein or chop suey(serve chow mein over chinese noodles; serve chop suey over rice.)
directions: Cook fresh vegetables with cooked meat for about 10 minutes. Add canned vegetables, reserving liquid from one can.
Add cornstarch and soy sauce to liquid, then add to vegetables and meat.
Cook only until thick.
Serve over noodles or rice while hot.
Serves 6.

title: chewy molasses cookies
directions: Mix shortening and sugar in a large bowl.
Cream well.
Add egg and molasses.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill 1 hour.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Take meat off the bone.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: Sift
the
dry	ingredients.
Add
the liquid until the mixture will drop easily from spoon.
Drop by tablespoonful in to boiling
chicken stock or any other stew or stock you would like. Cover
tightly
and let boil 15 minutes.
Do not remove cover during that time.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend softened cream cheese with cottage cheese.
Add sour cream.
Blend in the rest of the ingredients.
Chill 1 hour.

title: firecracker enchilada casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in a large skillet until meat is brown and onion is tender; discard pan drippings.
Add chili powder, cumin and salt; stir well. Cook meat mixture over low heat 10 minutes.
Spoon meat mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Layer beans, tortillas and cheese over meat mixture.
Pour tomato liquid over cheese; chop tomatoes and spread tomatoes and chiles over cheese.
Spread soup over all.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: chili(double recipe)
directions: Cook and stir hamburger, onion and garlic in 3-quart saucepan until hamburger is light brown; drain.
Stir in tomatoes with liquid, celery, chili powder, salt, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, red pepper sauce and kidney beans.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat. Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Makes 10 servings.
Also works well in crock-pot (all day) on low.

title: hot chicken salad souffle
directions: Cut bread into cubes; spread half on bottom of greased casserole.
Mix chicken, celery, onion and mayonnaise; spread over bread cubes and cover with remaining bread.
Beat eggs; add to milk and pour over chicken.
(Important:
Cover with waxed paper and refrigerate overnight.)
Next day, spread chicken soup over all and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: ice cream torte
directions: Take ice cream out of freezer and let set out while toasting first 3 ingredients, so it will be very soft.
Melt stick of butter in large jelly roll pan and toast first 3 ingredients for 30 minutes in 300° oven.
Toss every 10 minutes until evenly browned.
Remove and add brown sugar until well combined.
Put 1/4 of mixture aside.
Press rest of mixture in bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Slice ice cream and spread in bottom of pan evenly.
Sprinkle remaining mixture over ice cream.
Freeze. Remove from freezer 10 minutes prior to serving.
Serves 16.

title: lemon bisque
directions: Chill milk.
Dissolve jello in hot water.
Chill until partly set.
Whip until light and fluffy.
Add lemon juice and sugar. Whip milk and fold into jello mixture.
Line bottom of pan with crumbs.
Pour in jello mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs and chill.

title: hot muffins
directions: Mix all together and put in muffin pan.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.
Makes 6 muffins.

title: fresh blueberry cream pie
directions: Bake pie shell; leave to cool.
Add milk (as needed), 1 teaspoon lemon juice and the powdered sugar.
Whip until creamy. Fold in Cool Whip until completely blended into mixture.
Pour mixture into baked pie shell.
Place the blueberries, 1 teaspoon lemon juice and 1 cup granulated sugar over heat.
Cook until mixture is hot throughout.
Cool.
Pour blueberry mixture over cream cheese filling already poured into pie shell.

title: coconut pie(makes its own crust.)
directions: Combine all ingredients in order and mix well.
Pour in well-greased 10-inch pie pan. Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 300° until golden brown.

title: country vegetable soup
directions: In 4-quart microproof casserole, combine all ingredients except parsley.
Cook covered on High (maximum power) 20 minutes.
Stir. Cook on 50 (simmer) 20 to 25 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes. Discard bay leaf.
Divide parsley into individual serving dishes. Ladle hot soup over parsley.
Serve immediately with crackers or hard rolls.

title: taco dip - salad
directions: Mix the cream cheese and sour cream together.
Spread in bottom of two cake pans.
Cover with shredded lettuce, chopped onion, green pepper, tomato and grated Colby cheese.
Serve with taco chips or crackers.

title: one bowl homemade brownies
directions: Microwave chocolate and margarine in large microwavable bowl on high speed 2 minutes or until margarine is melted.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Stir in sugar until well blended, then add the eggs and vanilla until mixed.
Mix in flour until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Cut in squares. Yields 24 brownies.

title: sweet and sour meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, onion, crackers, salt, pepper, 1/2 cup tomato sauce and egg.
Form a round loaf.
Mix remaining tomato sauce, vinegar, mustard and brown sugar; pour over meat loaf.
Pour 1/2 cup water around edge of meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pepper rings
directions: Prepare and wash peppers.
Cut in rings.
Put in pan, cover with water and bring to boil.
Boil at least 2 minutes.
Take out and place pepper rings in ice water.
Let cool and pat on towels to drain.
Place in jars.
Bring the sugar and vinegar (per pint) to a boil and pour over peppers and seal at once.

title: general's fortune cookies(china)
directions: Combine egg whites, sugar, and salt. Beat in rest of ingredients one at a time. Blend well and chill for 20 minutes. Preheat oven to 350. Do just 2-3 cookies at a time. Drop slightly rounded teaspoon full of thick batter for each cookie on a greased cookie sheet. Spread the dough very thin using the back of the spoon, make rounds about 3 inches in diameter. Bake for 5 minutes or until edges turn light brown. Place on wire rack. Working quickly place a fortune in each cookie, fold opposite sides together, crease crosswise at the center of the straight edge to form a flattened side, then bend backward to form the traditional shape. Cool in muffin tins to hold shape. Yields 4 dozen.

title: teriyaki steak
directions: Cut steak into 1/8-inch thick slices.
Combine remaining ingredients in small bowl.
Place meat in slow-cooking pot.
Pour sauce over meat.
Cover pot.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.
Serve with rice.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: *Suggest 6 green onions, broccoli florets, red and green pepper.

title: ginger-spiced chicken
directions: Saute chicken and garlic in oil until lightly browned, about 4 minutes.
Stir in peppers and mushrooms.
Cook and stir until crisp-tender, 2 to 3 minutes.
Combine water, cornstarch and soy sauce in small bowl, stirring until smooth.
Stir into chicken mixture.
Add ginger and bouillon cube.
Cook over medium heat until mixture thickens and comes to a boil.
Cook 1 minute.
Spoon over rice and sprinkle with nuts.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice in water for 20 minutes.
Add milk and simmer for 20 more minutes.
Add sugar and salt.
Continue simmering until creamy.
Do not give up, it may take a while.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Sprinkle cinnamon over top and serve either warm or at room temperature.
Very delicious!

title: stormy day bean soup
directions: Rinse beans.
Heat beans and water to boiling; boil gently 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; cover and let stand 1 hour or soak overnight.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 2 or 3 hours.
(Add water, if necessary.) Remove ham bone.
Trim meat from bone; add to soup.
Season to taste.
Makes 7 (1 cup) servings.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix dry ingredients with the shortening, cutting it in until mixture is the size of peas.
Beat the egg, water and vinegar with a fork.
Add to flour mixture; mix well.
Form into a ball.
Divide ball into four (4) pieces.
Each piece will roll to make one (8 or 9-inch) pie crust.
Unused portions may be wrapped and stored in refrigerator for a week or freezer about 1 month.

title: cupid's peanut patties
directions: Cook sugar, syrup, milk and peanuts over low heat.
Cook until soft ball stage.
Remove from heat; add oleo and vanilla.
Butter platters and drop by tablespoons on plate.

title: squash muffins
directions: Cut and wash squash.
Cook squash in water for 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain well and mash.
Measure 2 cups and combine squash, eggs and butter and stir well.
Set this aside.
Combine remaining ingredients
in a large bowl and make a well in the center.
Add squash mixture, stirring just until moistened.
Spoon into greased muffin pan 3/4 full.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: blueberry pudding
directions: Mix blueberries, lemon and cinnamon.
Place in a well buttered 8-inch square pan, 2-inches deep.
Cream sugar and butter. Add milk. Sift baking powder with flour and salt and add to butter mixture.
Spread this over berries.
Mix together the additional sugar with cornstarch and salt.
Sprinkle over batter.
Pour the cup of boiling water over the top but do not stir. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli in lightly greased casserole. Place celery on top of broccoli. Combine soup, sour cream, pimento, salt, pepper and cheese. Pour over celery and broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Mash bananas; add to sugar and butter and add eggs and vanilla in one bowl.
In another bowl, sift together flour, salt, soda and powder.
Add wet ingredients to dry and alternate with sour milk.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: rum cake
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients.
Grease and flour Bundt pan. Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Remove from oven and poke holes with fork all over!

title: creamed corn bread
directions: Melt margarine in 8-inch square baking pan.
Mix other ingredients together and pour into hot pan.
Do not stir in the margarine.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, until done.
Cool slightly; cut and serve.
This is a nice change from regular cornmeal bread.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and ice cake.

title: goulash
directions: Brown meat, onion and mushrooms.
Drain and put in a large pot.
Add all ingredients but macaroni.
Simmer for 30 minutes. Add water if needed.
Add macaroni and cook on medium heat until noodles are soft.
Top with cheese and serve.

title: caramel oatmeal chewies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine flour, brown sugar, soda, oats and salt.
Stir in margarine, mixing well. (Reserve 1 cup.)
Press remaining onto bottom of pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until light brown.
Cool 10 minutes.
Top with nuts and chocolate pieces.
Mix caramel topping with 1/4 cup flour until smooth.
Drizzle over chocolate pieces.
Sprinkle with reserved oat mixture.
Bake an additional 18 to 22 minutes.
Cool.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix all cake ingredients.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° in three 9-inch greased cake pans.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In large bowl, mix pudding and milk.
Add condensed milk. Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer vanilla wafers and bananas.
Chill.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Combine cake mix, oranges, 1 box of pudding, 1 cup pineapple and 4 eggs.
Do not drain any juices.
Beat for 4 minutes.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: baked hamburgers(main dish)
directions: Mix ground chuck, eggs, bread, milk and onion into little patties about 2 inches thick.
Fry lightly in pan until slightly brown.
Transfer to medium casserole dish.
Mix celery salt, salt and pepper and dilute soup with a half can of water.
Mix together and add to casserole, covering the ground chuck.
Bake in oven for about 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Makes 10 to 15 burgers, depending on size.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix together pudding and milk.
Mix together cream cheese and margarine, then mix all of these with carton of Cool Whip.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix together all ingredients except chicken.
Place chicken in single layer, skin side up, in large shallow baking pan; pour mixture on chicken.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until fork can be inserted with ease, basting occasionally with the pan drippings.
Serve hot with plain rice.

title: cedar creek shrimp creole
directions: Cook bacon until brown and remove.
Saute vegetables and add cooked bacon.
Boil and peel the shrimp in the meantime and add all other ingredients.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours and serve over fluffy rice.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix 1 cup sugar, flour, cocoa and salt.
Add 1 cup milk and beaten egg yolks.
Add remaining milk.
Cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Pour into pie shell.
Beat egg whites at room temperature until stiff, adding 1/4 cup sugar and cream of tartar.
Spread meringue over pie.
Bake at 375° until meringue is browned.

title: baked apples
directions: Mix sugar, raisins and cinnamon.
Stuff apples with sugar mixture and dot them with butter.
Pour water into cooker.
Add apples.
Cook on low for 7 to 8 hours.

title: pioneer peach cobbler
directions: Line the sides and bottom of a deep baking dish with Pioneer pie crust, reserving some dough to put on top of pie.
Spoon peaches over bottom crust and sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and dot with 3 teaspoons oleo.
Cut reserved dough into strips and lay on top of pie.
Dot with 3 teaspoons oleo and sprinkle with 1 teaspoon sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mother's delight sunday special(hot dish)
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken; set aside.
Cut chicken in pieces and arrange in casserole dish.
Pour soup and rice mixture over chicken.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: la. pecan ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and add sugars and cornstarch.
Add scalded milk and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture coats the spoon heavily. Allow to cool and add the rest of the milk and cream.
Mix.
Stir in chopped pecans.
Pour into ice cream freezer.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.

title: brown sugar carrots
directions: Place carrots in pan with melted butter, onions, salt, parsley and sugar.
Cover closely and simmer over very low flame for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.
Serves 2.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli and cauliflower into bite-size pieces.
Mix all ingredients well.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients like pie crust.
Press in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Mix the remaining ingredients.
Pour over crust and bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Break cake in bite-size pieces.
Mix in other ingredients. Put in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix strawberries into glaze.
Put on top of cake mixture and refrigerate.

title: melting moments
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the oleo and sugar until fluffy. Blend in flour gradually.
Beat at medium speed on electric mixer for 5 minutes, until satin smooth.
Chill several hours.
Roll 1/2 teaspoon into marble size balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets at 350° for 12 minutes.
Put 2 cookies together with frosting. Yields 6 dozen.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Cut up the cauliflower into large salad bowl.
Mix the next 6 ingredients until well blended, then add to the cauliflower and toss.

title: italian stuffed mushrooms
directions: In a skillet, cook the bacon until crisp.
Meanwhile, remove mushroom stems from caps; set caps aside.
Mince half the stems and discard the rest.
Add minced stems to bacon and drippings, saute for 2-3 minutes.
Remove from the heat and stir in remaining ingredients.
Firmly stuff into mushroom caps.
Place in a greased 15 in. x 10 in. x 1 in. baking pan.
Bake at 425 degrees for 12 - 15 minutes or until the mushrooms are tender.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add enough milk to make it moist.
Add the 3 egg yolks and beat well, then add rest of milk and vanilla.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Cool and pour into pie shell.
Beat the 3 egg whites until stiff.
Add 6 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour on top of filling and bake until whites are brown.

title: pineapple au gratin
directions: Drain pineapple chunks and save 4 tablespoons juice.
Mix all ingredients (except crackers and butter) together and place in casserole.
Cover top with Ritz crackers and pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage brunch casserole
directions: Prepare the evening before.
Cook sausage; drain thoroughly on paper towels.
Beat the eggs and evaporated milk slightly.
Add sausage, cubed bread and Cheddar cheese.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch casserole; cover with foil.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes or until firm in a preheated 350° oven. Makes 6 servings.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Slice and boil 10 to 15 minutes in salt water.
Drain.
Put one layer of eggplant in baking dish.
Add one layer of cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle 1 teaspoon onion flakes over crackers.
(Can use fresh onions, chopped.)
Repeat layers.
Pour can of mushroom soup over all other ingredients.
Can mix or just leave soup on top.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: yam and apple casserole
directions: Boil potatoes and slice thick.
Slice apples and place with potatoes in layers in casserole.
Dot with butter.
Cover with juices, sugar and salt.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 400° until bubbly.
Baste and lower heat to 350° and continue cooking 40 minutes.
Add nuts and marshmallows and bake for 5 more minutes.

title: french breakfast puffs
directions: Mix Crisco, sugar and egg.
Add the remaining ingredients. Bake in greased muffin tins at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Then roll in butter, cinnamon and sugar.

title: tea cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Mix in other ingredients.
Roll into small balls.
Press in middle with thumb.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool before icing centers.

title: hot cranberry-apple cider
directions: In large kettle, combine apple cider, cranberry cocktail juice, brown sugar, cinnamon sticks and cloves.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Strain.
Serve hot! Serves 25.

title: cry baby cookies
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt and nuts together.
Add in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix cherry pie filling, crushed pineapple and Eagle Brand milk.
Fold in softened Cool Whip.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan and freeze.
Serve frozen.

title: meat loafspringfield, missouri
directions: Combine and mix all ingredients well.

title: baked beans and sausage
directions: Cut sausage in 1/2-inch pieces.
Saute, part at a time, in large skillet until lightly browned.
Remove to a paper towel. Preheat oven to 300°.
In large bowl mix beans, onions, brown sugar and catsup, stirring thoroughly to combine.
Stir in sausage.
Divide between 2 to 3-quart casseroles or 1 large casserole dish.
Lay pieces of bacon on top of bean mixture (if desired).
Bake for 2 hours at 300° or until mixture is thick.

title: fireside casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Saute chuck in butter and add tomato sauce. Remove from heat.
Combine cheeses and chives in bowl.
In 3-quart casserole, spread one-half of noodles.
Cover with all of cheese mixture.
Add rest of noodles.
Pour melted butter over noodles and then pour meat sauce over all.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: frozen fruitcake salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine fruits and nuts.
Stir together sour cream and Cool Whip and add to the fruit.
Stir well and pour into a mold and freeze overnight.
Unmold 10 minutes before serving.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients.
Add chicken, peas, celery, onions and eggs.
Let stand in refrigerator for at least 2 hours before serving.
Mix in potato sticks just before serving.
Mound on lettuce.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: cowboy cornbread
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients; set aside.
Saute the ground beef; let drain.
Prepare the onion, cheese and peppers and place in separate mounds ready to use.
Grease a large iron skillet; heat.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix ingredients and put in casserole dish.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Heat to crispness, about 15 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix the dry jello with the dry cake mix.
Add the eggs, oil and cold water and beat 4 minutes.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 325° and cool.
Grate the rind and squeeze the lemons.
Combine this juice with the powdered sugar.
Poke holes in the cake and pour this mixture over the cake.

title: country chicken salad
directions: Combine
chicken,
salad oil, orange juice, vinegar and salt. Let
stand while preparing remaining ingredients or let stand overnight.
Gently
toss
all together.
Makes 12 servings.

title: good picnic casserole
directions: Make stuffing according to directions.
Add chicken and vegetables.
Mix altogether.
Heat in microwave until hot.

title: english toffee
directions: Mix and press 2/3 of mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pork chops bavarian
directions: The amounts depend on how much you want to make.

title: hot bean casserole
directions: Fry bacon; saute onion in some of the bacon fat.
Stir all ingredients together and put in casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: buttermilk dressing
directions: Stir with wire whisk until blended. Cover and chill 2 hours. Serve with salad.

title: baked pork chops with rice
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides.
Remove from frying pan.
Put in small roaster, adding rice and tomato juice.
Bake in 350° oven for nearly 1 hour.

title: easy vegetable-beef soup
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in 4-quart Dutch oven, stirring frequently, until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in sauce mix, water, salt, pepper, mustard and tomatoes; break up tomatoes.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in noodles and vegetables. Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes longer. Makes 6 servings.

title: fresh vegetables and dip
directions: Wash and pat dry vegetables.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Peel carrots and slice into thin strips.
Mix together Hidden Valley salad mix into the cottage cheese and mayonnaise.
Refrigerate. Place on serving plate.
Ready to serve.
Keep chilled.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Combine and beat the cream cheese, egg and sugar.
Stir in chocolate morsels.
Set aside.
Combine the flour, sugar, soda, vinegar, vanilla, cocoa, salt, water and oil.
Beat well.
Fill lined cupcake tins 1/2 full with chocolate batter.
Top each with 1 heaping teaspoon of cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with sugar and nuts, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: About 20 minutes before serving, in 10-inch skillet, on medium low heat in hot oil, stir all ingredients until well mixed.
Cover pan and cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve immediately. Makes 4 servings.
50 calories per serving.

title: mimi's turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
When done, poke holes all over cake.
Pour can of sweetened condensed milk over hot cake.
Then pour caramel over cake and spread evenly. Then sprinkle chopped walnuts over cake.
Whip heavy cream with sugar until thick and fluffy.
Spread over cake when cake is cooled.
Refrigerate.

title: zucchini tomato kiesh
directions: Mix veggies together and put into buttered pie plate.
Mix Bisquick, milk and eggs together and pour over veggies.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Combine egg, shortening and corn.
Add corn mixture to flour; mix until smooth.
Drop by spoonful into hot, deep fat.
Fry until golden brown.

title: chalupa
directions: Put pork or beef roast, dry beans, onion, garlic, seasonings and water into large crock-pot.
Cover and cook for at least 10 to 12 hours, on low setting, or until meat falls apart.
Serve on top of small Fritos with your favorite garnish.
Serves several.
Meat and bean mixture freezes well.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy, gradually beat in
oil and sugar. Add zucchini, cinnamon, salt, baking soda
and	baking	powder. Mix well.
Gradually blend in flour, mixing
well
after
each addition.
Fold in chopped nuts, and chips.
Use
Bundt
pan or loaf
pans, filling 3/4 full.
Bake in 350° oven
for
hour. Great with cream cheese.
This recipe will make
6	small
loaf pans.

title: martin warner's brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch Pyrex pan.
No bowl needed.
In large pot over direct low heat, melt chocolate, butter and sugar.
Remove from heat; whisk in eggs, one at a time.
Whisk in vanilla and molasses.
Stir in flour, nuts and chocolate chips. Bake 30 minutes.
Cake is done when whole center puffs up and surface cracks across the center.
Cool for hours before cutting. Center will fall during cooling.
End product is fudgy.
Add more flour for a more cakey brownie (yuck).

title: green beans in mustard marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients; marinate overnight.
Serves 8.
