title: company cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling, salted water for 10 minutes.
Drain well.
Place 9 x 13 dish.
Saute onion in margarine until tender, then mix in cheese and soup.
Pour this sauce mixture over cabbage and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into 4 pieces.
Shake in 3/4 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon mixture.
Grease tube pan.
Put nuts in pan. Add coated biscuit pieces.
Boil 1/4 cup sugar, oleo, brown sugar, 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon and water.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake 40 minutes.
Turn out of pan while hot.

title: zesty steak chili
directions: In dutch oven, over medium heat, cook Steak and Garlic in Oil until meat is browned.
Add Onion; cook and stir for 5 minutes. Stir in 2 cups Water and the next 8 ingredients; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 2 hours or until tender.
Combine Flour, Cornmeal and remaining Water; stir until smooth.
Bring Chili to boil; add flour mixture; cook and stir for 2 minutes until thickened.
If desired, garnish with low-fat Cheese, light Sour Cream, Onions and Olives.

title: southwest cheesecake
directions: Combine chip crumbs and margarine; press onto bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Cook sausage until done; drain grease.
Add onion, celery, bell pepper.
Mix soup, rice, and broth; add to sausage mixture. Let set overnight.
Next day, add almonds and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325 degrees.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Cream well cream cheese; add the crushed pineapple with juice last.
Mix in mayonnaise, sugar, vanilla, salt, powdered sugar and
Cool
Whip.
Blend well.
Now add pineapple; blend well.
Add the cranberries and the nuts.
Mix easy.
Pour into a
x 13-inch glass dish; cover and freeze. Just slice into squares and serve.

title: fresh vegetable marinade
directions: Remove florets from broccoli and cut into bite sized (don't use stalks).
Combine broccoli, cauliflower, mushrooms, celery and green peppers; toss lightly.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour over vegetables.
Chill at least 3 hours.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, water, salt and vinegar.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved.
Boil until 260° or until it has reached hard boil stage.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Stir to mix.
Slowly pour syrup over popcorn.
Stir with wooden spoon.
Dampen hands with cold water and press into balls.
Wrap in plastic wrap.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Stir and let stand at room temperature all day (10 hours minimum).
Starter is now ready to use.
If bread is to be made, measure out Starter for recipe and return remaining portion to refrigerator, or put all of Starter in refrigerator to make bread another day.

title: grandma's tea cakes
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, lemon extract and milk.
Mix well.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well. Chill 1 or 2 hours. Shape into 1 1/4 inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 11 to 13 minutes. Do not overbake.
Cool 1 minute in pan.
Place on wire rack.
Yield:
5 dozen.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown pork chops; add salt and pepper.
After chops are brown, add mushrooms with liquid and the beef broth.
Cook on low heat for 1 hour.
Add Worcestershire sauce and rice.
Continue cooking for 30 to 45 minutes more until rice is done.

title: fried salmon patties
directions: Crush the crackers until they are fine.
Mix them with all the other ingredients.
Drop by tablespoons and fry in the butter.

title: market salad
directions: In a large bowl, whisk together first 5 ingredients.
Add vegetables; toss thoroughly to blend.
Add cheese; toss lightly. Cover and chill 2 to 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Mix sugar and water into melted chocolate.
Beat in egg.
Add butter, 1 spoon at a time, beating well after each.
Ice cake.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Beat eggs well; add milk, mustard, nutmeg and salt.
Mix well.
Add spinach and cheese to mixture.
Stir well.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300°.
Bake until knife inserted in middle comes out clean, about 40 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Cut and serve.

title: mexican wedding cake(cookies)
directions: Mix all ingredients and work into a crumb mixture.
Roll into small balls; flatten with glass dipped in flour.
Bake in slow oven (275°) for 40 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar until thickly coated.
Makes 60 cookies.
Delicious.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over 100% bran cereal and let cool.
Cream sugar and shortenings.
Add eggs, cooled 100% bran and buttermilk. Add dry ingredients.
Add All-Bran.
Stir until moistened well. Store in covered dish.
Can be kept in refrigerator 6 weeks.
When ready to use, add raisins, dates, nuts, etc. and bake in muffin pans at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: lee's shrimp in angel hair pasta casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter the sides and bottom of an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
In bowl, mix eggs, half and half, yogurt, Feta and Swiss cheeses, parsley, basil and oregano.
Spread 1/2 the angel hair pasta on the bottom of baking dish.
Cover with salsa.
Add 1/2 the shrimp.
Add remaining pasta to baking dish. Pour and spread egg mixture over pasta.
Add remaining shrimp and top with Monterey Jack cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes (until bubbling).
Cover with foil during the baking.
Remove and let stand 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: rolled tortillas
directions: Mix all ingredients except tortillas together and spread on tortillas.
Roll tightly and wrap in plastic wrap.
Chill at least 2 hours. Cut in 1-inch slices and serve.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and add salt, pepper and onion.
Set aside.
Mash Ro-Tel tomatoes and add 3 cans of soup.
Stir well and add to meat.

title: dessert lemon soup
directions: Boil water, sugar and raisins for 10 to 15 minutes.
In a small bowl, stir potato flour into 1/2 cup cold water.
While stirring, pour the potato flour mixture into the boiling soup. Beat the egg in a bowl, then stir it into the soup.
Add the lemon juice and peel and stir well.
The soup is best served chilled.

title: cheesy stuffed potatoes
directions: Scoop out centers of potatoes, leaving skins intact.
In a bowl combine potato centers with remaining ingredients except cheese. Beat until fluffy.
Stir in cheese.
Mound mixture into skins. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed.
Divide batter in half.
First half, add 1/2 can sweet condensed milk and 1 stick melted butter. Bake approximately 10 minutes or until firm.

title: shrimp pasta salad
directions: Place in a large bowl.
Set aside.

title: easy refrigerator yeast rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over shortening, sugar and salt.
Blend and cool.
Add beaten eggs.
Sprinkle yeast into warm water and stir until dissolved, then add to mixture.
Add flour; blend well. Cover and place in refrigerator for at least 5 hours.
Dough must be in large mixing bowl as it rises slightly in refrigerator. This will keep a week to 10 days and may be used as needed.
Three hours before using rolls, roll into desired shape, using enough extra flour to make dough easy to handle.
Place in greased pan; allow to rise at room temperature for 3 hours or until double in size.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: seasoned oyster crackers
directions: Place all ingredients in double sack.
Shake well.
Leave overnight.

title: okra bread
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; stir in okra.
(If batter is too moist, add a bit more hush puppy mix.)
Pour into greased and floured 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden.
Cut into squares.

title: german coleslaw
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake one hour in a 350° oven.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water until tender. Drain.
Melt butter.
Stir in flour and salt until smooth.
Add milk gradually, stirring until thickened.
Add cheese.
Cover and let stand until cheese melts.
Stir to mix.
Place broccoli in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Pour cheese sauce over broccoli.
Cover with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 20 or 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Wash peppers and cut off tops.
Remove seeds. Boil (steam) in 1-inch of water for 5 minutes. Brown meat and onion.
Drain.
Add tomato sauce, rice and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 5 to 10 minutes. Stand peppers upright in baking dish.
Place 1/2 ounce of cheese in bottom of each, then fill with meat mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes.
Place 1/2 ounce of cheese on top of each pepper before serving.

title: lemon fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit and save all juices except orange juice.
Mix reserved juices with pudding mix.
Mix gently with fruit. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: sweet potato custard
directions: Peel, cut up and cook potatoes until tender. Drain potatoes. Beat with mixer.
Add butter and sugar.
Beat well. Add the milk and eggs; continue to beat. Add salt and flavoring after beating well.
Pour into 2 pie shells and bake at 350° until firm.

title: ugly cake
directions: Cream butter, cake mix and 1 egg.
The mixture is like dry pie crust mix.
Press this into the bottom of an 8 x 10-inch pan.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt oleo in 4-quart baking dish.
Add onion soup mix and mix well.
Place chicken in a layer on top of mixture.
Sprinkle the rice on top of this.
Add the water.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove cover and brown.
If you do not have a 4-quart casserole dish, you can halve this recipe and bake it in two 2-quart casseroles.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: art's potato saladserves 16
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Boil for 25-30 minutes.
Cool, then dice.
Add next 8 ingredients and mix.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Mix noodles, tuna, sour cream, milk, mushrooms, salt and black pepper.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix bread crumbs, cheese and margarine.
Sprinkle over noodle mixture and bake uncovered for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sherried beef
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Season meat and mix all ingredients together.
Place in pot and cover.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°, then change to 300°.
Continue baking for two and one-half hours. Stirring is not necessary.
Serve over rice.

title: country sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Divide into 1 pound packs.
Wrap and freeze until ready to use.

title: stuffed cornish hens
directions: Mix ingredients for stuffing in bowl.
Stuff mixture into cornish hens.
Brush hens with melted butter and season to taste. Roast at 350° for approximately 1 1/2 hours.
During roasting time, water may be added.
Baste often.
Raise temperature in oven to 400° for last 10 minutes.
Garnish may be added on serving platter for color.

title: reese's cups
directions: Melt butter.
Crush crackers.
Beat all together.
Pour in pan.
Melt chocolate chips and pour over top.

title: over thats
directions: Melt butter in baking pan.
Add crushed crackers evenly over butter. Sprinkle chocolate bits over crackers.
Add coconut. Place pecans evenly over coconut. Drizzle condensed milk over top of the pecans.
Place in oven at 350° to 400° until coconut has a golden look.
Let cool and cut in squares.

title: orange chicken
directions: Bake in oven at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add orange rind and cranberry sauce.
Chill until thickened.
Stir in pineapple and celery. Pour into a 1 1/2-quart mold or large bowl and chill until set. Serve with a dollop of mayonnaise.

title: scalloped potatoes and ham
directions: For sauce, stir together the soup, milk, marjoram and pepper in a bowl.
Set aside.

title: exquisite fruit topping
directions: Mix the marshmallow cream and cream cheese together. Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Dip cut up fruits in this tasty dip.

title: eagle brand
directions: Blend in blender.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: turtle bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Mix 1 1/2 cups flour and next 3 ingredients. Add melted butter and mix until crumbly. Reserve 3/4 cup and put rest in a greased and floured 9 x 13 pan. Bake for 10 minutes. Remove from oven and reduce heat to 350°. Sprinkle nuts and chips over partially baked layer. Combine 1/4 cup flour and caramel. Drizzle over chips and nuts. Sprinkle reserved crumbs over caramel mixture. Bake 20 minutes. Cool and cut.

title: quick luscious potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese, in a large casserole. Mix well.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: perfect scalloped oysters
directions: Drain oysters, saving liquid.
Combine crumbs, butter, salt and pepper.
Spread 1/3 of buttered crumbs in a greased 8 x 1 1/4-inch round pan; cover with half the oysters.
Using another third of the crumbs, spread a second layer; cover with remaining oysters.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease 13 X 9 X 2 inch rectangular pan.
Beat dry cake mix, oil, eggs and sour cream in medium bowl on medium speed 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally. Spread half of batter into pan.
Stir together brown sugar, pecans and cinnamon; sprinkle over batter in pan.
Carefully spread remaining batter evenly over pecan mixture.
Bake about 45 minutes or until deep golden brown.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Combine cheese and mayonnaise. Blend until smooth. Fold in whipped cream, fruit and marshmallows.
Put into loaf pan as mold. Freeze until firm. Cut into slices.
You may serve while still frozen.

title: rice with spinach
directions: Mix oil, onion and spinach. Cook over low heat for 5 minutes. Add rice and parsley.
Stir to coat.
Add chicken broth. Cover and cook with rice until tender.
Add grated cheese, salt and pepper before fully cooked.
Add more broth, if needed.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Bring Jell-O and pineapple to a boil.
Cool completely.
Add buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Mix together and refrigerate.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Put dates, cherries, pineapple and nuts in bowl.
Mix flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add to fruit.
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Add to floured fruit mix.
Grease a cookie sheet.
Make into balls and mash down with fork.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes. Cookies should be light in color and edges brown when removed from oven.

title: window cleaner
directions: You may also add blue or green food coloring if you want it colored.

title: sassy zucchini
directions: In skillet (I prefer electric), cook beef and onion until meat is browned.
Stir in next 4 ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Stir in rice and zucchini.
Cover tightly.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Cook until zucchini is tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: crab ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, drained crabmeat and 2 tablespoons of cocktail sauce.
Add garlic powder to your taste.
Shape into a ball.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Serve by pouring cocktail sauce over top with your favorite crackers on the side.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add the rest of the ingredients except milk and clams.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Add clams and milk, then heat thoroughly.
Serve.

title: super bowl chili or party chili
directions: In a large pot (canner large enough to hold 4 gallons chili), bring tomatoes, Tabasco sauce and tomato paste to a simmer.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion. Drain off grease.
Pour beef and onion into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Spread mixed vegetables over it and creamed corn over that.
Spread mashed potatoes over corn.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: poor boy stroganoff
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add beef and lightly brown.
Add salt and pepper.
Place dry noodles onto meat.
Cover with tomato juice, vinegar and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and simmer until noodles are tender, about 40 minutes.
Add more juice if necessary.
Stir in sour cream and heat through.

title: potato flitters
directions: Grate potatoes.
Add eggs, flour, salt and pepper. Mix well. Fry with a little vegetable oil until done.

title: peanut butter cup bars
directions: Mix melted butter and peanut butter.
Add rest of ingredients except chocolate.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate bits and then spread over top.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Combine sugar, oil, vinegar and salt. Add drained beans and onion. Stir well. Serve chilled.

title: pineapple souffle
directions: Beat together sugar, butter and eggs.
Add and stir in pineapple.
Fold in bread crumbs.
Bake in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish at 350° for 1 hour.
Can be served hot or cold.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Make batter of 1 cup sugar, flour, milk, baking powder and salt.
Melt butter in baking pan.
Pour batter in butter; add fruit.
Mix rest of sugar, water and pinch of salt together and pour over batter and fruit.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt in top of double boiler.
Add milk gradually.
Add chocolate and cook over boiling water until chocolate is melted and mixture is thick, stirring constantly. Cook for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour small amount over egg yolks.
Return to double boiler and cook 2 minutes longer. Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Put in pie shell and cool.
Top with whipped cream.

title: chocolate marshmallow bars
directions: Place the first four ingredients in a double boiler (water in bottom should be hot, but not boiling).
When melted, pour over Rice Krispies and marshmallows in a large bowl.
Mix and pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate.
Cut into squares.

title: nick's pancakes
directions: Heat small 8-inch skillet on medium heat with 1/2 teaspoon butter Crisco.
Beat ingredients with wire whisk until blended. Pour into hot skillet and cook until edges only are dry.
Flip over and cook until golden.

title: amish pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs together.
Add pumpkin.
Then add dry ingredients, then water, stirring just until mixed.
Pour batter into two greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Freezes well.
May use 3 mini loaves at 40 to 45 minutes.

title: baked fruit pudding
directions: Drain fruits well.
Place in layers in a baking dish. Sprinkle each layer with brown sugar, dabs of butter and slivers of almonds.
Crush macaroons.
To each layer, add lemon juice and sherry (1/2 cup of sherry in all).
Cover top layer with crushed macaroons. Bake for 30 minutes and serve hot.

title: so easy cream puffs
directions: Melt shortening in water and bring to a boil.
Dump in flour and salt all at once.
Stir and remove from heat.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Place on a cookie sheet a tablespoon at a time for large puffs or a teaspoon for small puffs.
Cook at 450° for 20 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° until lightly brown.
Cool. Slice off 1/4 from top of puff.
Fill with cream filling.
Replace top and sprinkle with powdered sugar or if filled with chocolate cream, dribble with chocolate.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all but chips.
Fold in chips.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: In a large bowl, add sugar, salt and shortening.
Add scalded milk and mix with mixer. Add water and mix.
Next, add yeast and mix.
Next, add eggs and mix.
Add 2 cups flour and mix with mixer. Add 2 more cups flour and beat well with mixer.
Add 2 cups of flour and stir with wooden spoon. Add 2 cups of flour and stir with wooden spoon. The last 2 cups of flour just work enough in to have a soft dough.
(Knead with hands.)
Sprinkle flour on a smooth surface and put dough out on this.
Let raise for 5 minutes. While dough is resting, grease bowl.
At the end of 5 minutes, knead dough on flat surface until it is elastic and smooth.
Place in bowl and let rise until more than double in bulk. When dough has risen, divide in half and roll out thin. Next, spread with butter Crisco.
Sprinkle on top of this white sugar.
Next, sprinkle brown sugar on top of that, then sprinkle with cinnamon.
Roll up like jelly roll. Cut into rolls about 1 1/2 to 2-inches thick.
Place on pans sprayed with Pam and nuts sprinkled on bottom.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 20 minutes.

title: quesadillas
directions: Cut onion and pepper into 1/2-inch squares.
Cut chicken or beef into 1/2 to 1-inch strips or crumble sausage.
Saute onion, pepper and meat.
On 1/2 of a flour tortilla place a layer of cheese, a layer of onion, pepper, and meat and another layer of cheese.
Fold the other half of the tortilla over to form a half moon shape.
Cook in a lightly greased electric skillet at 300° until tortilla begins to brown, then flip over and brown the other side.
Use a knife or pizza cutter to cut into wedges.

title: chocaroon pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in a saucepan over low heat.
Stir in eggs, sugar, flour and vanilla.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Combine milk and coconut; spoon over chocolate mixture, leaving a 1/2-inch border.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool at least 2 hours before serving.

title: mexican chocolate chiffon cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.

title: children's play doh
directions: Combine salt and flour with water until molding consistency. Add a few drops of food coloring.
Make sure you do not get the food coloring on your hands, as it does not wash off immediately. Mix food coloring into doh until uniform.

title: sausage balls
directions: Place all ingredients in a bowl and mix thoroughly with your hands.
Roll mixture into balls, 1-inch each in diameter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes or until slightly brown.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Start with COLD OVEN!
Have everything at room temperature. Cream shortening, margarine and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat after each egg.
Add
flour,
spoonfuls
at a time, with milk. Add
vanilla. Fold
in
pineapple.
Pour
into
greased
and floured tube pan. Place in cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Glaze with 1/2
stick
margarine, 1 1/2 cups powdered sugar and 1 cup pineapple, drained.
Glaze cake while hot.

title: breakfast apple squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Combine flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Pour eggs into small bowl; gradually beat in sugar until mixture is light, about 2 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 35 minutes or until edges pull away from pan.
Cut in 24 squares.

title: ginger, lemon, walnut muffins
directions: Grate lemon peel and ginger; mix with sugar.
Add butter and beat until smooth.
Add eggs and sour cream.
Add nuts and dry ingredients by folding gently.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes in greased tin.

title: fish loaf
directions: Grind fish in food grinder.
Grate onion on fine side.
Add eggs, pepper and salt, butter and beat in milk gradually.
Put into 9 x 9 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° to 375°.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: taco casserole
directions: Cook together ground beef, onion and green chilies.
Drain and add taco seasoning.
Add tomatoes and cream of mushroom soup to the macaroni after it has been cooked and drained.
Place a layer of ground beef mixture in casserole dish. Top with the noodle mixture.
Continue alternating layers until all is used. Top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: oven round steak dinner
directions: Season meat with 2 teaspoons salt and dash pepper.
Roll in flour.
Cook onions in hot fat until tender but not brown; remove onions and brown meat slowly on both sides.
Place meat in 3-quart casserole, add onions, potatoes and bay leaf; pour soup over. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 45 minutes or until meat is tender.
Add beans; cook 10 to 15 minutes more.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix butter, sugars, eggs, vanilla and peanut butter until smooth.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add to peanut butter mixture.
Add oats and stir until moistened.
Spread into a greased sheet pan until smooth.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Combine graham crumbs, margarine and brown sugar.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Do not cook.
Prepare Dream Whip and combine with cream cheese and icing sugar.
Whip together until well blended and spread onto crumb mixture.
Top with cherries.
Chill.

title: fiesta dip
directions: In medium bowl, combine ingredients. Blend well.
Refrigerate until ready to serve. Serve with tortilla chips or fresh vegetables.

title: peanut brittle(church of god candy)
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water; bring to boil and boil about 5 minutes (until it strings).
Add peanuts and cook until golden brown (290° on candy thermometer).
Add salt, soda and margarine (use hard margarine, not whipped or light); stir well.
Pour onto lightly buttered surface; a cookie sheet or aluminum pie pans work well.
Thin candy is more crisp than thick slabs.
Break into pieces and store in airtight cans or bowls.

title: pineapple delight salad
directions: Drain pineapple, Add enough water to pineapple juice to make 1 cup of liquid.
Add gelatin to liquid and boil 2 minutes.
Add marshmallows and cool.
Add cottage cheese, pineapple and nuts. Fold in whipping cream.
Chill until firm in mold.

title: chicken lasagne
directions: Sauce:
Saute onion and green pepper.
Add drained mushrooms, chicken soup, pimento and basil.
Mix together.
Layer noodles, chicken, cheese, cottage cheese and sauce; repeat.
Sprinkle Parmesan on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, uncovered, in 11 1/2 x 7-inch baking dish.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown the meat with the onion.
Drain the fat. Add the remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add water, salt and pepper, if needed.

title: lemon fluff jello
directions: Dissolve the jello in boiling water.
Add cold water and undrained pineapple.
When jello begins to thicken, stir in pie filling and Cool Whip.
This makes a good size salad or dessert.

title: calzones
directions: Unroll pizza crust stretching to form 14 x 11-inch rectangle. Spread Ricotta on half of dough lengthwise to within 1-inch of the edge.
Sprinkle the pepperoni, ham and Mozzarella.
Fold unfilled side of dough over filled half and press edges together. Transfer to a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with basil and Parmesan if desired.
Slice. Serve with spaghetti sauce for dipping.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine other ingredients, except paprika, and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 375° to 400° for 1 hour.

title: 3 bean casserole
directions: Chop up bacon; fry until crisp.
Remove fat; put aside.
Cook beef and onion until brown.
Return bacon and all other ingredients to pan; mix well.
Put in casserole.
Bake for 1 hour and 30 minutes at 325°.

title: lillian's rhubarb pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add white sugar, salt and 5 to 6 tablespoons flour.
Add rhubarb and mix well.
Pour in unbaked pie crust.
Mix brown sugar, 1/2 cup flour and butter well.
Sprinkle over top of pie.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Decrease heat to 375° and bake until done.

title: caribbean baked squash
directions: Place squash in 1-quart casserole.
Cover.
Microwave 10 to 12 minutes on High or until almost tender, stirring once.
Set aside.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Mix butter, powdered sugar and egg.
Fold in Cool Whip, pineapple and apple chunks.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: chicken sopa casserole
directions: Boil chicken, debone and cut into small pieces.
Mix chicken with soups, onion and chilies.
Add milk.
Break tortillas or Doritos in small pieces.

title: sausage squares
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with 1 can crescent rolls. Brown sausage and drain; add Cheez Whiz.
Spread over rolls and top with other can of rolls.
Brown in 350° oven.
Cut into squares.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Melt butter,
adding
flour.
Mix well.
Add 1/3 cup of sour cream.
Return to heat, making paste.
Add remaining sour cream; stir
constantly.
Season
to
taste with salt, pepper, paprika and
cayenne red pepper.
Cut cheese into small pieces and add to mixture.
Stir until dissolved.
Add mushrooms.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Dredge meat in flour.
In a skillet with 1/4 cup margarine or butter, saute onions until tender.
Remove from pan; set aside. Add remaining butter and brown meat on all sides.
May need to add a little more butter.
This is cooked on medium heat.
Add broth and seasonings to taste.
Cook until meat is tender and sauce thickened.
Just before serving, add plain yogurt or sour cream. Heat through.
Serve over cooked, flat, buttered and seasoned noodles.

title: snowy swirls meat loaf surprise
directions: *Medium Cheddar cheese can be substituted, if desired.

title: sweet and sour marinade(venison)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Marinate venison or meats for 2 to 6 hours.
Baste meat with mixture while cooking.

title: pineapple-pecan cheese ball
directions: Mix together until well blended.
Shape into ball; wrap in Saran Wrap and chill at least 3 hours or overnight.

title: stuffed veal shoulder
directions: Have pocket cut in meat to hold stuffing.
Melt half the shortening in a heavy skillet.
Add onion and cook slowly until soft, then add parsley, celery, salt and bread crumbs.
Toss until well mixed.
Cool.
Add half the liquid and mix.
Stuff lightly into the pocket; tie with twine.
Rub outside of roast with salt, then brown on both sides in remaining shortening.
Pour in rest of liquid and bake in slow oven (325°) 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Add more water if necessary.
Make gravy with remaining liquid.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°.
Put blueberries, sugar, flour and cinnamon into mixing bowl. Pour blueberry mixture into pie crusts. Cut margarine into small pieces.
Put them on top of the blueberry mixture.
Wet your fingers with cold water and run them along the top edge of the bottom pie crust.
Turn the remaining crust upside-down on top of the blueberries and crust together. Cut slits in the top crust to let steam escape.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until lightly brown at 350°.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain all
vegetables.	Combine
remaining ingredients; mix together and pour over vegetables.

title: quickie  pie (cobbler)
directions: Mix sugar, flour, milk and baking powder; melt butter in a glass casserole.
Pour mixture over melted butter.
Do not stir. Put peaches on top.
Bake at 350° until brown on top.

title: scalloped cauliflower
directions: Combine soup, milk, and eggs. Stir in half of cheese, bread crumbs, parsley, pimento, onion, salt and pepper.
Then add cauliflower.
Turn into 10 x 6 x 2 inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and bake 5 minutes more.
Serves 6-8.

title: molasses softies
directions: Cream butter; then slowly add sugar, egg, molasses, syrup, milk, flour, soda, cinnamon and ginger.
Mix well.
Scoop into balls; then roll in sugar.
Bake for 5 minutes at 325°.

title: santa fe chicken
directions: Saute chicken in butter 4 to 5 minutes; add onion and bell pepper and saute.
Drain liquid from Ro-Tel into a 2 cup measuring cup; add water to make 2 cups.
Add 2 tsp. chicken bouillon to liquid mixture and stir to dissolve.
Add to chicken mixture and bring to boil.
Stir in Ro-Tel and rice.
Turn off heat.
Top with grated cheese and place the lid on it.
Let stand 10 minutes until the juice is absorbed.

title: incredible cheesecake
directions: Beat eggs well.
Then preheat oven to 350°.
Mix in sugar, vanilla and cream cheese. When mixed well add sour cream.
Pour into cheesecake pan already prepared with graham cracker crust or 3 deep-dish pie crusts.
Bake until outside edges are brown and center looks stiff.
Chill overnight or at least 4 to 5 hours. Can also be converted to low-fat version.
Use Egg Beaters, low-fat cream cheese and low-fat sour cream.
May need to bake a little longer.

title: jumbo rice krispies cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt and set aside.
Measure margarine and sugar into large mixing bowl.
Beat until well blended and smooth.
Add egg and vanilla flavoring and beat well. Add sifted dry ingredients and mix until combined.
Stir in Rice Krispies, chocolate chips and nuts.
Mix until well combined. Drop by level measuring tablespoons onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until they are brown. Remove immediately from baking sheet to cooling rack.

title: shrimp louis dip
directions: Stir all ingredients and mix well.
Cover and chill.
Makes 3 cups.

title: hearty chicken bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a medium bowl, combine potatoes, half the cheese and half the onions.
Mix thoroughly.
Spoon into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole, spreading across bottom and up sides to form a shell.
In a large bowl, combine chicken, mixed vegetables, soup, milk and seasonings.
Pour into potato shell. Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes or until heated through.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake 3 more minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: lemon delight
directions: Pour over rhubarb, then pour 1/2 cup water over it.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix together.
Press into pie shell.
Save some for topping.

title: chicken deluxe
directions: Place chicken in greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place half slice of cheese on each chicken breast half.
Cover chicken and cheese with undiluted cream of chicken soup.
Pour sherry over all.
Combine stuffing mix with melted butter; spread over mixture in pan.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Rich, but good!

title: shoyu chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chicken.
Place chicken in shallow, ovenproof pan.
Pour soy mixture over and bake at 325° for 1 hour, turning twice.
Sauce may be thickened with cornstarch.
Serve with hot rice.

title: glazed rum carrots
directions: Put carrots (cut into 2-inch lengths) into a saucepan with water, brown sugar, butter and rum.
Cook, boiling gently, until carrots are glazed and water has evaporated.
Be careful not to burn!
I usually parboil carrots first.

title: iced oatmeal-raisin cookies
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Combine oats, flour, walnuts, soda, salt and cinnamon.	Cream shortening, butter and sugars until fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.	Beat in dry ingredients
until mixed.
Stir
in
raisins.
Drop by tablespoons 2 inches
apart onto cookie sheets.
Bake for 12 minutes.
Cool on cookie sheets on rack for 5 minutes.
When cool, brush with icing.

title: kick-off bars
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and set aside.
Melt margarine and peanut butter over low heat.
Add marshmallows and melt until smooth.
Immediately pour marshmallow mixture over cereal mix. Press into 10 1/2 x 15 1/2-inch greased jelly roll pan.
Let stand until firm.
Cut into bars.

title: french crepe
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder and salt.
Combine eggs, milk and water.
Beat until smooth.
(I like to make batter the night before.)
In cast-iron skillet, add shortening (Crisco). When very hot, add 3 to 4 tablespoons of batter and fry until golden brown.
Serve with your favorite topping.
Brown sugar and sour cream is mine.
Roll like a jelly roll.
Enjoy.

title: tennessee pot roast
directions: Combine
flour, salt, pepper and allspice.
Dredge meat, reserving excess flour.
Brown meat in shortening.	Remove meat to Dutch oven or large pan. Heat apple juice and bouillon cube and stir to dissolve.
Pour liquid over meat; cover tightly and cook slowly 2 hours.
Add carrots, celery, potatoes and thyme; cover and
continue
cooking for 30 minutes, or until meat and vegetables	are
tender.
Remove
meat
and
vegetables to warm platter.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: sweet potatoes and apples
directions: Pare and slice sweet potatoes.
Core and slice apples. Arrange sweet potatoes and apples in alternate layers in buttered casserole.

title: lima bean soup
directions: Rinse and pick over beans and place in a large stock pot. Cover with cold water; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat; cover and let sit one hour.
Drain beans.
Replace beans in stock pot along with the ham stock, vegetables and spices.
Simmer 1 hour or until vegetables are fully cooked.
Add ham.
Freezes well.

title: low-fat pintos
directions: Slice onions and separate in rings.
Soak in sweet milk for 1 hour or overnight, if you like.
Make batter of Aunt Jemima pancake mix, as it says on box.
Have the batter pretty thick. Dip onion rings one at a time in the batter and drop in hot deep fry grease.
Drain on paper towels.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Cream shortening in a large mixing bowl; gradually add sugars, beating at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, beating well.
Combine flour, soda and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Stir in water, nuts, coconut and candy. Chill dough at least one hour.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 325° for 12 minutes or until browned.
Cool.
Yields 16 dozen.

title: orange-cranberry relish
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Throw away the juice.

title: apple bars
directions: Mix well and roll out half to fit 8 x 12-inch pan.
Crust comes only part way up the sides.

title: tin plate special
directions: Wash beans.
Cover with cold water and let soak overnight. Bring beans to a boil and cook 1 hour.
Drain, discarding water. Brown roast in hot shortening in a large Dutch oven or roaster. Add peppers and onions; cook until tender.
Add beans and remaining ingredients.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 2 1/2 or 3 hours or until tender.

title: bailey's irish cream
directions: Beat eggs in blender.
Add other ingredients and chill.
Shake well before serving.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Put onion and rice in small pot with 1 cup water, salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and parboil for 10 to 15 minutes.
Make sure all water is absorbed.
Add to uncooked ground beef.
Add garlic powder, salt and pepper to taste.

title: mouse cookies
directions: Freeze cookie dough 1 hour or more.
Remove wrapper and slice frozen dough into 1/4-inch slices (head).
Cut some slices into 1/4-inch slices for ears.
Press on ears, M&M's for eyes and a chocolate chip for the nose.
Bake at 350° on an ungreased cookie sheet for 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: momma's fudge
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients until thick (medium to hard ball forms when dropped in cool water).
Add the butter, vanilla and peanut butter.
Pour into a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch dish.
Cut into squares.
Bottom and sides of dish may be slightly buttered.

title: strawberry fruit salad
directions: Sprinkle jello on Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Blend in cottage cheese, fruit cocktail and pineapple.
Mix well.
Add pecans. Chill before serving.

title: hot dish
directions: Brown meat. Add onion; cook until tender.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Mix well. Stir in noodles.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle crumbs over top. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes or until hot.

title: dogfood (sloppy joe dip)(yield: 4-6 servings)
directions: 1. Cook the meat in a skillet and drain off any fat.

title: reese's-n-chips deluxe
directions: You will also need mini muffin paper liners.

title: barbecue sauce for ribs
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium-sized saucepan and bring mixture to a boil, stirring constantly.
Serve over your favorite meat.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Topping:
Mix brown sugar, walnuts and 1/2 cup chocolate pieces; set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon; set aside.
Beat shortening and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Add egg; beat thoroughly.
Add bananas, oatmeal and nut meats.
Mix sifted dry ingredients together with other mixture, mixing thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet, 1 1/2 inches apart.
Bake until cookies are done; remove at once.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut hard-cooked Eggs lengthwise.
Remove yolks and mash.
Then blend together with dressing mixture.
Then add the crumbled bacon. Blend together then fill the egg whites.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix ingredients in large bowl and chill overnight.
Makes a big salad.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine soup, 1 cup cheese, sour cream and pepper.
Stir in vegetables and half of onions.
Spoon into 3-quart oblong baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Stir, sprinkle remaining half of cheese and onions over vegetable mixture. Bake 20 minutes or until hot and bubbling and onions are golden.
Makes about 12 servings.

title: russian tea
directions: Make 1/2 gallon tea with 8 bags of water and 1 1/2 cups sugar. Mix rest of ingredients. Make 1 day ahead of serving so cloves can mellow.

title: marbled brownies
directions: Cream cheese mixture; beat together the softened cream cheese and butter.
Add the sugar, eggs, flour and vanilla.
Beat until smooth and set aside.
Prepare one package Duncan Hines double fudge brownie mix using cake like instructions.
Spread half of the brownie batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour all of the cream cheese mixture over the brownie batter.
Spoon the remaining brownie batter in spots over the top.
Swirl the two mixtures together with a knife or spatula.
Bake at 350° for 36 to 39 minutes.
Cool and frost with milk chocolate (ready made) frosting.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cornstarch and salt together.
Add to boiling water, stirring constantly and cook over low heat until mixture is thickened and transparent in color.
Add beaten egg yolks; stir well.
Remove from heat; add lemon juice and rind. Cool; pour lemon filling into pastry shell.
Make meringue and cover top of pie.

title: white clam sauce
directions: Saute garlic in hot oil for 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 7 minutes.
Serve over cooked spaghetti or linguine.

title: hot chicken or ham salad
directions: Place in baking dish.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 450°.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Bring to boil berries and 2 cups sugar. Add another cup sugar. Bring to full rolling boil. Boil 7 minutes. Remove, skim and stir frequently until cold. Next morning, put in containers and store in freezer.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Combine 1 cup cornmeal, milk, eggs, salt, soda, bacon drippings and corn in a bowl.
Mix and set aside.
Saute ground beef until light brown.
Drain and set aside.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine and sift all dry ingredients.
Gradually beat in walnuts, oil, eggs, raisins and carrots.
Pour into sheet pan or 3 8 inch layers.
Bake at 325 degrees for 35 minutes.
Raisins are optional and the walnut are put on top of icing and not in the cake.

title: spinach dip
directions: Let frozen spinach thaw overnight.
Mix all ingredients together.

title: pumpkin brownies
directions: Spray an
x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan.
Pour batter into pan.
Spread evenly.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes. Cool in pan.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Makes 15.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, flour and 1/4 cup milk.
Mix well and add eggs and remaining milk, butter and vanilla.
Cook in a double boiler until thick.

title: fruity pizza pie
directions: Slice cookie dough and place on 14-inch pizza pan with sides touching.
Bake as directed on dough package.
Cool.
Mix together cream cheese and whipped topping.
Spread cheese mixture on cooled crust.
Slice fruits and arrange on top of cheese mixture.

title: deviled crabs
directions: Put 1 tablespoon butter in pan, then simmer 1/2 cup celery and onion.
Add to crab mixture.
Add 1 or 2 raw eggs.
If mixture is too wet, add a little cracker meal.
Season with salt and pepper. Roll and dip in egg and cracker meal.
Fry in deep fat.

title: sweet tortilla triangles
directions: Heat broiler.
In small bowl, combine sugar and cinnamon. Brush both sides of tortilla wedges with melted butter;
sprinkle both sides with cinnamon & sugar.
Place tortilla wedges on baking sheet; place in broiler about 4 inches from heat.
Broil 1 minute per side or until golden brown.
Serve with scoop Dulce de Leche Ice Cream.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix
in
bowl the nut butter, water, honey and vanilla. Stir in
other
ingredients.
Roll
into
balls
and place on sprayed cookie
sheet.
Mash
balls down lightly with a fork. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes approximately 3 1/2 to 4 dozen tablespoon sized cookies.

title: old-fashioned custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs lightly; add sugar, salt, nutmeg and milk.
Beat well together and pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, then sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: island chicken and rice
directions: Sprinkle chicken with pepper and 1 tablespoon cornstarch.
In a large skillet, cook chicken and onions in oil until lightly brown.
Blend reserved peach juice, soy sauce, vinegar and remaining cornstarch and add to chicken.
Cook, stirring until clear and thickened.
Add peaches, green pepper and tomato. Simmer 5 minutes or until green pepper is tender-crisp.
Serve over fluffy rice and sprinkle with almonds.

title: mom's special chocolate milk shake
directions: Easy!
Add all ingredients into the blender and mix for 1 minute.
Pour into a tall glass and sprinkle chocolate jimmies on top.
Makes 1 serving.

title: cherry-angel food cake
directions: Mix all this together until well blended.
Spread this between layers and on top of cake.
Pour a can of cherry pie filling over top of cake.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: banana dogs
directions: Spread peanut butter on the inside of the hot dog rolls.
Peel banana for each roll.
Place banana in roll like a frankfurter.

title: ham-cheese delight
directions: Cook finely chopped onion in butter until tender.
Add finely chopped ham, slightly beaten eggs, shredded sharp cheese, fine cracker crumbs, milk and dash of pepper.
Mix well.
Turn into 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Serves 6.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Stir well. Chill.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Line cookie sheets with waxed paper.
In heavy saucepan over low heat, melt butterscotch and chocolate chips until smooth; stir frequently.
Stir in peanuts.
Drop mixture by rounded teaspoons onto prepared cookie sheets.
Chill until set.
Makes 48 pieces.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Combine soy sauce, sherry, cornstarch, garlic and 1/4 cup water; set aside.
In wok or skillet, stir-fry chicken in hot oil 2 minutes.
Add vegetables.
Stir-fry 4 minutes.
Add soy sauce mixture.
Cook and stir until slightly thickened.

title: nut roll
directions: Mix marshmallows with milk.
Heat to melt marshmallows and add remaining mixture.
Make rolls and roll in graham cracker crumbs. Refrigerate.
Makes 8 to 10 small nut rolls.

title: smoked fish & cheese dip
directions: Blend all ingredients & chill for several hours.
Garnish with pimento if desired.

title: texas-mex chicken bites
directions: In a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch microwave-safe baking dish, place poultry.
Cover with microwave-safe plastic wrap.
Turn back one corner to vent.
Cook on 100% power (High) for 3 minutes.
Turn poultry pieces over.
Rearrange by moving the outside pieces to the center of the dish.
Cook, covered, on High for 3 to 4 minutes more or until poultry is tender and no longer pink.
In a plastic bag, combine cornmeal, chili powder, paprika, red pepper and salt. Cut cooked poultry into 1-inch pieces.
Put pieces into the bag. Close bag and shake to coat poultry.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach and drain well.
Combine with rest of ingredients.
Form into balls.
(If too soft, refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours.)
Place on cookie sheet and freeze.
Place frozen spinach balls in a plastic bag and store until needed.
Bake, frozen at 350°, for about 15 minutes or until firm.

title: praline strips
directions: Put a single layer of crackers on a large cookie sheet.
Heat margarine and sugar to a boil.
Turn heat down and boil 2 minutes. Remove from heat; stir in nuts.
Pour mixture over crackers evenly.
Place in a 400° oven for 5 minutes.
Cut in squares when cool.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Add flour, soda, milk, vinegar, vanilla and food coloring.
Beat well.
Pour into greased pans to bake.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes (in layers or oblong pan).

title: cheesy meat loaf
directions: Mix hamburg, onion, eggs and bread crumbs together.
Split mixture in half.
Press half into pan.
Spread cheese evenly over center of mixture.
Mold the rest of the hamburger mix over the top, sealing the edges together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apache cheese bread(makes approximately 10 generous appetizer servings)
directions: Cut and reserve top of bread.
Scoop out inside of bread, leaving about a 1-inch crust all the way around.
Save bread for breadcrumbs to be used later.
Combine all the other ingredients; mix well.
Fill bread with this mixture and replace the top.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix all ingredients, except ginger ale.
Add ginger ale to punch mixture when ready to serve.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Add milk all at once.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 minute more.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Place potatoes in large bowl; gently stir in cheese sauce.
Transfer to a greased 2 1/2-quart dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: okra creole(diabetic - vegetable)
directions: Heat oil in saucepan.
Saute okra, celery, green pepper and onion.
Stir in chopped tomatoes.
Cover and simmer 1 hour. Yields four 1/2-cup servings.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Beat egg and milk; add oil.
Pour in dry ingredients and stir until flour is moistened.
Batter will be lumpy.
Fold in berries.
Fill greased or paper-lined muffin cups about 3/4 full. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: ground beef soup
directions: In a large frying pan, cook ground beef.
Add onion and cabbage and cook until tender. Put ground beef mixture into large pot and add tomato juice, frozen vegetables, water, salt, pepper, parsley and bay leaf.
Bring to a boil and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Bring soup to a boil again.
Add noodles and simmer until noodles are done.
You may add more water if you like it that way.

title: pocatello potatoes
directions: Cool potatoes with skins on.
Dice potatoes.
Cube cheese and sprinkle on top.
Cook onions slightly in butter.
Add to potatoes with bread cubes.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Toss.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake in 350° oven until cheese melts.

title: cream cheese pecan ball
directions: Cream all together.
Refrigerate until firm (several hours). Roll into a ball, then roll in 3/4 c. chopped/crushed pecans. Serve with chocolate graham crackers or chocolate wafers.

title: italian rice
directions: Heat fat in a 10-inch skillet; add rice, ground beef and onion.
Cook, stirring frequently, until meat, rice and onion are soft.
Add green pepper and celery and cook slowly for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until rice is tender.
Stir occasionally.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Crush vanilla wafers.
Mix all ingredients together.
Mold in a loaf shape pan.
Refrigerate.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and baking powder.
Mix well until blended.
Add nuts and raisins; mix well. Pour into 2 well-greased 9 x 5 x 2-inch bread loaf pans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: cheese grits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bring water to boil in medium saucepan.
Add salt and grits; return to boil.
Reduce to slow boil and cook for 20 minutes.
Set aside 2/3 cup cheese.
Add rest of cheese, butter and eggs to the cooked grits and mix well.
Pour into buttered casserole dish and top with the remaining 2/3 cup cheese.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: chocolate bread pudding
directions: Scald the milk with the chocolate and butter in it.
Pour over the bread crumbs.
Cool a little.
Then add the egg, sugar and vanilla mixture.
Pour into a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until silver knife inserted comes out clean.
Serve warm with or without hard sauce or cream.

title: 5 minute fudge
directions: Cream butter, evaporated milk, salt and sugar over medium heat.
Cook for 4 to 5 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Start timing when mixture starts to bubble around edge of pan.
Remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallows, chocolate pieces, vanilla and nuts. Stir vigorously for 1 minute or until blended.
Pour into an 8-inch square buttered pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: texas hot
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Cover and chill until ready to serve.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar in a bowl; cut in lard.
Beat egg until fluffy.
Mix the egg, water and vinegar together.
Add to the dry ingredients.
Gather dough together. Roll.
Yields enough dough for 6 crusts.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, put 1 layer of graham crackers.
Mix 2 boxes of vanilla pudding with 3 cups of milk.
Blend in 1 container of Cool Whip and spread 1/2 of the mixture over grahams, then layer with grahams again.
Spread pudding over grahams. Layer with 1 more layer of grahams.
Mix chocolate pudding with 1 1/2 cups milk and top over grahams.
Chill 3 to 4 hours or overnight.

title: salmon cakes(quick and easy)
directions: Drain salmon, reserving 2 tablespoons juice.
In a bowl, combine juice with all ingredients except oil.
Mix well.
Evenly divide into 6 balls and form into patties.
In a large skillet, in hot oil, fry patties on each side until golden brown, Drain on paper towels.
Makes 4-6 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Shape into ball and roll in chopped pecans.

title: baked chicken reuben
directions: For more flavor, use low-fat (lite) American cheese.

title: raspberry walnut brownies
directions: Melt chocolate with shortening over warm water.
Cool slightly.
Blend together eggs, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Stir in chocolate mixture, then flour.
Fold in walnuts.
Turn into well-greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: ham pick-ups
directions: Slice rolls horizontally into halves.
Do not separate rolls. Combine margarine, poppy seed, dry mustard, onion and Worcestershire sauce in bowl; mix well.
Spread on cut sides of rolls.
Layer ham and cheese on bottom half of rolls.
Replace top of rolls.

title: polish sausage and potato soup
directions: In a large kettle, melt butter and add kielbasa, onion and celery.
Cook until very tender.
Add remaining ingredients, except potatoes.
Cover and cook for 1 1/2 hours.
Add potatoes, cover and cook 25 minutes longer.
Good with hot French bread.

title: mexican flank steak
directions: Sprinkle flank steaks with garlic powder and pepper.
Spread with tomatoes and sauce.
Roll and tie in shallow pan.
Pour tomato sauce, bouillon and water over meat.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Baste occasionally.

title: crab souffle
directions: Place olive oil, parsley, onion, and garlic in Dutch oven, saute until onion becomes tender.
Pour in plum tomatoes, add oregano, salt and pepper.
Cover and let simmer for one hour, stirring frequently.
Add crabs and let cook for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: will's famous sweet-hot barbecue sauce
directions: In a large 8-quart stockpot, simmer the oil, onion, green pepper and celery until transparent. Add all the other ingredients and cook on low heat for approximately 2 hours. After the sauce has cooked for 2 hours, thicken, if necessary, with 2 tablespoons cornstarch blended with 1/2 cup cold water.
Add to the sauce and cook for another 1/2 hour.

title: ranch potato casserole
directions: Mix everything except cornflakes.
Put cornflakes on top. Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: frozen bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix together and let stand 1/2 hour.
Stir occasionally.
Put in containers and fill to one-inch from top.
Freeze.

title: isabelle's banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and margarine; add eggs, then add milk and vanilla.
Stir well.
Add flour and soda, then add mashed bananas, Next, add nuts if desired.
Bake in 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake 55 minutes at 350°.

title: cordon bleu
directions: Pound chicken flat.
Layer ham and cheese on each chicken piece; roll into logs.
Tuck ends.
Mix eggs and milk together; dip chicken into milk mixture.
Roll in flour, dip in milk again and roll in bread crumbs.
Chicken should now be secured (you may need more flour and bread crumbs).
Fry on medium heat in about 1 inch of oil on all sides until golden brown.
Place on a cookie sheet; bake in oven for about 20 minutes, or until cheese is oozing out of the ends.
Top with white sauce; sprinkle with fresh chopped parsley.
Serve on a platter of wild rice.

title: herbed cheese tortellini
directions: Cook pasta according to package.
Cool.
Chop tomatoes, onion, parsley and basil and mix together.
Make dressing of oil, garlic, vinegar and pepper.
Marinate several hours or overnight.

title: corn salad
directions: In large bowl mix corn, red onion, green pepper and parsley. In small bowl whisk together sour cream and broth; add vinegar. Whisk to blend.
Whisk in mayonnaise.
Beat until light and frothy.
Toss sour cream mixture, salt and pepper with vegetable mixture.
Chill.
When ready to serve, garnish with tomato, bacon and green onion.

title: flowerpot dirt pudding
directions: You will need one 8-inch flowerpot.

title: sherbet(orange and strawberry sherbet)
directions: Mix together and freeze.
May be frozen in ice cube trays. Place about 3 cubes in a dish for dessert.

title: pork chops in gravy
directions: Dip chops in egg mixture and in bread crumbs. Brown chops in oil. Place in a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish. Combine the soups and pour over. Sprinkle each chop with cheese. Cover and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Makes 8 servings.

title: cheddar cheese and spinach quiche
directions: Mix together spinach, cheese, flour, milk and eggs.
Crumble bacon over the top and salt and pepper.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: apple squares
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Stir in egg and add dry ingredients. Add apples and nuts.
Bake in 9-inch pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sizzled salmon with chopped tomatoes
directions: Place salmon in baking dish.
Pour orange juice on fish and marinate 10 minutes.
Combine tomatoes and mint.
Set aside.

title: lobster newburgh
directions: Cut the lobster into 1-inch pieces.
In a large skillet, melt the butter.

Add lobster pieces; saute briefly 2 or 3 minutes. Set aside lobster, then stir in flour, salt, nutmeg and cayenne. In a bowl, beat the egg yolks; blend in light cream. Pour mixture into skillet; gradually stir in lobster, stirring constantly until the sauce thickens slightly.
Add sherry.
Serve bubbling hot over crisp toast.
Garnish with parsley.

title: banana cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 round 8-inch pans or oblong 13 x 9 1/2 x 2.
Beat egg whites until frothy.
Gradually beat in 1/3 cup sugar.
Continue beating until stiff and glossy. Set aside.
Sift remaining sugar, flour, baking powder and baking soda and salt into another bowl.
Add oil, mashed bananas, half the buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat 1 minute on medium speed. Scrape sides of bowl.
Add remaining buttermilk and egg yolks. Beat 1 minute more.
Fold in beaten egg whites.

title: harvest pound cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs together and blend well.
Add baby food, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Blend the flour and nuts.
Bake in Bundt pan for 1 hour at 350° in sprayed pan.

title: spinach pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet and spicy sauce(for ribs on grill)
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.

title: custard bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Add salt and sugar to milk.
Pour over bread.
Beat eggs, vanilla and margarine.
Mix well.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart greased casserole dish.
Place in another dish with hot water 1-inch from the top.
Bake 60 minutes or until knife inserted into center comes out clean.

title: tuna salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Slice and dice onion and celery.
Drain tuna; put all in bowl.
Mix with Miracle Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: fresh apple bundt cake
directions: Mix eggs, corn oil and sugar together.
Sift together flour and cinnamon.
Add these dry ingredients to eggs, oil and sugar. Continue beating until smooth.
Add chopped apples to mixture. Add coconut.
Add vanilla and chopped pecans to mixture (will be thick).

title: peanut logs
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients with your hands. Shape into 2-inch balls.
Melt chocolate chips and wax together on low to medium heat. Roll peanut butter balls in
melted chocolate.
Put in refrigerator on waxed paper and let cool and dry.

title: potato-stuffed tomatoes
directions: Cut thin slice off tops of tomatoes.
Scoop out insides; turn upside down to drain.
Scrub potatoes well; cook in 1 inch boiling, salted water for 35 to 40 minutes, or until tender. Drain; peel.
In a large bowl, beat potatoes, milk, butter and egg white together until smooth.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
With a pastry bag or spoon, fill tomatoes with potato mixture.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until potatoes are golden.
Makes 6 servings.

title: onion casserole
directions: Pour the soup over the onions.
Place in casserole and sprinkle top with grated cheese and cracker crumbs.
Bake in medium oven until hot through and browned slightly on top.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: beef brisket
directions: Sprinkle brisket generously on both sides with garlic salt and seasoned salt.
Put into a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Add onion. Mix barbecue sauce, soy sauce, wine and brown sugar.
Pour over meat.
Cover tightly with foil and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 3 hours. Remove meat from sauce; cool slightly.
Slice across grain into thin slices and arrange on serving platter.
Combine flour and water; add to pan drippings and stir until gravy thickens.
Pour some of the gravy over meat and pass remaining gravy at the table.

title: light southern pecan pie
directions: Cream butter; add brown sugar gradually and cream, mixing well.
Blend in syrup and vanilla thoroughly.
Add eggs and pecans.
Turn into pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Reduce temperature to 350°; bake for 25 minutes longer.

title: cran-pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 1/4 cups hot water.
Add other ingredients.
After it is set add topping.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into a baking dish. Top with grated cheese or bread crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add milk.
Stir in ReaLemon and vanilla.
Make graham crust according to directions on box. Fill crust with cream cheese mixture.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Chill for 3 hours.

title: burger goulash
directions: Brown ground beef.
Arrange in layers the macaroni, ground beef and sauce in a large casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Crush vanilla wafers and set aside.
Melt butter; beat in sugar, well beaten eggs and milk and pour over crushed wafers. Let soak thoroughly.
Stir in nuts and coconut.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in slow oven at 275° for 1 1/2 hours. Dust with powdered sugar or serve plain.

title: no fail fudge(microwave)
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk in large glass bowl.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Puncture several holes in plastic.
Microwave on High 5 to 10 minutes.
Stir and continue cooking on High for 5 to 6 minutes or until mixture forms a soft ball in cold water. Stir in chocolate pieces until melted.
Fold in 3/4 jar of Marshmallow Creme and vanilla.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into 2 or 3 quart buttered pan.
Chill until firm; cut into squares.

title: sweet watermelon pickle
directions: Prepare the watermelon rinds by cutting off the pink part and the hard green outer rind.
Cut into desired shapes and put into alum water (1 tablespoon alum to 1 quart cool water).
You will need 2 to 3 quarts.
Let stand overnight.
Drain and rinse.
Add water to cover and cook until tender, about 30 minutes.
Drain thoroughly.

title: matt's power shake
directions: Take all the ingredients and throw them all together in the blender.

title: herbed cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees.
In a bowl mix flour, baking powder, dill and salt.
With a pastry blender cut in Crisco shortening until mixture looks like coarse meal.
Stir in cheese. Add milk and stir just enough to hold together.
Place on a lightly floured surface and knead lightly.
Roll 3/4 inch thick. Cut with floured biscuit cutter without turning cutter (push straight down) and place on parchment lined cookie sheet.
Bake for 12-15 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: hot cranberry punch
directions: Combine juices, water and brown sugar in a large pan or Dutch oven.
Add spices, tied in a cheesecloth bag.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Reduce to low heat.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.
Yields 3 quarts of punch.

title: cheesy cornbread casserole
directions: Brown and drain ground beef, onion and green pepper.
Mix remaining ingredients until moistened.
Pour 1/2 mixture in greased casserole.
Top with beef.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup Cheddar cheese.
Top with other half of cornbread mixture.
Double recipe for 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: golden ham
directions: Score fat edge of ham.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over ham in shallow baking dish.
Refrigerate overnight or let stand at room temperature 1 hour, spooning marinade over ham several times.
Place ham on grill over slow coals.
Cook 15 minutes on each side, brushing frequently with marinade.
Heat remaining marinade and serve with ham.

title: mardi gras pie
directions: Mix condensed milk and lemon juice together; fold in Cool Whip, then fold in peaches.
Slice bananas and arrange in pie crusts.
Put half of the filling in each crust.
Add half of the blueberry filling to each pie; spread even and chill 2 to 3 hours. Makes 2 pies.

title: black bean and vegetable soup
directions: In large saucepan or Dutch oven, cook onion in oil until tender.
Add tomatoes, picante sauce and seasonings.
Stir in beans, peppers, and squash; cover and simmer until vegetables are tender, about 15 minutes.
Makes about 8 (1 cup) servings.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Mix milk,
pineapple,
cranberries and pecans together. Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Saute chicken pieces in butter until golden.
Remove from heat.
Combine in same skillet soup, onion flakes, parsley, salt, thyme and water.
Bring to boil.
Pour rice into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Pour all but 1/2 of soup mixture over rice.
Top with chicken, then remaining soup mixture.
Cover and bake 30 minutes.

title: saucepan peanut butter crunchies
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa in large saucepan.
Add butter and milk and boil 2 minutes.
While stirring, remove from heat.
Add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.
Cool until set.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: skillet meal
directions: Heat diced bacon, ground beef and onion in skillet over high heat.
Reduce heat until meat is slightly browned.
Add remaining ingredients; when steaming, cool over heat for 35 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cream pie and variations(makes 9-inch pie)
directions: Mix flour or cornstarch with the sugar and salt.
Blend well. Put in saucepan.
Add hot milk very gradually, stirring constantly to avoid lumps.
Place on medium heat and cook while stirring until it boils and thickens.
Add a small amount to the egg yolks, then add the yolks to the hot mixture.
Replace on fire and cook until thick and smooth.
Add butter and vanilla.
Stir well.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Pour into shell.
Cover with meringue. Beat 3 egg whites until frothy.
Add 6 tablespoons of sugar very gradually while beating hard.
Should be stiff peaks but not dry. Spread on top of pie.
Seal to crust.
Make some peaks with back of spoon.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes until golden.

title: bride and groom punch
directions: Combine the frozen lemonade with water and the orange juice with water and mix these well. Add pineapple juice and keep well chilled.

title: pickled onion rings
directions: Combine all ingredients except onions in a large saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Drop in onion slices and turn off heat.
Let cool; then refrigerate.

title: easy microwave fudge(makes about 2 pounds)
directions: Place all ingredients, except nuts, in a large bowl. Microwave at Medium (50%) until chocolate chips are melted, 3 to 5 minutes, stirring once or twice during cooking.
Stir in nuts. Pour into well-greased square baking dish, 8 x 8-inches. Refrigerate until set.

title: sausage cacciatore
directions: Cut sausage into 1/2-inch pieces.
Crush garlic. Dice onion. Slice zucchini, mushrooms and peppers.
Cook spaghetti according to package directions.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and add remaining ingredients.
Drop spoon size balls onto cookie sheet.
Smash with fork.
Bake at 350° for about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Add thawed langostinos to crushed crackers, then add scallops (if large, cut into pieces). Add minced clams, the juice and melted butter. Combine all ingredients. Add a little warm water to make moist. Should be moist like stuffing. Bake, uncovered, in an 8-inch baking dish for 30 minutes at 350°. Cover the last 20 minutes. Serves 8.

title: raisin cake
directions: Stew raisins in 2 cups water for 15 minutes.
Add Crisco, sugar, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg, salt and soda in 1 cup cold water.
Mix in flour.
Put in a pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 3/4 hours.

title: walnut apple dessert
directions: Place apples in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with 1/4 cup brown sugar and cinnamon. In a mixing bowl, cream butter and remaining brown sugar. Add eggs. Stir in flour and 1/2 cup walnuts. Spread over apples. Sprinkle with remaining walnuts. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until the apples are tender. Serve warm with ice cream, if desired. Yield: 12 to 16 servings.

title: frosted treats
directions: Melt margarine in 3-quart saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows; stir until melted and well blended.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Rice Krispies until well coated.
Press into 9-inch square pan.
Cool.
Frost with topping.
Cut into squares.

title: secret kiss cookies
directions: Cream together the egg, butter, sugar and vanilla.
Stir in the flour.
Chill overnight.
Shape dough around Kisses.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and roll in powdered sugar.

title: mimi's carrot cake
directions: Mix and beat well sugar, oil and eggs.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add carrots and nuts and mix well.
Bake in greased and floured 8-inch pans (2 thick layers or 3 thinner layers) or a 13 x 9-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
(It only takes 3 to 4 good sized carrots to make 3 cups!)

title: chicken breast
directions: Pound chicken breast with wooden mallet to approximately 1/4-inch thick.
Place slice of meat and cheese on each.
Tuck in sides and roll up as for jelly roll.
Skewer or tie securely. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Brown in butter.
Remove from skillet.
Place in shallow pan.
Combine soup with wine and mushrooms.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: brenda's carrot cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into a 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in a 350° oven.

title: nanny's blue ribbon brownies
directions: Combine chocolate morsels and butter in a glass bowl. Microwave on High 2 minutes, stirring once.
Stir in condensed milk and rest of ingredients.
Spoon into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Yields about 3 dozen.

title: beef teriyaki
directions: Combine all ingredients but the steaks and mix well.
Pour over steak strips.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator.

title: shortbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll out and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion.
Combine soup and tomatoes in a saucepan.
Heat, stirring often.
Layer in baking dish the meat, tortillas (broken or cut in pieces), Ranch Style beans and cheese. Repeat the layers.
Top with soup and tomatoes mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: minute fudge frosting
directions: Bring to a boil, stirring.
Boil gently 1 minute.
Beat until lukewarm.
Add vanilla; beat and spread.
Covers top of 2 layers. If more frosting is desired, double recipe and cook 4 minutes.

title: mexican caviar
directions: Mix all ingredients and let sit in refrigerator overnight. Serve with chips, crackers or taco salad.
The longer it sits, the better.

title: old fashion peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt together.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, on medium speed, mix margarine and peanut butter until smooth.
Beat in sugar, then add eggs and vanilla. Add flour mixture and beat on medium speed until well blended. Refrigerate until chilled.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on pan and bake for 12 minutes at 350°.

title: 5 hour stew
directions: Put ingredients in a casserole with a tight fitting lid.
Mix soup and water together; pour over.
Cover and put in a 275° oven for 5 hours.

title: vegetable rice ring
directions: Combine cooked rice and Italian salad dressing; cover and chill several hours or overnight.
Add mayonnaise to undrained rice mixture and stir until combined.
Fold in radishes, cucumber, chopped tomato, green pepper, celery and green onion.
Press into 5 1/2 cup ring mold.
Cover, refrigerate at least 2 to 3 hours.

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: Beat eggs with the 1/4 teaspoon salt.
In a wok, heat 1 tablespoon of the oil over medium heat.
Add green onion and stir-fry for about 30 seconds.
Add eggs and stir and cook until soft curds form; remove from pan and set aside.
Add 1 tablespoon of oil in pan.
Add shrimp, peas and carrots.
Stir-fry for 2 minutes to heat through; remove from pan and set aside.
Heat the remaining 2 tablespoons oil in pan.
Add rice and stir-fry for 2 minutes to heat through.
Stir in soy and shrimp mixture.
Add eggs and fold in until they are in small pieces.
Season with salt.
Makes 4 or 5 servings.

title: colonial pecan carrot cake with orange glaze
directions: Combine oil and sugar; mix well.
Sift together remaining dry ingredients.
Sift 1/2 of dry ingredients into the sugar mixture; blend well.
Then add the remaining dry ingredients alternately with eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add carrots and mix well, then mix in pecans.
Pour into lightly oiled 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in slow oven (325°) for about 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool with pan upright.
Frost with Orange Glaze.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli as directed and put in greased casserole. Place chicken on top.
Combine other ingredients in bowl.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: california pesto pizza
directions: Drain off olive oil from pesto sauce so that only the paste remains.
Spread sauce over pizza shell.
Cover pizza with cheeses.
Top with onion and bell pepper.
Bake at 375° for approximately 15 to 20 minutes until cheese starts to brown.

title: fruit delight
directions: Slice bananas into a shallow bowl; sprinkle with small amount lemon juice.
Drain pineapple and oranges; mix juices with pudding.
Add all fruit to pie filling, then stir in pudding mixture and nuts.
Keeps well in the refrigerator for several days.

title: almost champagne
directions: In a large pitcher or carafe, combine ingredients.
Pour over ice cubes in chilled wine or champagne glasses.
Serve immediately. Makes 16 (5 ounce) servings.

title: crunchy vegetable salad
directions: Combine vegetables in a large mixing bowl.
Pour salad dressing over and toss evenly.
Refrigerate until serving time. Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: hot chicken supreme
directions: Combine all ingredients, except grated cheese and crushed potato chips.
Toss together.
Put into a flat 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with the grated Cheddar cheese and crushed potato chips.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix pie mix and milk; let it start to thicken, then add coconut and Cool Whip.
Fold in and put a layer of Cool Whip on top, sprinkled with coconut.
Chill 2 hours.
Slice and serve.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Mix popcorn, gumdrops and peanuts in large paper bag or bowl. Melt oil, margarine and marshmallows in a large roaster pan.
Stir constantly until melted over medium heat.
Stir the popcorn mix into marshmallow mix and instantly pack into angel food cake pan, which has been sprayed with Pam.
Press firmly until full.
Invert immediately onto cake dish.
Work quickly; I use 2 wooden spoons, then when mixture has cooled some, use hands rinsed in cool water. Serves 8 to 10.
Can be mailed, arrives fine!

title: jelly roll
directions: In a small mixer bowl, beat eggs for about 5 minutes.
Pour eggs into large mixer bowl.
Gradually beat in sugar.
On low speed, blend in water and vanilla.
Gradually add flour, baking powder and salt, beating until smooth.
Pour batter into 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan with wax paper (greased).
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pineapple salad mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup of boiling water.
Let stand for a few minutes until cool.
Mix in sour cream, nuts and pineapple (juice and all).
Pour into mold that has been greased with mayo. Refrigerate for a few hours.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients with electric mixer and chill overnight or at least 1 hour.
Serve with fruit chunks.

title: old fashion rice pudding
directions: Combine milk, rice, pudding mix, raisins and egg in saucepan. Stir over medium heat until mixture just comes to boil.
Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Pour into dessert dishes and sprinkle with cinnamon or nutmeg.
Makes 10 servings.

title: blueberry cream pie(9-inch pie)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine sour cream, 2 tablespoons flour, sugar, vanilla, salt and beaten egg; beat 5 minutes on medium mixer speed or until smooth.
Fold in blueberries.
Pour filling into pastry shell.
Bake in 400° oven for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven. Combine 3 tablespoons flour, butter and chopped nuts, stirring well.
Sprinkle nut mixture over top of pie.
Return pie to oven and bake 10 more minutes.
