Chill before serving.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Mix flour with 1 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Coat chicken with flour mixture.
Heat oil and cook chicken over medium heat until brown, 15 minutes.
Drain.
Mix tomatoes, tomato sauce, mushrooms, water, onion, garlic, 1 teaspoon salt, oregano, 1/4 teaspoon pepper and bay leaf.
Break up tomatoes; pour over chicken.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 30 minutes; serve with spaghetti.

title: quesadillas
directions: Drain grease from skillet after frying bacon.
Divide cheese, green onions and bacon among the 8 tortillas, putting cheese on one half of tortilla topped by onion and bacon.
Fold tortilla over and fry in skillet until tortilla begins to brown.
Turn and fry other side (like
a grilled cheese sandwich).

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook garlic in 2 tablespoons oil until tender.
Add tomatoes, onion, green chiles, garlic salt, oregano and 1/2 cup water.
Cook over low heat until thickened.
In a separate bowl, combine chicken, cheese and sour cream.
Heat 1/3 cup oil.
Dip tortillas in oil just until they are limp.
Fill with chicken mixture and roll up.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with tomato mixture.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: knudson c. cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, or until done.

title: shrimp squares
directions: Combine the bread crumbs, 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese and melted butter in a bowl and mix well. Press the mixture evenly over the bottom of 4 greased 7 x 11-inch baking pans. Layer the Swiss cheese, scallions and shrimp over the crumb mixture and pat firmly. Beat the eggs in a large bowl. Add the cornstarch and beat until blended. Add the milk and beat until well mixed. Add the nutmeg and cayenne. Pour over the layers. Sprinkle with the remaining 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Reduce the oven temperature to 350°. Bake for 15 minutes longer. Cool for 20 minutes or longer. Cut the baked layer in each pan into 24 squares. Yield: 96 servings.

title: quick pineapple cake
directions: In 9-inch deep pan, melt buttermilk, flour, sugar, milk and vanilla.
Beat until blended.
Drain pineapple (save juice).
Pour flour mixture in butter.
Spread coconut, then spread pineapple. Do not stir.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until springs back when touched.
Pour pineapple juice over while hot.
Let cool; cut into squares. Serve with whipped cream.

title: lemon drop cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan at 350° for 40 minutes.
As soon as cake is removed from oven, prick with a fork all over surface, and pour the topping over the cake immediately.

title: easy coconut custard pie
directions: Mix together well the sugar, flour, eggs, margarine, milk, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until crust is brown and custard is firm.

title: over stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until tender; remove from oven and cut in half the long way.
Cool.
Saute bacon until almost done.
Add onion, celery, and mushrooms; saute until browned.
Scoop potatoes out of shell.
Put shells aside for later.
Mix potatoes, bacon mixture, and cheese with hand masher.
Refill potato shells with mixture. Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes or until browned.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in half and scoop out potato, leaving skin.
Put all the potato in a bowl and mash.
Add milk, butter, salt and pepper.
You can add sour cream.
Scoop the potato into the potato skins.
Add shredded cheese, Bac*Os, chives, etc.
Put on microwave-safe dish and heat until cheese melts.

title: cheese spread
directions: Grind all ingredients and mix with enough mayonnaise to make a spread.

title: mama's 7-up salad
directions: Soften cream cheese; set aside. Empty contents of Jell-O and sugar. Add 1 cup hot water; stir until dissolved. Add cream cheese; mix well. Add remaining ingredients except 7-Up.
Mix well. Pour into a 5 x 11 baking dish. Pour cold 7-Up over mixture. Chill.

title: caramel cheese(prim ost)
directions: Cook buttermilk in heavy-bottomed saucepan until it begins to curdle.
Add flour; stir until thickened.
Add sugar, stirring frequently, until it turns nice and brown.
You may want it sweeter; if so, add sugar.

title: mom's steak and rice
directions: Stir
flour into strips of meat.
Add soy sauce and let set for 1/2 hour.
Saute onions and bell peppers in 1/4 stick margarine.
Brown
steak
in 1/4 stick margarine; stir to keep from
burning.
Add
peppers,
onions,
salt and pepper.
Cook rice
in
water.
When done, stir rice into meat mixture.
Add more soy sauce to desired taste.

title: cheese dip
directions: Cook bacon and onions together. Cook hamburger meat in bacon and onion drippings. In a crock-pot, chop up Velveeta cheese. Add bacon, onions and hamburger. Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and black pepper. Cook until cheese is melted or ingredients are
thick as dip.

title: it's better than potato salad
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Chill.
Add mayonnaise or salad dressing, celery, onion, mustard and salt. Mix well. Chill.
Stir in eggs, radishes and cucumber before serving.

title: old settlers' beans
directions: Brown and drain ground beef, bacon and onion.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spinach fillo appetizer(triopetes)
directions: Mix ingredients, except fillo leaves.
Cut fillo leaves into triangles.
Put teaspoon of filling into each appetizer.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: old fashioned crackling bread
directions: Mix cracklings with dry ingredients.
Add egg and buttermilk. Beat until combined.
Pour into a hot greased skillet.
Bake in a 450° oven for 25 minutes or until light brown.
Serve hot.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix and roll into a ball.
Roll ball in another 1/2 cup of chopped nuts to coat.
Chill and serve.
Serves 6.

title: daddy's favorite sloppy joes(yield: 4 big or 6 small sloppy joes)
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix well with hand; roll in small balls and chill.

title: fried deer meat
directions: Tenderize meat by berating with back of a butcher knife or use a meat tenderizer.
Dip meat in flour, salt and pepper.
Melt Crisco in skillet.
Let get hot on medium heat.
Put meat in skillet; cook until golden brown.
Cook slow or the meat may be tough.
You can soak the deer meat overnight in refrigerator in saltwater to take away some of the strong taste; rinse well.

title: banana brownies
directions: Puree bananas in blender; should be 1 1/2 cups.
In bowl, beat sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla, then bananas.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to banana mixture and beat until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool on rack 10 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Put layer of rice on bottom of casserole dish.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pasta saladnederland, texas
directions: Cook package of spaghetti and drain.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Prepare potatoes.
Mix remaining ingredients to make a baste. Arrange potato wedges, peel side down, in 2-inch shallow baking pan.
Baste with mixture.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 45 minutes until golden brown and tender.
Baste occasionally with oil mixture.
Serves 8.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water, then cool.
Mix all ingredients together.
Mold and let set until firm.

title: mexican salad
directions: Toss the lettuce, tomatoes, onion and shredded cheese together.
Brown the beef.
Add the drained kidney beans and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer meat mixture about 10 minutes.
To salad mixture, add the broken taco chips and hot meat mixture. Toss with the French dressing.
Serves 4 generously.

title: grandma's homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and sugar well.
Add evaporated milk, vanilla and salt.
Beat well.
Pour mixture into a 4-quart freezer.
Add whole milk to fill line of freezer.
Ice cream consistency is better if using a hand-crank freezer.

title: sin-amon chocolate cake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 13 x 9-inch rectangular cake pan with a nonfat cooking spray.
In saucepan, simmer pineapple juice until it is reduced in volume to 1/2 cup.

title: best blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Mix remaining ingredients just until blended.
Do not beat.
Fold in blueberries.
Fill 12 greased muffin cups.
Sprinkle with sugar. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add other ingredients and bake at 325°.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Slice real thin and place in jar.
Cover with cold brine.

title: crawfish or shrimp etouffee
directions: Melt butter in a large heavy pot (iron preferred).
Saute onions, garlic, green pepper and celery until onions are clear. Stir in all ingredients except crawfish (or shrimp).
Simmer 30 minutes on low heat.
Stir occasionally.
Add crawfish (or shrimp) tails; simmer 25 minutes over medium heat.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: pound cake
directions: Blend margarine, butter and Crisco together.
Add sugar; continue to blend.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add alternately the flour, to which salt and baking powder have been added, and milk with vanilla.
Pour into 2 well-greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: pretzel dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add strawberries.
Stir well until thawed.
Let mixture jell slightly and pour over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate.

title: sesame munchies
directions: Toast nuts and seed at 300° to 350° for 15 minutes.
Combine all ingredients except nuts in frypan.
Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and immediately stir in nuts and seed, mixing thoroughly.
Turn into buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
With large, buttered spoon, press candy firmly and evenly over bottom of dish.
Cool at room temperature for approximately 15 minutes, then lift out with spatula.
Cut candy into 1 x 2-inch pieces.
Wrap after at least 2 hours.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil together.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing well.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add to first mixture. Add the rest of the ingredients, mixing well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes in a Bundt pan or tube pan.
Cool, then cover with icing.

title: chutney spread for date nut bread
directions: Pulse ingredients for the cheese spread in food processor until mixture is combined. Transfer spread to a small serving dish and garnish with shaved crystalized ginger. Serve with date nut bread.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownies per package directions.
Cool.
Punch holes in brownies with fork.
Pour Kahlua over brownies and set pan aside. Make chocolate mousse per package directions.
Break candy bars and place in food processor to make small pieces/crumbles.
Remove brownies from pan and break up into crumbly pieces.
Place 1/2 of these pieces into bottom of large deep dish bowl/dish.
Cover brownies with 1/2 of mousse, then 1/2 of candy, then 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Repeat layers, ending with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chocolate sprinkles or an extra crumbled candy bar.
Refrigerate until serving.

title: black forrest cheesecake
directions: Butter 9-inch pan.
Finely crush cookies.
Cut in butter until mixture is well blended.
Press crumbs into bottom of pan and up sides to 3/4-inch of top.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat whipping cream and chocolate over low heat until melted.
Cool 10 minutes.
Beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Beat in eggs.
Add chocolate and vanilla.
Stir well. Pour into crust.
Bake 1 1/4 hours.
Cool completely.
Serve with cherry pie filling and whipped cream.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook beef, onion and pepper in margarine until lightly browned.
Add soups and water and simmer about 5 minutes.
Blend with 1/2 cup cheese and cooked spaghetti in 3-quart casserole. Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Enjoy!

title: mini cheese-cakes
directions: Line muffin tin with foil liners.
Place one vanilla wafer on each liner.
Mix cream cheese, vanilla and sugar on medium speed until well-blended.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Pour over wafers, filling 3/4 full.

title: glazed walnuts
directions: Mix sour cream and sugar.
Heat to 223°, stirring constantly. Add vanilla and nuts.
Stir rapidly until mixture has coated nuts. Spread on foil.
Cool and store in airtight containers.

title: hollandaise sauce
directions: In double boiler over hot water, melt butter.
Mix in lemon juice and egg yolks.
Cook slowly, beating with whisk constantly. Add boiling water a drop at a time.
Remove from heat.
Keep warm to serve.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Combine ingredients and place in baking dish.
Top with slices of cheese.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Remove cover and finish baking until done.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix and pour into 2 ready made pie shells.
Chill and serve.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Mix soup, rice and water in bottom of casserole.
Season pork chops and place on top of rice.
Cover and cook at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Prepare stuffing following directions on box. Mix cream of chicken and cream of mushroom soups using 1/2 can of water.

title: baked greek chicken
directions: Wash and drain chicken.
Place in large mixing bowl.
In small mixing bowl, mix next 8 ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Toss and refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: pecan puff balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together except powdered sugar.
Roll into balls the size of hickory nuts.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes at most.
While hot, roll in powdered sugar.
Cool.
Roll again in powdered sugar.

title: ranch meat loaf(microwaved)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium mixing bowl; mix well. Pat into 8 x 4-inch glass loaf dish.
Microwave on Roast for 25 to 30 minutes or until well done in the center.
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes before serving.
Drizzle with catsup and garnish with parsley.

title: derick's favorite cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Prepare a large spring-form pan by generously buttering and sprinkling with crushed graham cracker crumbs.
Blend cream cheese and sugar together in large mixing bowl, beating until well blended.
Add eggs; beat until smooth. Add remaining ingredients; blend until smooth.
Pour into pan and place in pan of water.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or longer. Cake should be firm and lightly browned around the edges and soft and light in color in center.
Remove from oven; leave in spring-form pan overnight in refrigerator.
Garnish with strawberries although it is delicious all by itself.
May be frozen for later use.

title: pineapple cheese cake
directions: Boil
pineapple, sugar and water for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir
in
jello
and
cool
in refrigerator until mixture begins to thicken.
Fold in cheese and whipped cream. Chill until set.
Serves 9.

title: white trash
directions: Mix all ingredients except chocolate or almond bark as package directs; pour over mixture, mixing and coating well (using your hands is the best method). Put mixture on waxed paper to dry. Break into chunks; store in airtight containers. Saves well for several weeks.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as label directs; drain well and set aside. Saute onion in margarine.
Add cream of mushroom soup, drained mushroom bits, slivered almonds, garlic flavored cheese and the pimento.
After cheese melts, add broccoli and mix well.
Place in buttered casserole dish; sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° until lightly browned.

title: bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350° or 375°.
Cooking time 1/2 hour to 1 hour.
Time could vary.

title: corn puff
directions: Melt margarine in casserole.
Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Pour over margarine in casserole; do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese over top when done.

title: riz biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in milk.
Sift flour and sugar; cut in shortening.
Mix and knead.
Roll out into 1/4-inch thickness. Cut and brush with butter.
Place one on top of the other and let rise for about 1 hour or until doubled in size.
Bake at 395° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: 1 hour rolls
directions: Heat milk.
Add butter, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm and add yeast.
Mix and add 1/2 sifter of flour.
Knead well.
Let rise 15 minutes.
Roll and cut.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Bake in hot oven for 20 minutes.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix in large mixing bowl the first 5 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish and add topping.

title: no-bake cookie balls
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and milk in pan; boil for 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients and roll into balls.
Yields 4 dozen.
Store at room temperature.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs and spices.
Add margarine to hot milk, then stir into potato mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350 degrees for 50-60 minutes or until knife inserted into center comes out clean.

title: friendship
directions: Cook until you are so hungry anything would taste good.
Eat to your heart's content.

title: fruit pizza
directions: For crust, melt butter and mix with crumbs and 3 1/2 tablespoons sugar.
Press onto a pizza pan and put into freezer for 45 minutes.
For glaze, boil orange juice, water, cornstarch and 1/2 cup sugar until thick and let cool.
Beat cream cheese and Cool Whip together and spread on crust.

Place strawberries, bananas, blueberries, peaches, kiwi fruit, grapes, pineapple, raspberries, oranges or whatever you would like on mixture. Spread glaze on top of fruit with pastry brush until all fruit is covered completely.
Cover and refrigerate.
Slice like a pizza.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix the first six ingredients.
Add oil and buttermilk.
Mix and put in cupcake papers.
Bake at 375° for 17 to 20 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cinnamon. Add eggs to oil; mix well and add to dry ingredients. Add rest of ingredients. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes in greased and floured loaf pans. Cool 30 minutes and cover with foil.

title: kelly's salad
directions: Dissolve the jello in the boiling water.
When it is partially set, stir in the remaining ingredients.
Pour into shallow dish or pan to set.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except noodles.
Pile lightly into greased, individual baking dishes or 1 1/2-quart casserole.
If desired, cover and store in refrigerator for several hours or overnight.
Remove from refrigerator.
Sprinkle top with chow mein noodles.
Bake, uncovered, in moderate oven (350°) for 25 to 30 minutes or until heated through.
Garnish with parsley, rice, olives and pimiento.
Serves 6.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Flatten chicken breasts with meat mallet.
Dip into egg and coat with mixture of bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Heat oil in skillet and brown chicken on both sides.
Pour spaghetti sauce into an 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Place chicken on top of sauce, then sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese and then Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 400° until cheese is melted and lightly browned.

title: sesame yogurt sauce
directions: In a medium-size skillet, saute the onion and bell pepper in oil over medium-high heat for 5 to 7 minutes or until soft.
In a small dry skillet, saute the sesame seed until they are golden. Add the garlic and green chili peppers to the onion mixture and cook several minutes more, stirring constantly.
Add the sesame seed and stir.
Remove from heat and stir in the yogurt, salt substitute and cumin.
Serve hot over cooked grains, pasta or vegetables.

title: pineapple cream cheese ball
directions: Cream together chopped onion, green pepper, cream cheese and pineapple.
Form into a ball.
Roll in chopped pecans to coat. Chill and serve with snack crackers.

title: easy coffee breakfast cake
directions: Put filling in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry mix on top. Melt margarine and pour over cake mix.
Put nuts on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Good with coffee or just any time.

title: salmon forcemeat
directions: Cook milk and breadcrumbs for 10 minutes.
Add salmon, chopped and run through sieve.
Add cream, egg, butter, salt and pepper.

title: apple brownies
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except apples and nuts.
After mixing, fold in apples and nuts.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: apple pie
directions: Prepare pastry for two crust pie.
Fill bottom shell with sliced apples.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over apples. Cover with top crust and bake in 425° oven for 45 minutes or until crust is brown and apples are tender.
Remove from oven.

title: mud pie
directions: 1st Layer:
Combine in bowl the flour, 1/2 cup chopped nuts and melted butter.
Pat into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: chili con queso
directions: Melt Velveeta over low heat and brown meat separately.
Drain meat; add to cheese and add remaining ingredients.
Serve warm with Doritos.

title: becky's pecan pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add margarine.
Spread nuts in bottom of deep-dish pie shell.
Add mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: layered taco dip
directions: In a large skillet, brown beef; pour off fat.
Add chiles and bouillon; cook and stir until bouillon dissolves.
Cool.
Stir in refried beans.
In small bowl, combine sour cream and taco seasoning; set aside.
In 7 or 8-inch spring-form pan or on a large plate, spread beef mixture.
Top with sour cream mixture and guacamole.
Cover; chill several hours.
Just before serving, remove side of spring-form pan.
Garnish with cheese, tomatoes, green onions and olives.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: apple butter
directions: Wash, core and quarter apples.

Cover and cook apples and cider in a large crock-pot on low setting for 8 to 10 hours (or high setting for 2 to 3 hours) until apples are very tender. Process apples and liquid through food mill to remove apple peel. Measure and return processed apples to crock-pot.
For each pint of processed apples, add 1 cup of sugar, 1 teaspoon of cinnamon, 1/2 teaspoon of allspice and 1/2 teaspoon ground cloves.
Cook on high setting for 6 to 8 hours.
Stir every 2 hours.
Remove cover after 2 hours to allow fruit to cook down.
Pour hot apple butter into hot, sterilized canning jars.
Seal at once and process in boiling water bath.

title: tabooley - arabic(wheat garden salad)
directions: Soak wheat in water for 5 minutes.
Squeeze wheat dry by pressing between palms.
Chop onions, parsley, mint leaves, tomatoes and cucumbers nice and fine.
Add lemon juice, oil, wheat and seasoning and mix well.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Beat egg and 1/3 of soup.
Add bread crumbs and soak for 5 minutes.
Add onions, salt and pepper and bread crumbs to meat and mix.
Form approximately 6 patties and place on baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Mix remaining soup and water (I add Worcestershire sauce) and pour over patties.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes more.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Break cake into small pieces in a large baking dish or bowl. Combine cream cheese and sugar in a mixing bowl. Add milk and then Cool Whip. Mix well. Pour over cake pieces. Spread pie filling on top and sprinkle with nuts. Chill and serve.

title: l b j ranch cheese wafers
directions: Add a few drops of water if needed to hold dough together when forming wafers.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Line 2 cookie sheets with foil.
In medium bowl mix egg whites, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Add flour and blend well.
Fold in coconut.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet 1 inch apart.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool on cookie sheet.
Remove and store in tightly covered cookie jar.

title: la gaza
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and pepper; drain.
Add tomato sauce, corn, chili powder and Tabasco sauce.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Prepare noodles according to package; drain.
When both are finished, combine and place in 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Place cheese on top. Place in preheated 350° oven, just to melt cheese.
Serve.

title: creme fraiche
directions: Beat together the 2 ingredients. Leave at room temperature for a few hours or overnight until thickened. Cover and refrigerate until needed. It has many uses such as topping for fruit salad, aspic salads or fresh berries.

title: green rice
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Cook rice in 1 1/2 cups water. Saute onion and bell pepper in oleo.
Add mushroom soup and Cheez Whiz.
Mix all together and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown ground beef; drain and discard pan juices.
Place ground beef in the bottom of casserole.
Save small amount of ground beef for garnish.
Prepare instant mashed potatoes according to the manufacturer's directions.
Top ground beef with potatoes.
Top potatoes with grated cheese. Garnish top with rest of ground beef. Cook in preheated oven at 325° until cheese bubbles

title: nutty noodle clusters
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine chocolate and butterscotch chips. Melt, stirring constantly, over low heat.
Remove from heat and stir in noodles and nuts.
Mix quickly.
Dip by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper and cool.
Makes 24.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt margarine; blend in other ingredients.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: turkish delight
directions: Cook sugar with water and corn syrup in a heavy bottomed saucepan until mixture forms a soft ball or reaches 240° on candy thermometer.
Keep hot.
Soften gelatin in lemon juice.
Dissolve cornstarch in 1/2 cup cold water and pour into hot syrup.
Simmer slowly until very thick; remove from heat and add gelatin and lemon juice.
Stir until gelatin dissolves.
Stir in desired flavoring and nuts.
Sprinkle a thick layer of confectioners sugar in an 8-inch square pan.
Pour in candy and let set in a cool dry place (not refrigerator) for 3 to 4 hours.
Top with a layer of sugar and cut into 1-inch squares.
Dredge lightly in additional sugar and store in airtight container.

title: brownies
directions: Set aside flour and sugar.
Boil and cool the margarine, water and cocoa.
Add flour and sugar.
Add buttermilk and rest of ingredients; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes in jelly roll pan.

title: easy chocolate frosting
directions: Melt butter and cocoa. Add milk and boil for 3 minutes.
Add the powdered sugar slowly with mixer.
If icing gets stiff, add a few drops of water.

title: cheese cake
directions: Bake at 450° for 5 minutes.
Cool, then chill overnight.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Mix milk and pudding until blended.
Fold in whipped topping. Add apples and candy bar pieces and mix well.
Chill until ready to serve.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: raisin puffs
directions: Simmer raisins in water, covered, until all water is absorbed. Allow to cool while preparing batter.
Mix margarine with sugar until fluffy.
Add cinnamon and vanilla.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add carrots and orange rind.
Blend soda and 1/2 cup of the flour; mix with egg mixture.
Add 3 more cups of flour and steamed raisins.
Mix well.
Shape by teaspoonfuls into balls.
Roll in dish of cinnamon sugar.
Bake at 375° on greased cookie sheet for 9 minutes.
Remove from oven before firm for chewy texture.
Makes 72 cookies.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Put rice in bottom of
baking dish.
Lay chicken on top and cover with soup and
water.
Salt
and
pepper
to	taste. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours, covered.
Cook another 1/2 hour, uncovered.

title: creamed cabbage and stuffed frankfurters
directions: Cut cabbage small; cook in pan covered with salted water. Cook until tender; drain (save 1 cup of the liquid).
In frypan, saute onion in oil.
Remove onion from pan.

title: layered taco dip
directions: In large Pyrex dish, layer beans first, then avocado dip.
Mix sour cream with taco seasoning, then layer it and remaining ingredients, ending by spooning salsa over top.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: russian boat dip
directions: Cut bread around, leaving the outer crust, top only to make a cover for the bread.
Scoop out the inside.
Cut inside part into small pieces to use for dip.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into the bread cavity.
This also makes a pretty centerpiece.

title: miss bessie's egg white delights
directions: Mix together brown sugar and vanilla.
Fold into egg whites and beat until stiff.

title: egg souffle
directions: Mix eggs, milk, mustard, salt and bread.
Add sausage and cheese.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: french oven stew
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Mix all ingredients in a heavy 3-quart saucepan (ovenproof).
Cover and bake, stirring 3 times, 3 hours or until meat is tender and sauce is thickened.
Makes 10 servings.

title: snack mix
directions: Mix all ingredients; chill for at least 24 hours or longer.

title: english rock cakes
directions: Mix stiffly and put on greased pan in mounds.
Sprinkle little sugar on each.
Bake at 425°
for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: apple crumble
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients with fork until crumbly.
Butter 8-inch dish.
Slice apples.
Put crumb mixture on top of apples.
Put 1/3 cup of melted butter over top of crumbs and sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients, except butter, broth, tomato paste, Worcestershire sauce and sour cream.
Form 12 meatballs; brown in butter.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Scald milk.
Pour over dried bread that has been seasoned with a little sugar and salt.
Serve in a coffee cup.

title: cheese souffles
directions: Alternate bread and cheese in buttered casserole.
Beat eggs until light and mix with remaining ingredients.
Pour egg mixture over cheese and bread.
Let stand 4 hours in refrigerator or overnight.	Bake
1 hour at 350°.
Sprinkle with bacon bits. Serves 4 to 6.

title: date squares
directions: Pour hot water over dates; let stand.
Cream the shortening and add sugar.
Beat.
Sift the flour with cocoa and add alternately with water from dates and the lemon juice to creamed shortening mixture.
Add dates and nuts.
Pour into greased square pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Break up potatoes in pieces in baking dish.
Mix butter, chicken soup, onions and cheese together and pour over potatoes.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° then sprinkle potato chips and bake 25 minutes more.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: mexican dip
directions: In a large rectangular dish, layer ingredients as listed. Refrigerate for at least four hours.
Serve with tortilla chips or corn chips.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Grease a casserole dish well with butter.
Layer bottom with cracker crumbs.
Add 1 can asparagus, 2 sliced boiled eggs, sprinkle with almonds and spread with thick layer of cracker crumbs.
Lightly salt and pepper.
Repeat second layer same as first.
Mix soup with Pet milk.
Pour over casserole and top with cracker crumbs and a few almonds.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients except for stuffing.
Place in a casserole dish and top with stuffing.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: cinnamon apple dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve with fresh apple slices.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Combine soup (undiluted), cream cheese, mayonnaise, gelatine, salt and pepper in a saucepan over low heat; blend until smooth. Stir in shrimp, celery and onion.
Pour into well-greased mold and chill 4 hours or overnight.
Unmold and serve on lettuce leaves with Ritz crackers and seafood sauce.

title: big meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients in order given and work all up together with a big spoon.
Form into a big loaf or 2 loaves.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cherie's scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel potatoes and slice them.
Put in baking dish.
Stir into saucepan mushroom soup, butter, milk and cheese.
Cover potatoes.
Add salt and pepper.
Bake about 45 minutes.

title: east coast crab appetizers
directions: Melt cheese and butter; add crab meat and mushrooms.
Spoon on quartered muffins.
Place under broiler until slightly brown. Serves 12 to 14.

title: pumpkin streusel squares
directions: In one bowl, combine flour and sugars.
Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Stir in nuts.
Reserve 1 cup of nut mixture.
Press remainder into 12 x 7-inch baking pan, halfway up sides also.
In another bowl, mix remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour into prepared dish.
Top with reserved crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mother's brown sugar cake
directions: Beat up brown sugar, eggs, butter and lard and milk (with soda).
Fold in beaten egg whites last.
Bake until a toothpick comes out clean.
Bake at 350° to 375°.

title: toasted pecans
directions: Place pecans in flat pan and sprinkle with salt, lemon juice and butter. Place pan in 200° oven, stirring nuts often until butter and lemon juice cook well into the nuts and they are toasted, approximately 1 hour.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Put crackers in brown bag.
Pour oil over crackers.
Shake to cover.
Mix dry ingredients together; pour over crackers in bag. Shake to cover.
Store in airtight container (Tupperware works great) for 24 hours before serving.

title: speedy taco bake
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain off fat.
Add taco seasoning, salsa and corn.
Stir together and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle cheese over that.
Mix Bisquick or Recipe Ease, eggs and milk together.
Pour over other mixture and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Deeelish.

title: lane cake ii
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add milk to baking powder and flour.
Then add egg whites to the mixture.
Bake until golden brown.
Make the Lane Filling.

title: roasted potatoes
directions: Quarter the potatoes.
Toss in the melted butter and seasoned salt.

title: spareribs, sauerkraut and potatoes
directions: This is a recipe for a family of four.
Double or triple if needed.
Your choice of how many ribs and potatoes.

title: low-fat applesauce muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt in large mixing bowl.
Mix cereal and milk in another bowl; let stand 3 minutes.
Stir egg, applesauce, sugar and margarine into flour mixture.
Stir just until moistened.
(Batter will be lumpy.) Stir in cranberries or raisins.
Spoon batter into muffin pan sprayed with no stick cooking spray, filling each cup 2/3 full. Bake 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm.
Freeze any leftover muffins.
Makes 12.

title: homemade pimento cheese spread
directions: Soften cheese to room temperature.
Shred and mix together.

title: no eggs, no milk, no butter cake
directions: Boil sugar, water, raisins, shortening, salt and spices together for 3 minutes.
Let cool.
Add flour and baking powder; mix well.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: swedish flat bread
directions: Mix like pie crust.
Break off 1-inch ball of dough and roll on floured board to size 5-inches.
Bake at 400° in middle of oven on cookie sheet for 5 minutes.
I sometimes flip the pieces over and put back in oven for a few minutes.

title: edna's pound cake
directions: Cream
butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and
whipping cream alternating.
Flour first and last. Add flavoring.	Spoon batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Put
in cold oven.
Cook at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or more until tested done.

title: great moist chocolate cake(good with or without icing)
directions: Sift together in a large mixing bowl:
sifted plain flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Add cooking oil, vinegar, vanilla and water.
Mix liquids into sifted dry ingredients. Mix well.
A wire whisk works really well.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix well and heat.
Pour sauce over meatballs in crock-pot and simmer.

title: six week muffins
directions: Combine bran, sugar and flour.
Add eggs, margarine and buttermilk; mix well.
Add nuts and mix again.
Store in covered glass container in refrigerator up to 6 weeks.
Use as desired.
If dough thickens as it sets, add a little water.
Bake in paper-lined or greased muffin tins at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
(Test with toothpick.)

title: berried treasure pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and 2 tablespoons milk until smooth. Spread in bottom of pie crust.
Arrange strawberries on cream cheese mixture.
Prepare whipped topping.
Mix as directed on package.
Prepare pudding with 1 cup milk.
Fold in 1 cup whipped topping.
Spoon into pie crust and chill until set, about 2 hours. Put remaining whipped topping and strawberries on top.

title: food processor pie crust
directions: Insert metal blade into processor.
Add flour, salt and fat. Process with short bursts until consistency of coarse meal.
Pour ice water through feed tube; process.
Stop as soon as dough begins to form.
If necessary, add a bit more water.
Remove; divide in two.
Flatten slightly; wrap in waxed paper.
Refrigerate 4 hours or freeze 1 hour.
On lightly floured cutting board, roll out 1/8 inch thick, allowing 1 inch margin around pan.
Fit into pan gently; do not stretch or pull.
To eliminate sogginess, brush bottom of crust with egg white.
Prick well with fork.

title: holiday punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in water.
Add orange juice, lemonade and whiskey.
Stir until frozen mixture is melted.
Freeze.
When ready to serve, scoop into glass and add 7-Up, Sprite or ginger ale.

title: smoked sausage casserole
directions: Cook pasta until done.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl. Pour into a casserole dish and microwave on High until cheese is melted and ingredients are hot.
(Stir every five minutes during cooking.)

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a tube pan (not the two piece kind).
Place pineapple in bottom of pan. Cover with pie filling, cake mix and then nuts. Cut butter into pieces and place over cake.
Do not mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serve warm or cold by dipping or dumping out with a spoon. Serves 10 to 12.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and celery until browned well. In large kettle, mix tomatoes, juice and beans. Add beef mixture. Simmer on low heat for about 1 hour. Add salt, pepper and bay leaves. Add chili powder to your taste. I cook macaroni on the side or rice to add whatever you desire.

title: sweet bread dough
directions: Mix 4 cups flour, sugar, salt and dry yeast together.
Melt oleo or butter in warm water; cool slightly.
Mix the 6 eggs in large bowl.
Add water and yeast mixture, then add flour mixture. Keep adding flour until dough is no longer sticky.
Make this for Povitica Dough.

title: strawberry gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add berries, stirring occasionally, until thawed.
Stir in pineapple, bananas and pecan halves.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Chill until firm, about 5 to 6 hours.
Top with sour cream, sugar, ginger and salt. Chill well.
Makes 8 servings.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Measure sugar, flour, salt and nutmeg into small bowl and stir to blend well; then stir in milk until well mixed.
Pare peaches, slice thinly.
Measure and turn into pastry-lined pan.
Spread level.
Then pour milk mixture over peaches, pressing slices down into milk with back of spoon.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 425° until nicely brown.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat egg yolks; add 1 cup sugar gradually.
Add milk and cook over hot water until thick and coats spoon, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Whip cream and egg whites with 1/2 cup sugar separately and fold into cooled milk mixture.
Add nutmeg to taste.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix salmon, corn meal and dash of salt.
Shape into patties. Fry in an iron skillet which you have added oil to.
Let the oil get hot before adding patties.
Fry until brown on both sides and drain on paper towels.

title: italian zucchini casserole
directions: Slice zucchini and cook in microwave for 5 minutes, stirring halfway through.
Combine the remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Place half of zucchini in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle on half the cheese, then place the rest of the squash. Pour the milk mixture over all.
Top with remaining cheese. Sprinkle on extra oregano, if desired.
Bake at 370° until set and lightly browned (30 to 45 minutes).

title: marinated mushroom bites
directions: In small bowl, combine mushrooms and green pepper; set aside. In small saucepan, combine remaining ingredients; bring to a boil. Pour over mushroom mixture.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator for several hours or until serving.
Serve kabob-style on wooden skewers.
Makes 8 appetizers.

title: bananas hawaiian
directions: Heat coconut
in
large
skillet until toasted, stir to brown evenly.
Remove to a sheet of foil to cool.
Add butter, sugar, rum
and
cinnamon
to skillet. Heat until bubbly.
Add bananas and
cook until slices are heated through.
Spoon over ice cream and sprinkle with toasted coconut.

title: crawfish vermicelli
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in butter until clear.
Coat crawfish with crawfish fat.
Mix flour with crawfish and coat. Add crawfish to onions and bell pepper.
Add salt and red pepper. Blend all ingredients together and cook, covered, over low heat, no more than 10 minutes, until done.
Let cool slightly before adding sour cream (it will separate if crawfish is too hot).
May be reheated but do not boil.
Serve over vermicelli.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: cheese cake squares
directions: Mix cake mix, melted oleo and egg together.
Dough will be stiff.
Lightly greased a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan and pat mixture in bottom of pan (not too much on the sides).
Mix powdered sugar, eggs and cream cheese.
After mixing add nuts.
Spread on top of dough.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until light brown.

title: never fail pie
directions: Mix pie
in the order of the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
This is put into 2 ungreased 9-inch pie pans (crustless).

title: granma gaye's butterscotch pie(updated)
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Using wire whisk, mix eggs and milk until well blended.
Add to dry ingredients and hot water.
Cook in microwave for 3 minutes on High.
Whisk and return to microwave and cook 2 3/4 to 3 minutes longer, whisking often.
Add butter and vanilla and pour into baked crust and add meringue.

title: italian beef skillet
directions: Trim fat from round steak, then cut meat into 5 serving size pieces.
Spray a cold large skillet with nonstick spray.
Add meat pieces to skillet; brown both sides of each piece.
Remove meat from skillet.
Add mushrooms, onion, green pepper, celery and garlic to skillet.
Cook until vegetables are nearly tender. Then, stir in undrained tomatoes, basil, oregano and red pepper.
Add meat to skillet, spooning vegetable mixture over the meat.
Cover and simmer about 1 1/4 hours or until meat is tender.
Stir occasionally.
Serve over spaghetti or noodles.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: grandmother's chocolate sauce
directions: Cook on low-medium heat until thickens.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix together and bake.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Mix until smooth.
Store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Yields 1 1/4 cups.

title: deer salami
directions: Mix well and form into roll.
Wrap in foil for 24 hours. Remove from foil and roll in cracked black pepper.
Cook on cookie sheet in 180° oven for 3 1/2 hours.

title: super thick eggnog
directions: Beat egg yolk, sugar and salt until thick and lemon colored. Add vanilla and blend in whipping cream.
Fold into egg yolk mixture.
Sprinkle cream of tartar over egg whites.
Beat until stiff.
Gently fold egg white mixture into cream mixture.
Chill well.
Just before serving, fold in cold milk.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and
sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time, and mix well.
Sift
flour
and
baking powder together.
Chop nuts and fruit; mix
with
some of the flour.
Fold flour into butter mixture; add flavorings and mix well.
Fold in nuts and fruit. Bake in
greased
tube pan.
Start in cool oven.
Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: biscuits(made from herman sourdough mix)
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix to form a soft dough; knead as little as possible.
Allow to rise 20 to 30 minutes.
Drop by spoon into an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine; add graham cracker crumbs.
Mix well and line a 9 x 13-inch pan with this mixture.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix ingredients on low speed until blended, then mix on high speed until light lemon color.
Bake in a Bundt pan 35 to 45 minutes.

title: forbes' hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients. Beat until stiff. Wait 1 hour before cooking. Beat again before cooking. Deep-fry.

title: georgia soup mix
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil.
Cook on low heat for 30 minutes.
Pour into Mason quart jars and seal.

title: italian style chicken
directions: Mix cooled chicken with rest of ingredients.
Toss and chill overnight.

title: fried oysters
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a medium bowl.
Dip oysters in egg, then dredge in meal mixture.
Fry oysters in deep, hot oil for 1 1/2 minutes or until golden, turning once.
Drain on paper towel; serve immediately.

title: crunchy broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Combine cauliflowerets, broccoli, water chestnuts and mushrooms in large salad bowl.
Combine mayonnaise, sour cream and dressing in small bowl and mix well.
Pour over vegetables.
Add peas and toss gently to coat.
Chill, covered, until serving time.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken barbecue sauce
directions: Mix oil, lemon or vinegar, water, salt, sugar and Tabasco. Put into a saucepan and heat.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Form sausage into balls about the size of a large marble; flatten into patties.
Brown lightly on both sides.
Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
In greased 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine patties, noodles, green pepper and chopped pimiento.
Heat and stir soup; add crumbled Blue cheese.
Stir until melted.
Pour over noodle mixture; top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: orange pecan salad
directions: Mix sugar and cream cheese together.
Stir in oranges, pineapple and coconut.
Spread in glass dish.
Sprinkle pecans on top.
For best results, chill for 1 to 2 hours.

title: tuna cashew casserole
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Set aside 1/2 cup noodles.
Combine rest of noodles with all other ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle the reserved noodles over the top.
Bake for 40 minutes. Serves 4.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown meat in 2-quart casserole dish.
Add onion and salt and pepper.
Add chopped cabbage and tomato sauce.
Add an additional can of water.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.

title: sunday breakfast
directions: This recipe is for all those husbands who want to help out on Sunday mornings.
Come on you guys!

title: frosted banana bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Spray 9 x 9-inch pan with non-stick cooking spray.
Beat sugar, sour cream, oleo and egg whites in large bowl on low speed 1 minute, scraping bowl occasionally. Beat in bananas and vanilla on low speed 30 seconds.
Beat in flour, salt and baking soda on medium speed 1 minute, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until light brown; cool.
Spread with Frosting.
Cut into 24 bars.

title: moist 'n crispy onion chicken
directions: Put soup mix and bread crumbs in plastic bag.
Brush chicken with mayonnaise.
Put chicken in bag, one piece at a time; shake until coated.
Bake in baking dish at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: "hannah adams" chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lay chicken breasts in buttered (or Pam sprayed) casserole.
Top with Swiss cheese.
Dilute soup with water and pour over chicken.
Add mushrooms, if desired.
Mix stuffing with melted butter and sprinkle on top.
Bake, uncovered, 50 to 60 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend cream cheese and Cheddar.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Shape into ball, wrap in plastic and chill.
May roll in pecans before serving.
Serve with crackers and seafood sauce (ketchup and horseradish).

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Crush whole wheat crackers and spread evenly on top of casserole.
Dot with olive oil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sea breeze
directions: Fill a tall glass with ice, then add rest.

title: hawaiian meatballs
directions: Season meat with salt and ginger; form into 16 small balls. Dip in egg, slightly beaten with 1 teaspoon water.
Dip in flour. Brown all over in hot oil; remove from pan.
Make sauce in same pan.
Drain syrup from pineapple; add water to make 1 cup liquid. Stir into drippings in pan.
Stir in brown sugar, cornstarch, vinegar and soy sauce.
Cook, stirring constantly until sauce thickens.
Arrange meatballs, peppers and pineapple in separate piles in pan.
Stir each gently to coat with sauce.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Serve with buttered noodles.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Combine other ingredients and heat to a boil.
Add carrots and heat through.
Remove mixture from stove and pour into serving bowl.
Chill overnight.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Combine Raisin Bran, flour, sugar, baking soda and salt in a very large bowl with a lid. Make a well in the center of mixture. Add eggs, buttermilk and oil.
Stir just enough to moisten the dry ingredients.
Cover and store in refrigerator up to 6 weeks.

title: oatmeal peanut butter-chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat butter and peanut butter at medium speed with an electric mixer until fluffy.
Gradually add sugars, beating well.
Add eggs and vanilla, mixing well.
Combine oats and baking soda; add to butter mixture, mixing well.
Stir in chocolate morsels (by hand). Drop by tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 10 minutes.
Cool on cookie sheets for 5 minutes; remove to wire racks to cool completely.
Yields 7 dozen.

title: sweet potato nut whip
directions: Pare the potatoes; cook until tender.
Mash and add the beaten egg yolks and sufficient rich milk or cream to whip.
Add the butter, sugar and salt.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add whole pecan nuts; fold in the stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pile roughly into a buttered baking dish; sprinkle lightly with nut meats. Bake in a moderate oven at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: yale beets
directions: Drain beets and place in 1-quart casserole.
Mix dry ingredients together and blend with fruit juices and butter.
Pour over drained beets; cover and bake.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Tenderize the onion and celery in bacon.
Combine all ingredients except Velveeta.
Pour into baking dish. Pinch wedges into broccoli mixture until covered. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until bubbly.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together Crisco or margarine, white sugar and brown sugar.
Add well beaten eggs and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients.
Make into 2 to 3 long rolls.
Chill.
Slice and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes on ungreased cookie sheets.

title: powdered sugar frosting
directions: Mix together to desired consistency and frost.

title: peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: In a deep 2-quart microwave pan, mix the first 3 ingredients together.
Cook on High power for 7 to 9 minutes, stirring occasionally, until mixture bubbles and peanuts become brown.
Add the butter and vanilla; cook 2 1/2 more minutes on High.
Then stir in the baking soda until it foams and is well mixed.
Working fast, spoon onto a greased cookie sheet, spreading as evenly as possible.
Cool for 15 minutes and break into pieces.
Makes 1 pound and 3 ounces.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pecans.
Shape into a ball and roll in pecans.
Chill until time to serve.

title: mexican fudge
directions: Grate cheese.
Divide in half.
Mix 1/2 cheese with eggs and green sauce.
Put mixture into greased casserole or on a 9 x 12-inch cookie sheet.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown chops in oil.
Season with salt and pepper; drain. Combine remaining ingredients; pour over chops.
Cover; bake at 350° for about an hour.

title: calico beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain on paper towels and break into 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Pour off fat from pan, leaving a small amount to brown beef and onions.
Pour off excess drippings from beef/onion mixture.
Combine all other ingredients in a large pan or casserole that may be covered; add meat and blend through bean mixture.
Add bacon and fold gently.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 40 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve with a green salad and delicious loaf of bread.

title: stir-fried tomato beef
directions: Trim excess fat from steaks.
Cut meat into thin slices.
Core and cut tomatoes into 6 to 8 wedges.
Cut green onions to 1-inch lengths.
In a cup, combine water, sugar, cornstarch, soy sauce and vinegar.
Set aside.
In a large skillet, heat oil over high heat.
Add beef.
Stir until well browned.
Remove beef to bowl. Reduce heat to medium and add half of tomatoes to skillet.
Stir in cornstarch mixture and heat to boiling, stirring frequently. Add remaining tomatoes and onions.
Season with salt.
Stir in beef.
Serve immediately, with rice, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: biloxi chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in buttermilk a few minutes.
Shake chicken in a sack with mixture of dry ingredients.
Fry in hot oil until done, turning once.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Put dates, eggs, butter and sugar in skillet.
Cook 15 minutes over low heat; stir.
This will make thick syrup while hot.
Add Rice Krispies, pecans and vanilla; stir well.
Form into balls; roll in powdered sugar or coconut.

title: chicken croquettes
directions: Make a cream sauce by melting Crisco, flour and salt; add milk gradually.
Cook over low heat until thick and smooth.
Add chicken, onions and parsley.
Spread in shallow greased pan; chill.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Mix flour, pecans and margarine.
Spread mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press it down with a	spoon.	Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: old-fashioned gingerbread
directions: Combine flour, spices, salt and soda.
Sift into a large bowl. Stir in brown sugar.

title: chocolate pecan brownies
directions: Combine butter and chocolate in top of double boiler; bring water to boil.
Reduce heat to low and cook until the chocolate melts.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Combine milk, lemon juice, pineapple, Cool Whip, coconut, nuts and cherries.
Mix well.
Spoon filling into pie shells.
Chill well before serving.
Will keep in refrigerator for a week.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover bottom of pan with a thick layer of coconut and a layer of nuts.
Mix cake mix according to directions on box.
Spread cake mix over layers in pan.
In a separate bowl, mix cream cheese, oleo and sugar. Spread on top of cake in 6 to 8 places before baking.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, 325° for glass pan.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together chicken, soups, sour cream and broth.
Set aside. Mix cracker crumbs and butter.
Spread half of cracker crumbs in baking dish.
Spoon chicken mix over crumbs. Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: string beans
directions: Cook salt pork or turkey in a pot for 1 hour.
Wash beans and cut off tips (snapped).
Add beans, salt and onions to water. Cook covered for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: barbecue meat balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Roll in small balls and brown in grease.
Mix remaining ingredients and simmer while meat balls are browning.
When meat balls are brown, pour sauce over them and cook for a remaining 45 minutes.

title: coconut delight
directions: Cut butter into flour until mixture is consistency of coarse meal. Add pecans and press into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown; cool. Gradually add sugar to cream cheese, beating mixture well. Fold in 1 cup whipped topping and spread mixture in cooled crust. Prepare pudding according to package directions. Spread over cream cheese layer. Spread cherry pie filling over pudding layer. Top with remaining whipped topping. Sprinkle with toasted coconut.

title: pasta in a pot
directions: Cook ground beef in a large frying pan until brown.
Drain off excess fat.
Add onions, garlic, spaghetti sauce, stewed tomatoes and undrained mushrooms.
Mix well.
Simmer for 20 minutes or until onions are soft.
Meanwhile, cook macaroni shells according to package directions.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Pour half of the macaroni shells into a deep casserole.
Cover with half of the tomato meat sauce.
Spread half of the sour cream over sauce.
Top with grated Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with grated Mozzarella.
Cover.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: You will need sterilized jars and lids.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat peanut butter, butter, vanilla and salt until fluffy; gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk, then powdered sugar until smooth.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on baking sheets.
Chill until firm.
With fork or wooden pick, dip each into melted candy coating; let excess candy coating drip off.
Place on wax paper lined baking sheets; let stand or chill until firm.
Store covered at room temperature or in refrigerator. Makes about 12 1/2 dozen.

title: pizza dough
directions: Mix dissolved yeast, water and cooking oil well together and add to flour and salt.
Cover and let set in hot water for 5 minutes.
Then divide the dough and put on 3 (12-inch) pizza pans. Cover and let set for at least 2 hours in a warm place to raise. Prebake crusts on bottom shelf at 425° for 4 to 5 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter.
Add soup, diluted with broth, soy sauce, Tabasco and chicken.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Put in casserole and cover with noodles and almonds.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: big ann's potato salad
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into small pieces.
Boil until soft. Drain and spice according to taste.
Hard-boil eggs.
Peel and slice.
Chop onions, celery and peppers.
Place all ingredients into large bowl.
Add mayonnaise and mix together.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer until thick.

title: sunday dinner steak
directions: Prepare roasting bag as directed.
Place steak in center of bag.
Arrange vegetables around meat.
Mix soup and water.
Pour over and around meat.
Close bag and bake one hour in
325° oven.

title: spiced punch
directions: In 4-quart saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Simmer over low heat for 30 minutes.
Remove cloves and cinnamon sticks.
Serve hot.
Yields 24 cups (1/2 cup) servings.

title: dry flowers
directions: Cover flowers with mixture until dried.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease well and flour two round 8-inch layer cake pans.
Sift together the flour, salt, soda and cinnamon; set aside.
Combine sugar, oil and eggs; beat 2 minutes. Gradually add flour mixture.
Beat at low speed for 1 minute. Add grated carrots and chopped nuts.
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Arrange chicken in buttered 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Mix soup with sour cream and pour over chicken.
Use just enough stuffing mix to cover top of casserole and sprinkle poppy seed over this.
Pour melted butter over this and bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.
(Can make a day ahead and refrigerate.)

title: spanish coffee cake
directions: Mix flour, brown and white sugars, nutmeg, salt and oil. Reserve 3/4 cup. Add nuts and cinnamon to reserved portion for topping. To first mixture add buttermilk, soda, and beaten egg. Pour mixture into greased 9 x 13 inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chewy cake
directions: Melt butter and sugar in a saucepan.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: strawberry bread and spread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, combine first 6 ingredients.
Stir until evenly mixed.
Make well in center; set aside.

title: honey baked chicken
directions: Lay chicken in greased shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Beat egg yolk with honey and brush on chicken.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and eggs until fluffy. Add the bananas, vanilla, salt, soda and flour.
Mix lightly and pour in loaf pan, greased on the bottom only.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: italian chicken
directions: Wash chicken and place in a large bowl with an airtight lid. Pour dressing and soy sauce over chicken and seal with lid.
Mix well and marinate in the refrigerator for 4 hours or overnight. Remove chicken and place in an oven proof-baking dish.
Pour some of the marinade on the chicken pieces.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: easy, cheesy brunch casserole
directions: Put the bread in bottom of dish.
Saute onion and mushrooms in margarine and pour over bread.
Mix the sausage, cheeses and flour together; sprinkle on top of meat.
Mix the remaining ingredients; pour over mixture.
Cover and chill.
Eight hours later, remove from refrigerator and let stand 30 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until set.
Let stand 10 minutes and serve.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in saucepan, stirring until crumbly.
Drain. Add soup, brown sugar, catsup and onion.
Mix well.
Fold in beans and bacon. Spoon into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through. Yields 6 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; cook until thick.
Add the jello and cool.
Fold in the berries.
Pour into pie shell.
Let set up in refrigerator.

title: harvest date muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Line 12 muffin cups with paper baking cups or grease 12 cups.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except sunflower seeds.
Stir by hand until dry particles are moistened.
Divide evenly in 12 cups (cups will be full). Sprinkle with sunflower seeds.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until a toothpick in center comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes. Remove from pan.
Serve warm or store in refrigerator.

title: russian refresher
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in an airtight container for up to 6 months.

title: four layer dessert
directions: 1st
Layer:
Mix flour, margarine and pecans thoroughly in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: spinach and potato gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease shallow 3 quart casserole.
In 10 inch skillet, melt margarine or butter over medium heat - add shallots and cook 5 minutes or until tender, stirring occasionally.
Remove skillet from heat and stir in spinach, nutmeg, 1/4 tsp. salt and 1/4 tsp. pepper.

title: grilled chicken with cilantro butter
directions: Preheat grill to medium heat. In small dish, combine garlic, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Mash into a paste using back side of a large spoon. Add lime peel. Wash hands.

title: mom's great breakfast casserole
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with rolls.
Place sausage on top of rolls.
Next, sprinkle cheese.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper, dash of oregano and green pepper together.
Pour over top.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes, until slightly brown.

title: orange peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine butter, peanut butter, sugars, egg and juice and rind together in a bowl. Beat vigorously until mixture is smooth, light and fluffy. Combine sifted flour with the soda and salt. Sift again and add to the first mixture slowly until all is added. Add the chopped nuts.
Knead dough with hands until smooth. Pack firmly in two bars.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Place in refrigerator. Chill until firm. Cut in 1/8-inch thick slices.
Place on greased baking sheet. Bake in a 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until done.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: no-fail pie crust
directions: Combine flour, salt and shortening.
Chop fine.
Beat egg in same cup shortening has been measured and add vinegar to the egg. Fill with cold water to make 1 cup.
Add all 3 to flour mixture and combine using hands.
Makes 3 (2-crust) pies.

title: basic roll dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large bowl.
Add sugar and shortening, egg, salt and half of flour.
Mix until smooth.
Stir in remainder of flour to make soft dough.
Place in greased bowl. Turning to grease top.
Cover and let rise 1 hour or until doubled in bulk.

title: jeanne's peanut brittle
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, combine sugar and syrup.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, until it is a stringy consistency. Remove from heat. Add peanuts.
Place back on heat and cook until light brown. Remove from heat again and add butter, vanilla and baking soda. Quickly spread on buttered cookie sheet, thinly. Cool and break up.

title: scotch shortbread
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar; beat until light and fluffy.
Combine flour and salt; gradually add to creamed mixture. Blend well.
Roll out dough on a lightly floured surface to 11 x 17-inch rectangle 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into 1-inch squares or diamonds.
Transfer to cookie sheets.
Prick cookies with a fork. Bake in preheated 300° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove immediately to wire racks to cool.
Yields about 70.

title: buffet casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic in 1 tablespoon oil.
Cook spinach and drain, reserving liquid.
Add water to make 1 cup. Stir liquid, tomato and spaghetti sauces, salt and pepper into meat mixture and simmer 10 minutes.

title: granola
directions: Mix together all ingredients and spread on a greased sheet pan. Bake at 300° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Add 1 1/2 cups raisins. Makes 6 servings.

title: spinach dip
directions: Squeeze all the liquid out of the spinach.
Stir all the ingredients in a medium size mixing bowl; mix well until thoroughly blended.
Chill and serve with crackers or vegetable dippers.

title: bean soup
directions: Brown ground beef and drain. Cook bacon and brown it, then crumble it up.
Mix all ingredients together in a large pot. Simmer for 30 minutes. Good with crackers or cornbread.

title: can opener combo
directions: Heat green beans, soup, chicken and sage, stirring occasionally.
Serve on noodles. Serves 4.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Sift the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into a bowl. Blend in the butter.
Add the water; mix lightly.
Pat out into an 8-inch square pan.
Cover with cherries, drained from a pint can. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar.
Pour the cherry juice on top.
Bake for 40 minutes in the oven at 350°.
Serve warm with the sauce which forms in bottom of pan spooned over.
You'll love it!

title: sugarless fruit cake
directions: Bring to boil the fruits, oleo, water and juice.
Simmer 2 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix flour, soda, cinnamon, salt, eggs, nuts and vanilla.
Add to cooled fruit mixture.
Pour into angel food cake pan.
Cook at 325° for 40 minutes or until done.
Very moist and good.

title: easy broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Boil water and cook the California blend for 20 minutes. Drain and place in casserole dish.
Place cheese in the mix, followed by the undiluted soup.

title: lasagna
directions: Mix ground chuck, both spaghetti sauces (dry and bottled), and tomato paste together.
Add extra onions, chopped mushrooms and green peppers to taste, a little Oregano and enough water to get to thick, but spreadable consistency.
Mix cheeses together. Spread one layer of meat mixture in bottom of large lasagna pan; top with layer of noodles, then layer of cheese mixture, then noodles, then meat, then noodles, then cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 - 35 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Allow mixture to cool and serve with your favorite chips.

title: apple puff salad
directions: Cook juices with cornstarch until thickened. Add marshmallows. Let cool. Whip the cream; slowly add sugar and vanilla, whipping until sugar is dissolved and just until stiff enough to hold its shape. Add fruit and juice mixture to whipped cream. Spread 1 cup layer of crackers in 9 x 13-inch pan. Add layer of apple mixture, crumbs and apple mixture. End with crumbs. Refrigerate until firm.

title: marshmallow bars
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil in a double boiler.
Cool. Fold in graham crackers, marshmallows, coconut and nuts.
Put into a 9 x 9-inch pan. Refrigerate.

title: jelly roll
directions: Combine eggs and sugar; beat well, about 15 minutes with electric mixer.
Pour into well-greased and floured 10 x 15-inch cookie pan.
Bake at 325° until done (light golden brown).
Turn onto waxed paper and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Roll and let cool.
Unroll carefully and spread with desired filling.
Re-roll. To serve, cut in 1-inch slices.

title: good stuff
directions: Mix the cake mix with 2 eggs and butter.
Spread in a greased 11 x 7-inch pan.
Mix the remaining ingredients.
Spread on top of cake mix mixture.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cut into squares when cooled.

title: peach pie dessert
directions: Mix first three ingredients together.
Line pie plate with crushed vanilla wafers and pour preach mixture over and top with Cool Whip.
Freeze in freezer overnight, till frozen, take out and serve.

title: crock-pot potatoes
directions: Melt oleo in saucepan and add sour cream and soup.
Add instant onions.
Combine with cooked potatoes in crock-pot on low.
Heat for at least 1 hour.
Delicious.

title: vanishing oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix.
Add flour, soda, cinnamon and salt. Mix well.
Add oatmeal and raisins.
Drop from teaspoon on ungreased pan.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: crispy cookies
directions: Cream the butter.
Gradually add sugars, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer. Add eggs and beat well.
Add oil and vanilla. Combine flour, soda and salt. Add to creamed mixture. Stir in oatmeal, cornflake crumbs, coconut and pecans. Shape dough into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets and flatten each ball with fork.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes. Remove from cookie sheet and cool on wire racks. Yields about 7 dozen.

title: best year round punch
directions: Place sherbet in punch bowl and pour the ginger ale over it. You can begin serving immediately as the sherbet melts.
You have 112 ounces of ginger ale and 65 ounces of sherbet, a total of 176 ounces. Divide the size of your cups into this and you'll know exactly how many servings you have.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Cut cheese into small cubes and melt with soup.
Stir constantly.
Add thawed broccoli, and heat until warm.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chili dip
directions: Put cream cheese on bottom of microwave safe dish.
Add chili next, then top with Velveeta cheese.
Microwave on High 5 minutes. Dip with nacho chips.

title: butterscotch bars
directions: Pat in 9 x 13-inch pan graham cracker ingredients.
Add 2 cups coconut.
Sprinkle over crust.
Add Eagle Brand milk and spread over coconut.
Bake 15 minutes, then broil until top is light brown.
Cool.

title: cherry crunch cobbler
directions: Stir cherries and pineapple together.
In a separate bowl, mix cake mix, sugar and pecans.
Add on top of cherry mixture.
Pour melted butter on top.
Microwave 15 minutes on High.
If not done, stir and microwave an extra 2 or more minutes.
Serve with ice cream.
You may substitute cherries with apples.

title: easy chicken creole
directions: Heat olive oil in a large frying pan over medium heat.
Add chicken and saut until no longer pink (about 5 minutes).
Add peppers and onions and saut 5 more minutes, stirring as needed. Add Cajun seasoning and diced tomatoes.
Cover and simmer until tender but vegetables are still crispy (about 5 more minutes). Serve over hot rice.
Great with hot French bread and a green salad.
Serves 4.

title: green beans oriental
directions: Simmer the first 3 ingredients in oil for 10 minutes.
Drain. Blend 1/4 cup cold chicken stock with cornstarch.
Stir.
Heat remaining chicken stock to boiling and add cornstarch mixture. Stir until thickened.
Combine everything except 1/2 package almonds.
Turn into casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Add the rest of ingredients.

title: spicy apple cookies
directions: Cream butter until soft.
Add sugars, while continuing to cream.
Add eggs; beat well.
Mix and sift flour, soda, spices and salt.
Add with remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes, until golden.

title: apple-pecan spice cake(serves 15)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Sift dry ingredients together. Set aside. Blend oil and sugar in electric mixer at medium speed for 5 minutes. Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well. Add dry ingredients to oil mixture and combine thoroughly. Add apples, pecans and raisins and blend well with spatula. Pour batter into a buttered and floured 10-inch spring-form pan. Bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until an inserted knife comes out dry. Serve with caramel sauce and pecan ice cream.

title: sweet potato pone
directions: Wash the sweet potatoes and prick them with a fork.
Then bake them in a 350° oven for an hour.
Remove from oven and cool. Remove skin, then cut up and mash.
You should have 1 cup of mashed potato.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add vanilla.
Add 1 egg yolk at a time while beating.
Add flour and sour cream alternately.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Fold in cake batter. Cook in tube an for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: cornbread for two
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a small greased pan.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: seven-up salad
directions: Heat Seven-Up and pour over Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved. Mix cream cheese with hot water until smooth.
Add cream cheese mixture and remaining ingredients together.
Pour into a refrigerator bowl and chill several hours.
Serve on lettuce bed and garnish with cherries, if desired.

title: party cucumber sandwiches
directions: Cut cucumber into thin slices.
Mix together dressing mix and cream cheese.
Spread on bread slices.
Next place a cucumber on each slice.
Sprinkle dill weed on top of cucumber.

title: taco salad
directions: Layer vegetables in above order in large serving bowl.
Mix hamburger with tomato sauce and seasoning.
Pour over vegetables. Top with tomatoes, cheese and Fritos.
Mix all just before serving.

title: blue cheese snacks
directions: Mix baking mix, water and cheese until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously 20 strokes.
Smooth dough into ball on well floured cloth-covered board.
Knead 5 times.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with floured 2-inch cutter.
Cut each round into fourths.
Place wedges in ungreased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix butter and parsley; spoon over wedges.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.
Bake at 450° until lightly brown, 10 to 12 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Dice all peppers, tomatoes, onions and garlic fine.
Combine all ingredients.
Add Lawry's seasoned salt and lemon pepper (shake to own taste).

title: favorite chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, margarine and sugar in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Sift flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt together. Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, mixing well after each addition.
Mix in vanilla and walnuts.
Spoon into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove to wire rack to cool.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: frozen salad
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and salad dressing.
Add pineapple, fruit cocktail, marshmallows and seedless grapes.
Put in a tray and freeze.
Cut in cubes.

title: raspberry coconut cake
directions: *Or use your favorite raspberry jam made with Sure-Jell fruit pectin.
tags: recipe White Chocolate Butter Cream Frosting

title: sugarless applesauce cake
directions: Combine raisins, fruit and water in a saucepan and boil until water is evaporated and fruit is sauce (cool). In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, nutmeg and cinnamon. In another bowl, combine eggs, applesauce, sweetener, oil and vanilla. Add nuts and fruit to this mixture. Stir into dry mixture. Blend thoroughly. Pour batter into a greased tube pan. Bake 35 to 40 minutes in 350° oven or until done.

title: broccoli salad
directions: In large bowl, combine separated vegetables, bacon, eggs, onions and tomatoes; set aside.
Combine mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Mix until smooth.
Pour over just before serving.

title: cottage cheese-pineapple-dill bread
directions: In large bowl, cream oleo and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, then cottage cheese and pineapple; mix well.
In another bowl, combine remaining ingredients, except milk.
Then alternately, add the milk and the dry ingredients to the creamed mixture.
Spoon the batter into a greased and floured 8-inch round pan.
Bake at 375` for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°, continue baking for about 50 minutes or until done.
Cool 10 minutes then remove from pan to rack.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Add in order given.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour into 2 greased and floured bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Melt butter and cool.
Beat eggs, add sugar flour, coconut and milk.
Stir well.
Pour into 2-9 in. pie pans.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes.

title: seven-layer salad
directions: Alternate the ingredients in layers.
Top with dressing mixture.
Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese and refrigerate several hours.

title: crock-pot potatoes
directions: Slice all the potatoes; do not peel.
Swish the slices in 2 cups of warm water and cream of tartar.
Grease crock-pot.
Add half the potatoes, 1/4 cup of flour, 1/2 teaspoon of salt and 1/2 teaspoon of pepper.
Add remaining potatoes, 1/4 cup of flour, 1/2 teaspoon of salt and 1/2 teaspoon of pepper.
Pat 4 tablespoons of butter on top, then spread cans of soup on top.
Cook on high for 3 to 3 1/2 hours, then add 2 cups Cheddar cheese and cook on high another 1/2 hour.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: banana oatmeal cupcakes
directions: Combine flour, soda, nutmeg, salt and cinnamon.
Blend in blender egg, sugar, bananas and oil.
Add flour mixture, then add oatmeal and chocolate chips.
Bake at 400° until brown, about 25 minutes.

title: new england meat loaf
