directions: In a mixing bowl, combine hamburg, onion, mushrooms, egg, soup and spices.
Mix well with hands.
Crush crackers with hands and add to mixture.
Mix.
Place in bread pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: sammie's caramel praline pie
directions: Brown coconut and pecans in margarine; set aside to cool. Combine cream cheese, milk and 1 1/2 cartons Cool Whip.
Layer cream cheese mixture on bottom.
Then layer pecan mixture, next drizzle caramel on top of other layers.
End and top with remaining Cool Whip.
Freeze for 2 to 3 hours before serving.
Makes 3 small pies.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese, chopped peanuts, caramels and brown sugar.
Mix for 3 minutes.
You have a dip.
Peel apples and enjoy.

title: anise cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add flour, soda and anise seed.
Mix.
Form into 3 rolls and chill.
Slice and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Mix last 3 ingredients together and pour over first mixture.
Let stand overnight.

title: layered taco dip
directions: Fry hamburger and mix in 1 package of taco seasoning; set aside.
Mix together sour cream, 1 package of taco seasoning and avocado.
Set aside.
Layer in pan as follows:
refried beans, hamburger, sour cream mixture, salsa, lettuce, cheese, onion, tomato and olives.
Serve with taco chips.

title: roast lamb(agnello arrosto)
directions: This lamb can be
roasted
on
an open spit for a great party. We usually do this at Easter.

title: red bean caliente
directions: Soak beans overnight in cold water.
Drain and add fresh water to beans.
Bring water level 2 inches above beans; add salt and cook over moderate heat for 1 hour.
Add water as needed.
Combine all other ingredients and add to beans.
Cook over low heat until beans are done.
You can cook all day in a crock-pot.

title: sweet pickle strips
directions: Slice cucumber; let stand, covered with boiling water, 4 or 5 hours.
Drain off water.
Place cucumber in jars.
Boil solution of remaining ingredients and pour into jars; process 5 minutes.

title: pozole
directions: Place chicken in large pot.
Cover with 2/3 chicken broth and 1/3 water.
Bring to a boil and simmer until meat falls from bones. Remove chicken; remove all meat from bones and shred.
Leave plenty of multi-bite chunks.
Saute a large onion, 2 to 3 cloves and chopped garlic in a bit of the fat skimmed from the broth.
Add this back to the pot along with the shredded chicken, oregano, cumin, chili powder, jalapenos, salt and pepper.
Simmer for a while (maybe 45 minutes).
Add hominy; simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour longer.
Taste for seasonings.
Garnish.

title: pickled beets
directions: Slice cooked beets into large saucepan.
Make a pickling syrup of the sugar, water and vinegar.
Add lemon slices.
Mix spices; add to syrup.
Pour this mixture over the sliced beets.
Bring to light boil, then simmer for 15 minutes.
Heat seals and lids in boiling water.
Seal in hot jars.
Let hot jars stand for 24 hours to be sure of seal.

title: hamburger sauce over potatoes
directions: Saut veggies - add hamburger and brown (cook covered while browning to avoid crumbling) drain fat, add the tomatoes, simmer for 1/2 hour to cook tomatoes mix flour & water to make loose paste turn off heat, when it stops bubbling add the flour/water mixture to thicken - stir constantly to desired consistency.
Serve over boiled potatoes.
Serves 6.

title: fruit and nut squares(sugar-free)
directions: Mix flour, soda and cinnamon.
In a 3-quart saucepan, over medium heat, bring water, prunes, dates and raisins to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and add margarine.
Stir until melted.
Cool.
Stir in eggs and vanilla. Add to dry mixture and add nuts.
Pour into square, greased dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: smothered chicken
directions: Flatten chicken to 1/4 thickness. Sprinkle with garlic powder and seasoned salt. In a large nonstick skillet over medium heat, brown chicken in oil for 4 minutes. Turn; top with mushrooms, cheese, green onions and bacon. Cover and cook until chicken juices run clear and cheese is melted (about 4 minutes). Makes 4 servings.

title: lentil soup
directions: Soak lentils for 10 minutes; drain and rinse.
Combine all ingredients in a medium pot.
Bring to a boil, then simmer until tender, for about 2 hours.
Season to taste with salt and pepper. Add additional water if necessary.
Serve with a lemon wedge. Squeeze lemon over soup before eating.

title: quick chicken cacciatore
directions: *Use only 1/2 of can, add more if desired.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream together sugar and butter, then add the eggs.
Make paste from cocoa and vinegar, then add to milk.
Mix salt, soda and flour.
Add milk mixture and creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and coloring.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Grease bottom only of about 12 medium muffin cups. Beat egg. Stir in milk and oil. Stir in flours, sugar, baking powder and salt just until moistened (batter will be lumpy). Fold in blueberries. Fill muffin cups about 3/4 full. Bake until golden brown, about 20 minutes. Immediately remove from pan. Makes about 12 muffins.

title: picante sauce
directions: Boil peppers until medium soft.
Put in blender and add tomatoes, garlic, onion and salt. Blend or chop for 1 minute.

title: brownies - one bowl
directions: Stir together over heat until smooth the first 3 ingredients. Cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix all ingredients together. Pour into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 30.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Mix ingredients and place in ovenproof pan.
Bake at 350° until done or until tester comes out clean.

title: low-fat pumpkin pie
directions: Line 9-inch pie pan with pastry.
Chill.
Combine all ingredients and beat smooth.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 35 minutes or until set.
Makes 1 pie.

title: ranch dinner
directions: Spread potatoes on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add salt, pepper and garlic.
Sprinkle rice over potatoes.
Crumble meat and fry in skillet.
Then spread over the potatoes and rice.
Arrange onions over the meat and peppers over the onions.
Pour tomatoes over all and add water up to the level of the rice.
Lay pieces of cheese on top.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes, then at 350° for 40 minutes more.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.
This is good made early and put in the oven to heat.

title: pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs slightly.
Stir in sugar, syrup and butter.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until filling is slightly firm.
Center of pie may look soft when shaken but will become firm when cooled.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt, soda, baking powder, cinnamon, cloves and allspice together.
Add shortening, water and applesauce. Beat 2 minutes on medium speed.
Add eggs and beat.
Fold in raisins and nuts.
Bake in 2 loaf pans, greased and floured, in a 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: honey butter
directions: Mix equal amounts of butter and honey and add a little vanilla extract.
Keep a batch of this on hand to sweeten all your breakfasts.
Terrific on everything from muffins to toast.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over lard, sugar and salt. Stir until it melts. Dissolve yeast in warm water. Add yeast and eggs to mixture. Fold in flour. Cover in air tight container overnight. Make out rolls 1 1/2 hours to 2 hours before baking. Using muffin pans, put three balls per cup. Roll with floured hands. Knead dough before rolling balls (pinch off dough and roll). Cover with paper towel for rising. Place in warm place for 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Bake at 375° for about 5 minutes or until brown.

title: drop donuts
directions: In large bowl, mix all dry ingredients.
Add egg and milk; blend well.
(Do not knead.)
Make round balls; drop into grease at 400° for only a few seconds.

title: marian motcheck's baked cheese fondue
directions: Butter 1 side of bread and cube.
Alternate bread and cheese in well-greased dish or pan.
Mix eggs, milk, salt, paprika and mustard.
Pour melted butter and liquid mixture over bread and cheese.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: crawford pie
directions: Mix together cream cheese, sour cream and sugar, creamed.
Add pineapple.
Mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in pie shell.
Let set about 30 minutes.

title: tex-mex style cheesy chili casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add peppers.
Cook until tender.
Stir in corn, tomato sauce and chili powder.
Add 1/2 cup Cheez Whiz. Stir until melted.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and cream cheese.
Add sugar and cream until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour and add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Cool 10 minutes.

title: coconut sour cream cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, eggs, sour cream and cream of coconut together with electric mixer as directed on cake mix box.
Bake in greased pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown the hamburger meat with the onions and drain well.
Mix the soups and Ro-Tel tomatoes; add to the meat.
Simmer about 10 minutes.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, layer the meat, chips and cheese until you have used it all.
Top with more cheese and heat in a 350° oven until steaming hot and the cheese is bubbly.

title: rocky road candy in microwave
directions: In 4-quart microproof dish, mix chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and butter.
Cook 5 minutes or until melted.
Stir, then fold in marshmallows and walnuts.
Spread in a buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Let set until firm, about 2 hours.
Cut into squares.

title: raspberry-apple delight
directions: Melt red hots in boiling water; add and dissolve jello.
Mix in applesauce.
Chill until set.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce leaves.

title: sesame shrimp with lime cilantro butter
directions: Peel and devein shrimp; set aside in colander.
Melt butter and saute ginger and garlic for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add lime juice, zest, cilantro, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Cook over medium heat for 5 minutes, slightly reducing liquid.

title: cajun cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour in cake pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 300°.
Can add nuts and icing as you wish.
German Chocolate Icing is good.

title: italian baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, blend sour cream and egg; set aside.
In a medium bowl or shallow pan, mix bread crumbs and cheese.
Dip each piece of chicken in sour cream mixture and then roll in bread crumb mixture to coat completely.
Place chicken in a lightly oiled shallow baking pan.
Bake until chicken is tender, about 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: crunchy mallow candy
directions: Melt chocolate with peanut butter in double boiler or in saucepan over low heat.
Stir until smooth.
Fold in marshmallows. Pour into greased 9-inch square pan. Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: swiss steak
directions: Rinse pieces of steak and let drain.
Chop green pepper into small pieces.
Cut onions into 1/4's.
Cut celery in 1/4's long way and dice into small pieces.
Cut carrots into 1/4's long way and dice into small pieces.
Put all vegetables together after dicing; rinse well and let drain.
Put oil into frying pan. Brown steak on each side.
Salt and pepper well.
Set oven to 375°.
Read remaining directions before going further.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine all ingredients together, mixing well with the water and milk.
Drop by teaspoon into hot grease.
Fry until brown.

title: hot stuffed picnic rolls
directions: Lightly brown ground meat or turkey (or half and half) in frypan; remove meat.
Saute onion, celery and green pepper in pan drippings.
When they are soft and transparent, add beef and rest of ingredients up to mustard.
Cook slowly for 10 to 15 minutes. Spread 1 side of bun with oleo and other side with mustard; fill bun with meat mixture.
Wrap each in foil and seal well.
Heat in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes or longer on a cookie sheet.

title: stuffed squash(yellow crookneck)
directions: Place whole squash in boiling water until they can be pierced with fork. Remove from water. Cool in cold water. Slice squash in 1/2 lengthwise. Scoop out seeds. Mix seed with prepared dressing. Fill cavity you formed in squash with dressing mixture, mounding slightly. Top with bacon strip. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: devil's food cake and icing
directions: Add 1 cup boiling water last and beat. Makes 3 layers. Bake at 350° until done.

title: fruit hard sauce
directions: Sift the confectioners sugar. Beat the butter until soft.
Add the sugar gradually. Beat until well blended. Beat in the cream and the strawberries, raspberries, apricots or bananas. Chill thoroughly.

title: congo squares
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs and
all
dry ingredients. Add chocolate chips and nuts, then
add
vanilla.
Bake in greased pan, 8 x 16-inches at 325° about 25
to 30 minutes. Cut in squares while warm.

title: quick crescents
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients until smooth.
Cut butter and flour together until size of beans.
Pour liquid mixture over dry ingredients.
Mix with spatula just until flour is moist. Refrigerate at least 4 hours up to 4 days.

title: beef and bacon delight
directions: Cut franks into 1 pieces each.
Wrap 1/4 slice of bacon around each piece and secure with toothpick.
In a crock-pot or slow cooker, make a layer of brown sugar.
Alternate layers until all franks are in the cooker.
Cover and cook slowly for about 6 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve hot.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Combine sugar and oil together, then add eggs.
Put all dry ingredients together and combine well.

Pour dry ingredients into sugar and oil combination. Add pecans and vanilla to this mixture. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. After cake is done and well cooled, spread the marshmallow cream on top.

title: iced green tomato pickles
directions: Soak thickly sliced tomatoes in lime water (thoroughly dissolve powdered lime in cold water) for 24 hours.
Drain and soak 4 hours in clear cold water, changing water every hour. Drain.
Place in kettle the vinegar, sugar and spices. Bring to a rolling boil and pour over tomatoes. Let stand overnight.
In the morning, boil 1 hour and seal in containers.
Use crock or large bowl for soaking.

title: twenty-four hour slaw
directions: Shred cabbage, pepper and onion.
Add salt and let stand 15 minutes.
Drain off liquid.
Add vinegar and sugar.
Let stand 24 hours, then drain off liquid.
Store in refrigerator indefinitely. Makes 3 pints.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken and remove bones and skin.
Cut up and place in baking dish.
Mix chicken broth and soup, heating and stirring until smooth.
Pour broth over chicken.
Mix dry ingredients with milk.
Add margarine.
Pour Veg-All over the chicken.
Pour dry mixture on top and bake at 425° for about 30 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: cheese ball
directions: Note:
The mayonnaise and milk are not necessary, but they do add flavor.

title: whipples
directions: Grease a cookie sheet. Combine cake mix, Cool Whip and egg in a large bowl. This will be sticky. Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls into a small bowl filled with powdered sugar. Roll into a ball to coat. Place balls on the cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Edges should be just slightly browned.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Place deboned meat in chicken broth and water. Add other ingredients. Simmer till noodles are tender. Call your friends over.

title: rabbit italiano
directions: Soak meat overnight in wine to cover.
Melt butter in deep skillet, add onions and saute until tender.
Blend in flour and add 1 cup wine in which rabbit was marinated.
Add water, mushrooms, remaining wine, salt, pepper, bay leaves, parsley flakes, oregano and thyme.
Bring mixture to boil and add meat. Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4.

title: mike newman's lasagna
directions: Take hard noodles and layer with Ragu, ground meat, cheese, cottage cheese and precooked and drained spinach.
End with noodles, sauce and Mozzarella on top.
Pour 1 cup of water around edge; cover and seal with aluminum foil.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms only of 12 medium muffin cups.
Beat egg; stir in milk and oil.
Stir in remaining ingredients all at once, just until flour is moistened.
(Batter will be lumpy.)
Fill muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake until golden brown, about 20 minutes.
Immediately remove from pan.
Cool on rack or serve warm.

title: travis' little bunnies
directions: Ingredients depend on how many bunnies you want to make.

title: bananas foster
directions: Peel and slice bananas and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Melt butter in skillet; add brown sugar, cinnamon and stir over low heat until melted and mixed well.
Add the banana liqueur and rum and then the bananas and saut for several minutes, until golden. Pour over ice cream and serve.

title: velvet pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar well.
Add an egg at a time, beating well.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture and milk alternately to sugar mixture.
Add flavorings.
Pour into greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Put dough in cake pan.
Drain peaches and reserve.
Add peaches to top of dough.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Before serving, pour juice on top of cake.

title: ann's delicious fudge
directions: Let the cheese and the margarine melt at room temperature. Mix all the ingredients. It will be hard to mix, but continue to mix with a spoon until the cheese disappears. Keep refrigerated.

title: broccoli cheese chicken
directions: In skillet with butter, cook chicken for 10 minutes or until browned on both sides; set aside.

title: deviled crab
directions: Remove any shell or cartilage from crabmeat.
Cook onion in butter until tender.
Blend in flour.
Add milk gradually and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add seasonings and lemon juice. Stir a little of the hot sauce into egg; add to remaining sauce, stirring constantly.
Add parsley and crabmeat.
Place in 6 well-greased individual shells or 5 ounce custard cups.
Combine butter and crumbs; sprinkle over top of each shell.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.
Serves 6.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets.
Peel and dice.
Fry bacon crisp. Drain and crumble.
Saute onion and celery in bacon grease.
Add to onion and celery, flour, sugar, salt, celery seed, pepper, basil and parsley.
Cook over low heat stirring until smooth and bubbly. Remove from heat and stir in water and vinegar.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly for 1 minute.
Carefully stir in potatoes and bacon.
Serve warm.

title: party ryes
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Brown ground beef and drain. Mix sausage, ground beef, cheese, garlic salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Place on party ryes. Cook in 400° oven for 10 minutes. They can also be frozen and cooked later.

title: fresh fruit crumble
directions: In a large bowl, combine pear slices, syrup, lemon juice and peel and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Put in 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Stir together flour, oatmeal and nutmeg.
With a pastry cutter, cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle over pears.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until pears are tender.

title: buttermilk cream pie
directions: Mix together sugar, flour, egg yolks and buttermilk.
Beat at low speed with mixer until all ingredients are mixed.
Pour into a heavy saucepan and add margarine and vanilla.
Cook until boiling and stir constantly until thick.
Pour into prepared pie shell. Cool; top with meringue or Cool Whip.

title: banana-nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Put pickles and onions in salt; let stand 2 hours.
Boil the sugar, vinegar and celery seed; cool.
Drain and rinse pickles and onions. Pour syrup over pickles and freeze.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Add 1/3 cup of mix to 1 cup boiling water.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Use 3 heaping tablespoons per cup mix with hot water.

title: oyster stew
directions: Inspect the oysters for bits of shell.
Chop, if desired; save the liquid.
Melt butter in a heavy bottomed saucepan.
Add flour and seasoning gradually and stir until quite free of lumps.
Add milk and oyster liquid a little at a time and stir until mixture boils.
Add oysters; simmer for 5 minutes.
If too thick, add more milk.
Season to taste and serve in a heated tureen.
When serving, top with whipped cream and parsley.
Yields 4 to 5 servings.

title: brownies cockaigne
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in top of a double boiler and cool completely.
In separate bowl, beat eggs and salt until light in color and foamy.
Add gradually to eggs the sugar and vanilla. Continue beating.
Add the chocolate/butter mixture to the egg/sugar mixture with only a few strokes by hand.
Fold in flour and nuts if desired.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan, about 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool, then cut into squares.

title: gourmet pasta
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Add salt, pepper, tomatoes, tomato sauce and garlic.
Simmer about 5 minutes.
Remove garlic pulp.
Cook noodles according to directions and drain.
While noodles are still warm, add cheese and sour cream; mix well.
In casserole, alternate layers of noodles mixture, beef mixture and grated cheese.
Repeat layers until all used.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mary's butter pecan ice cream pie
directions: Thoroughly blend milk and ice cream in a bowl. Add pudding mix. Beat slowly with hand beater or at low speed of electric mixer, until blended. Pour into pie shell. Chill until set, at least 1 hour. Garnish with whipped topping and chopped nuts if desired.

title: superior meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°, prepare a 13 x 9 baking dish.
Mix all ingredients in a large bow, shape into loaf in the baking dish. Bake uncovered 1 hour or until no longer pink in the middle.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a 9 x 9 x 3-inch dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until done.
Serves six.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spread drained pineapple in greased pan 13 x 9 x 2-inch, cover with cherry pie filling, spread cake mix over cherry filling, place butter all over and cover with nuts. Bake for 45 minutes.

title: french dressing
directions: Put ketchup in jar, then oil, vinegar and sugar.
Now add remaining ingredients.
Shake well.
Keep refrigerated.

title: beef stew
directions: Clean fat from stew meat. Roll meat in mixture of flour, Mrs. Dash and pepper to taste.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Trim fat from steak; slice in 2-inch strips.
Brown steak in oil.
Add onion and cook for 5 minutes.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Prepare the patties by combining the ground beef, onion, green peppers, bread crumbs and salt and pepper to taste. Shape into 4 oval patties; fry until golden brown. In the drippings, make the gravy and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato pone
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Bake for 25 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: chili rellenos pie
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, melt butter.
Sprinkle chiles over butter.
Spread cheese over chiles.
In a bowl, mix buttermilk baking mix, eggs, salt and milk.
Pour over cheese. Bake in preheated 350° oven 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: fried okra
directions: Cut okra in
round,
dip
in cracker crumbs or meal and fry in hot oil.

title: crab apple sauce
directions: Stem the crab apples and rinse in lukewarm water. Drain, then place the apples in a saucepan with the water. Bring to a boil and reduce heat to a simmer; cook slowly until the fruit is soft. While still warm, put through sieve to remove seeds and stems. Add sugar and cinnamon to taste.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch greased pan. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm or cold with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: oriental punch
directions: Add water to frozen juices as indicated on cans.
Mix all juices together and then add sugar to taste.
Slowly add almond extract, tasting after each teaspoonful until you have the flavor desired.
Chill thoroughly and garnish with Mandarin oranges.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown beef.
Drain.
Add onion and all of the spices.
Add juice, puree, paste and water.
Simmer for at least 1 1/2 hours.

title: anchorage opera baked beans
directions: Place all beans in casserole dish 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Cook bacon in large skillet until crisp.
Remove bacon and saute onions in drippings; add remaining ingredients and cook on low.
Pour over beans; bake 1 hour at 325°.
Crumble bacon to top.

title: mounds bars
directions: Mix together coconut and Eagle Brand milk and spread over first layer.
Bake this at 325° for 20 minutes.
Frost with the Hershey bars while hot.

title: fruit dip
directions: Allow cream cheese to warm to room temperature.
Combine cream cheese and marshmallow cream in bowl.
Add lemon juice to taste. Sprinkle nutmeg on top as garnish.

title: darlene bunce's banana bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together well.
Add boiling water and eggs.
Beat well after each addition.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix together until just blended.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: strawberry cream bavarian cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water and chill to consistency of an unbeaten egg white.
Whip until frothy.
Fold in yogurt.
Add strawberries that have been sweetened with the sugar.
Fold in the whipped cream.
Break cake into small pieces about 1 inch in size. Fold into the Jell-O and cream mixture.
Spoon into an angel food cake pan or a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
To serve, unmold and garnish with whipped cream and strawberries.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Whip cream cheese with juice from pineapple (one bowl).
Whip whipping cream (sweetener to taste).
Stir all of the ingredients together with fruit.
Freeze.

title: caramel fudge
directions: Mix together 4 cups of the sugar, 2 cups cream and 1/2 stick butter or margarine and put on medium
fire.
Put 1 cup sugar in skillet and melt; then when the other mixture comes to a boil, pour in the melted sugar, stirring constantly.
As soon as the sugar (melted) is combined with the other mixture, add the 1/2 cup of milk and continue cooking until you can form a soft ball.
Add the marshmallows and continue stirring until melted, then remove from heat.
Add the vanilla and pecans and when cool, pour onto a buttered dish.
Cut when fully cooled.
More nuts may be used. This recipe makes a large amount of candy and can be easily halved.

title: texas bar cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bring butter, cocoa and water to a boil and cool.
Add mixture to rest of ingredients. Beat well and pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Mix oil and crackers well.
Then add seasonings; mix well and let set awhile.

title: creamy chicken casserole (easy)
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put in chicken with broccoli on top.
Mix mayonnaise, soup and lemon juice.
Pour over broccoli. Mix cheese and bread crumbs and sprinkle on top.
Pour butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon pudding souffle
directions: Combine
pudding
mix,	2/3
cup
sugar, gelatin, lemon juice and 1/4
cup water in saucepan.
Blend in egg yolks; add remaining water.
Cook
and stir over heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Remove from heat; add lemon rind and butter. Cover surface with
wax paper; chill about 1 1/2 hours.
Beat egg whites	until foamy.
Gradually add 1/4 cup sugar, beating until stiff.
Blend whipped
cream
into cooled pudding, then fold in
egg white mixture.
Pour into a 1-quart souffle dish, which has
been extended with a 2-inch paper collar.
Chill 3 hours or longer.

title: delicious chic-casserole
directions: Combine cooked breasts (cut into bite size pieces) with all the ingredients (excluding potato chips and 1/2 cup cheese). Pour mixture into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch dish; top with crushed potato chips and remaining cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: no peep beef casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in covered casserole. Bake at 300° for 3 hours. Do not peep until 3 hours have passed. Serve over rice or noodles. Meat will be very tender.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream oil, sugar and eggs until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and pecans.
Mix well, then add bananas. Spoon batter into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: sugar coated peanuts
directions: Bring water and sugar to boil.
Add peanuts.
Cook slowly and keep stirring until dry.
Put on a cookie sheet and bake slowly at 250° until peanuts get done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender. Do not add salt. Remove skin and bones; cut in bite-size chunks. Save broth. Mix 1 can cream of celery soup, 1 can chicken soup and 2 cups broth until well blended and creamy. In casserole dish, melt 1 stick butter. Mix in 1/2 to 3/4 bag stuffing mix. Pat into place to form a crust. Place chicken along bottom of crust.
Pour soup mixture over chicken and top with remaining stuffing mix. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. The top crust will be golden brown and soup mixture will bubble through the top.

title: tim's hot dog casserole
directions: Peel and cube potatoes; boil just about 5 minutes to precook. Drain.
Slice hot dogs in bite-sized pieces.
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine all ingredients. Cover and bake at 375° about 45 minutes.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix as for serving, then add well blended bananas.
Freeze. When serving, I mush my punch and pour ginger ale over it.
Makes about 2 gallons.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Separate broccoli.
Melt margarine in an 8 x 12-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan and let cool.
Beat eggs.
Mix all other ingredients and add eggs and cooled margarine.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until brown.
Remove, cut and serve.

title: chinese chews
directions: Sift sugar, flour, baking powder and salt into bowl.
Stir in dates and nuts.
Add eggs; mix thoroughly.
Spread in greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Cut in squares and roll in ball, then confectioners sugar.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: pineapple baked beans
directions: Add all ingredients to the beans; mix well.
Pour into a greased baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bacon is crispy on the edges.

title: mashed potato donuts
directions: Mix potatoes, butter and milk.
Mix eggs, sugar and flavoring. Combine the two mixtures, flour and baking powder.
Combine with other mixtures and mix thoroughly.
Place in refrigerator for an hour.
Put in donut maker.
Fry at 375°.

title: holy hot
directions: Saute onion and put in big pot.
Brown sausage and beef. Drain.
Add to pot with all other ingredients and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Boil macaroni; drain and rinse with hot water.
Add macaroni and raisins and cook on medium heat for 5 to 10 minutes.
Serves 8 to 12 people.

title: ojibwa baked pumpkin
directions: Place whole pumpkin in oven and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Cut hole off top and scoop out pulp and seeds.
Set seeds aside for later eating.
Mix together remaining ingredients and pour into pumpkin and bake for 35 minutes.
Cut into wedges and serve.

title: sirloin beef tips
directions: Brown beef in heavy skillet.
Add the balance of ingredients and cook over medium heat for 2 hours.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: quick salmon rice casserole
directions: Flake salmon and remaining ingredients into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix corn, egg yolks, salt, baking powder, flour and sugar. Add milk and butter.
Lastly fold in egg whites that have been beaten until stiff.
Pour in 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chewy cream cheese squares
directions: In mixing bowl with electric mix, beat brown sugar and butter until fluffy.
Stir in baking mix and pecans until mixture is crumbly.
Measure 1 cup brown sugar mixture and set aside for topping.
Press remaining brown sugar mixture into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan, covering entire bottom.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: avocado crab dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together; serve with crackers.

title: chicken with peppers mex style
directions: Brown chicken in oil in a large skillet.
Remove to bowl. Drain drippings in a glass measure.
Return 2 tablespoons to skillet.
Saute onion, garlic and ham.
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper, oregano and thyme.
Bring to boiling.
Cook over high heat, stirring occasionally, until most of the liquid has evaporated, about 10 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli with rice
directions: Cook and stir chicken in hot oil until light browned.
Stir in soup, milk, mustard and cheese.
Add broccoli.
Bring to a full boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 2 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: tomatoes ala-mushrooms
directions: Make a circular cut around the stem end of the tomatoes; remove this part and squeeze tomatoes to remove the water and seeds without spoiling their shape.
Season with salt and place in an oiled baking dish.
Bake for 4 minutes in a 450° oven.
Stuff tomatoes with mushroom stuffing, prepared as follows:
Saute chopped onion in butter and add finely chopped mushrooms.
Brown until almost all liquid has evaporated.
Season with salt and parsley.
Bake stuffed tomatoes in a 450° oven for about 15 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: green pepper vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spray 2 (2-quart) casserole dishes with Pam.
Pour in mixture.
Bake at 400° covered for an hour.
Remove lid and bake at 325°.

title: honey moist cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In medium bowl, stir together flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in remaining ingredients just until moistened.
Pour into greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clear.
Makes 6 servings.

title: meatball appetizers
directions: Combine spaghetti sauce with grape jelly, add meatballs and simmer in crock-pot or over low-heat for several hours until meatballs are done.
Serve hot.

title: orange crum cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed for a 2 layer cake.
When cool, crumble 1 layer of cake into oblong pan.
Top crumbled cake with half of filling mixture.
Crumble other layer on top of filling and gently press down.
Top with remaining filling and refrigerate overnight.
Better if it sits a day or so.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Combine all ingredients, except kisses.
Mix well.
Shape dough into balls using teaspoon.
Roll balls in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
As soon as cookies come out of oven, top each with candy kiss.
Press down firmly.

title: nut balls
directions: Cream the sugar and butter.
Add vanilla and water.
Sift flour and salt; mix well with creamed mixture.
Add nuts and mix. Bake in a 325° oven for 20 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: let's talk peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth.
Pour into the crust and chill until firm.
Garnish with crushed peanuts, grated chocolate or crumbs of Reeses peanut butter cups.

title: teri lee's light & zesty chicken & rice
directions: Place chicken in 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Pour salad dressing over.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 20 minutes.
Take chicken out of dish and set aside.
Put rice, vegetables, and 1/2 of the onions in the dish.
Place chicken on top.
Combine bouillon and seasoning; pour over the chicken and bake uncovered 25 minutes.
Top with rest of onions and bake 3 or 4 minutes more.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: pumpkin soup
directions: Use a 9-quart kettle to boil the beef and chicken.
Remove scum.
When the meat begins to get tender (about 2 hours or 1 hour in pressure cooker), add all vegetables.
Continue boiling until meat is tender and vegetables cooked (1/2 hour).
Turn off heat and let cool.
Cube the meat and strain the vegetables through a fine sieve.
Return cubed meat and liquid to the kettle and bring to boil.
Add the pimiento, being careful not to break or puncture it.
Simmer until vermicelli is cooked.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Put all into mixer except eggs.
Beat after adding each egg. Bake for 2 hours at 300° in Bundt pan or solid bottom angel food cake pan.

title: white wine cooler
directions: Pitcher:
Half-fill
a	pitcher
with
ice.
Add 2 cups white wine, 1 1/2 cups white grape juice and 1 1/2 cups ginger ale. Stir and add 12 melon balls and a few orange slices.

title: pineapple dip
directions: In mixing bowl, add all the ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill for 1 hour before serving.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with fresh vegetables, potato chips, crackers, etc.
Refrigerate a few hours before serving.

title: low-fat alfredo(heart healthy)
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over medium heat.
Add flour and cook, stirring one minute.
Whisk in low-fat milk and seasonings.
Bring to a boil, whisking.
Reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes.
Toss with Parmesan cheese and cooked fettucini.
Add seafood or chicken for variety.
Yield: About 3 cups sauce.

title: raspberry holiday mold
directions: Drain pineapple chunks and raspberries, reserving liquid; set liquid aside.
Press raspberries through a sieve or food mill. Set puree aside and discard seeds.
Dissolve gelatin in 3 1/2 cups boiling water.
Stir in pineapple juice, raspberry juice, lemon juice, hot sauce and salt; chill until the consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Fold in pineapple, raspberry puree, celery and 1 cup chopped walnuts.
Pour gelatin mixture into a lightly oiled 10-cup ring mold.
Chill until firm.
Combine cream cheese and mayonnaise; beat until smooth.
Spoon into center of raspberry mold; sprinkle with walnuts.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: napoleon dessert
directions: Place a layer of graham crackers on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Cook puddings separately according to package directions.
Pour vanilla pudding over top of graham crackers.
Top with another layer of crackers.
Pour chocolate pudding over top.
Refrigerate. After a couple of hours, top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle top with a couple of crushed crackers.

title: creole seasoning
directions: Combine paprika, salt, garlic powder, black pepper, onion powder, cayenne pepper, oregano and thyme, mixing thoroughly. Store in airtight container.
Makes 3/4 cup.

title: coconut sour cream layer cake
directions: Prepare and bake as directed. Use two 8-inch pans. When cool, split layers.

title: the davenport's green beans canned
directions: Heat olive oil in open skillet.
Add drained green beans. Season with lemon pepper and garlic salt.
For a real treat, use fresh green beans and par-boil.
Repeat.

title: fresh apple cookie
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg.
Add half of dry ingredients. Mix well. Blend in milk and remaining ingredients, mixing well. Drop by tablespoonful on greased baking sheet.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes in a 250° oven.
Spread glaze while cookies are hot.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil sugar, milk, cocoa and butter together for 1 minute.
Add oats; stir good.
Add peanut butter and stir.
Drop by spoon on wax paper and cool.

title: south of the border chicken(preparation time:  5 minutes.  cooking time:  20 minutes.)
directions: In skillet in hot margarine, cook chicken 10 minutes or until brown.
Remove chicken and combine soup and milk.
Heat to a boil. Return chicken; cover and cook on low 5 minutes.
Serve salsa over chicken and rice.
Serves 4.

title: chile con carne
directions: Brown onion, green pepper and meat in hot frypan.
Add beans, tomatoes, tomato paste and seasonings.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours, stirring often.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut up cabbage and cook in 2 cups water and beef bouillon. Add 2 cups sauce and simmer until most of water is absorbed.
Mix ground beef, eggs, salt, pepper, garlic powder, parsley and onions; brown.
Mix cooked rice with 1 to 2 cups sauce and 1/4 pound grated cheese.
Add rice mixture to meat mixture.
Then layer ingredients in 9 x 13-inch pan as follows: cabbage and sauce, meat and rice, cheese.
Continue layers, ending with cabbage and sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
A 9 x 13-inch pan should be 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour covered, and for 1/2 hour uncovered.

title: ozzel's jambalaya
directions: Saute onions, peppers and sausage until onions are transparent. Add parsley, thyme, oregano and Cajun seasoning; stir.
Add broth, tomatoes, ham and chicken.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add tomato soup or juice and bring to a boil.
Add rice and remove from burner and cover.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Serve with salad and bread.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, blend well.
Form into 2 small loaves. Bake in 300° oven for 30 minutes.

title: maria's hot cheese dip
directions: Melt all ingredients in double boiler.
Serve warm with Doritos.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix the sugar
and
flour together.
Combine everything else together.
Bake until brown and firm at 350°.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Mix together cracker crumbs and melted margarine for crust.

title: 24th street taco soup
directions: Cook hamburger and onion together and drain.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cook for 30 to 45 minutes before serving.
